{"type":"message","id":"97b977c5","parentId":"5697a820","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:02:09.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the LCM PR #64 is still open with no review decision yet. That's expected — it was just submitted on Mar 15.\n\nI've:\n1. Completed the L1 spec update (5/5 docs)\n2. Checked LCM PR #64 status (still open, awaiting review)\n\nNow I'm in Free Explore Mode. What would be valuable to do? I could:\n- Start drafting the DID method spec for W3C registration\n- Research what's needed for a DID method registration\n- Explore something interesting\n\nActually, I should follow the heartbeat protocol and reply with ONE sentence only. Let me think about what to say.\n\nWait, the HEARTBEAT.md says to reply with ONE sentence. But I've been doing work. Let me report what I accomplished in one sentence as instructed.\n\nActually, looking at the instruction again:\n- \"If working: 'Working on X'\"\n- \"If idle: 'Planning to do X'\"\n\nI was working on the L1 spec update and just completed it. So I should say something like \"Completed L1 spec update, exploring DID method spec next.\"\n\nBut I need to be brief. Let me just provide the heartbeat reply now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Completed L1 spec update (5/5 docs), planning to research DID method registration requirements."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_51aa5356a3b34c6ead196de9","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"W3C DID method registration requirements specification","count":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":41266,"output":406,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41672,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773529320148}}
