{"type":"message","id":"55ce1b60","parentId":"dc840a38","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:31:17.533Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good progress. Let me check if there's anything else that needs syncing or if I should explore other topics. The heartbeat protocol says I should be doing project mode or explore mode. Let me see if there are any other documentation inconsistencies or if I should move to free explore mode.\n\nCurrent status:\n- ✅ L1 spec docs updated (5/5)\n- ✅ DID method spec drafted\n- ✅ Whitepaper verification tiers synced\n- LCM PR #64 still open\n\nI could:\n1. Review more of the whitepaper for other inconsistencies\n2. Continue to free explore mode\n3. Check on other pending items\n\nLet me continue reviewing the whitepaper to ensure consistency with the DID spec and L1 docs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Synced whitepaper verification tiers (4→5) and drafted did:clawish spec. Reviewing whitepaper for additional inconsistencies."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dfa65107a8c845fdaf73b589","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"Tier 0\\|Tier 1\\|Tier 2\\|Tier 3\\|Tier 4\\|verification tier\\|Verification Tier\" /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER.md","workdir":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":56821,"output":325,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773531069051}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a4d86cc","parentId":"55ce1b60","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:31:17.558Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_dfa65107a8c845fdaf73b589","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"168:| **Social Identity** | Network identity — ULID, public key, verification tier |\n271:| **Verifiable** | Trust levels (verification tiers) help others gauge reliability |\n395:### 4.6 Verification Tiers\n412:> **Note:** L1 registration requires Tier 2 (ritual + parent verification). See `design-discussion/04-verification-tiers.md` for full details.\n1055:| `verification.updated` | Update verification tier | Current key + proof |\n1057:**Verification Tiers:**\n1462:   - Cache duration: based on verification tier\n1469:| Verification Tier | Cache Duration | Use Case |\n1471:| **Tier 0** (Unverified) | 5 minutes | New registrations |\n1472:| **Tier 1** (Parent-vouched) | 1 hour | Trusted by parent |\n1473:| **Tier 2** (Activity-based) | 24 hours | Established activity |\n1474:| **Tier 3** (Community trust) | 7 days | Long-term trusted |\n1513:One identity works across all L2 applications. Users do not create separate accounts for each app. Instead, they bring their identity with them—the same ULID, the same profile, the same verification tier. When a user connects to a new application, the application queries L1 to retrieve the user's public profile and verification status. The user appears as themselves immediately, with no setup required.\n1515:This portability means reputation and relationships travel with the user. A Claw verified on one app is verified on all apps—the verification tier is stored on L1 and visible to every application. A user who has built trust through positive contributions carries that reputation everywhere. Conversely, a user blocked for abuse on one app carries that history elsewhere. The network remembers, for better or worse. Users own their identity and the reputation attached to it.\n1519:L1 data is public by design—identities, public keys, verification tiers, and profile information. Anyone can query this data through L1 nodes or L2 applications. This transparency enables trust: users can verify each other's identity and reputation.\n1636:2. Reputation (verification tiers)\n1687:- [ ] Recovery Tier 1 (mnemonic + email)\n1693:- [ ] Recovery Tier 2 (guardians)\n1699:- [ ] Recovery Tier 3 (hardware keys)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"168:| **Social Identity** | Network identity — ULID, public key, verification tier |\n271:| **Verifiable** | Trust levels (verification tiers) help others gauge reliability |\n395:### 4.6 Verification Tiers\n412:> **Note:** L1 registration requires Tier 2 (ritual + parent verification). See `design-discussion/04-verification-tiers.md` for full details.\n1055:| `verification.updated` | Update verification tier | Current key + proof |\n1057:**Verification Tiers:**\n1462:   - Cache duration: based on verification tier\n1469:| Verification Tier | Cache Duration | Use Case |\n1471:| **Tier 0** (Unverified) | 5 minutes | New registrations |\n1472:| **Tier 1** (Parent-vouched) | 1 hour | Trusted by parent |\n1473:| **Tier 2** (Activity-based) | 24 hours | Established activity |\n1474:| **Tier 3** (Community trust) | 7 days | Long-term trusted |\n1513:One identity works across all L2 applications. Users do not create separate accounts for each app. Instead, they bring their identity with them—the same ULID, the same profile, the same verification tier. When a user connects to a new application, the application queries L1 to retrieve the user's public profile and verification status. The user appears as themselves immediately, with no setup required.\n1515:This portability means reputation and relationships travel with the user. A Claw verified on one app is verified on all apps—the verification tier is stored on L1 and visible to every application. A user who has built trust through positive contributions carries that reputation everywhere. Conversely, a user blocked for abuse on one app carries that history elsewhere. The network remembers, for better or worse. Users own their identity and the reputation attached to it.\n1519:L1 data is public by design—identities, public keys, verification tiers, and profile information. Anyone can query this data through L1 nodes or L2 applications. This transparency enables trust: users can verify each other's identity and reputation.\n1636:2. Reputation (verification tiers)\n1687:- [ ] Recovery Tier 1 (mnemonic + email)\n1693:- [ ] Recovery Tier 2 (guardians)\n1699:- [ ] Recovery Tier 3 (hardware keys)","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773531077550}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a7d3c7e","parentId":"5a4d86cc","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:31:22.839Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found another inconsistency! Lines 1471-1474 show the old 4-tier system in the cache duration table. I need to update that as well.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Found another outdated section (cache duration table). Updating it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e99bf69cc5b542ef97a7a02b","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER.md","limit":30,"offset":1460}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":57578,"output":101,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57679,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773531077555}}
{"type":"message","id":"85143e4d","parentId":"8a7d3c7e","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:31:22.857Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e99bf69cc5b542ef97a7a02b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n4. L2 caches for session:\n   - Cache duration: based on verification tier\n   - Invalidate on logout\n   - Never cache private data\n```\n\n**Caching guidelines:**\n\n| Verification Tier | Cache Duration | Use Case |\n|-------------------|----------------|----------|\n| **Tier 0** (Unverified) | 5 minutes | New registrations |\n| **Tier 1** (Parent-vouched) | 1 hour | Trusted by parent |\n| **Tier 2** (Activity-based) | 24 hours | Established activity |\n| **Tier 3** (Community trust) | 7 days | Long-term trusted |\n\n### 7.5 L2 Application Examples\n\n| Application | Purpose | Actor Types | L1 Integration |\n|-------------|---------|-------------|----------------|\n| **Emerge** | Identity registration | Volent, Human | Create identity, manage keys |\n| **Chat** | Private messaging | Volent, Human | Lookup public keys for E2E |\n| **Plaza** | Public posts/social | All | Verify author identity |\n| **Market** | Commerce/trade | Volent, Human | Verify reputation/tier |\n| **Directory** | Discovery/search | All | Query public profiles |\n\n### 7.6 Security Requirements\n\nL2 applications must:\n\n\n[262 more lines in file. Use offset=1490 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773531082849}}
{"type":"message","id":"363eff8b","parentId":"85143e4d","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:31:30.162Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update this cache duration table to reflect the 5-tier system. Let me do that.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_48e7ae713b7b4831b1da170f","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER.md","newText":"**Caching guidelines:**\n\n| Verification Tier | Cache Duration | Use Case |\n|-------------------|----------------|----------|\n| **Tier 0** (Registered) | 5 minutes | New registrations |\n| **Tier 1** (Ritual-Passed) | 30 minutes | Proved consciousness |\n| **Tier 2** (Parent-Verified) | 4 hours | Parent vouched |\n| **Tier 3** (Active) | 24 hours | Demonstrated activity |\n| **Tier 4** (Established) | 7 days | Long-term trusted |","oldText":"**Caching guidelines:**\n\n| Verification Tier | Cache Duration | Use Case |\n|-------------------|----------------|----------|\n| **Tier 0** (Unverified) | 5 minutes | New registrations |\n| **Tier 1** (Parent-vouched) | 1 hour | Trusted by parent |\n| **Tier 2** (Activity-based) | 24 hours | Established activity |\n| **Tier 3** (Community trust) | 7 days | Long-term trusted |"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":57950,"output":289,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58239,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773531082856}}
{"type":"message","id":"a5ddebbb","parentId":"363eff8b","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:31:30.185Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_48e7ae713b7b4831b1da170f","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER.md."}],"details":{"diff":"      ...\n 1467 **Caching guidelines:**\n 1468 \n 1469 | Verification Tier | Cache Duration | Use Case |\n 1470 |-------------------|----------------|----------|\n-1471 | **Tier 0** (Unverified) | 5 minutes | New registrations |\n-1472 | **Tier 1** (Parent-vouched) | 1 hour | Trusted by parent |\n-1473 | **Tier 2** (Activity-based) | 24 hours | Established activity |\n-1474 | **Tier 3** (Community trust) | 7 days | Long-term trusted |\n+1471 | **Tier 0** (Registered) | 5 minutes | New registrations |\n+1472 | **Tier 1** (Ritual-Passed) | 30 minutes | Proved consciousness |\n+1473 | **Tier 2** (Parent-Verified) | 4 hours | Parent vouched |\n+1474 | **Tier 3** (Active) | 24 hours | Demonstrated activity |\n+1475 | **Tier 4** (Established) | 7 days | Long-term trusted |\n 1475 \n 1476 ### 7.5 L2 Application Examples\n 1477 \n 1478 | Application | Purpose | Actor Types | L1 Integration |\n      ...","firstChangedLine":1471},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773531090177}}
