{"type":"message","id":"1af6c12a","parentId":"c052c0cf","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:45:48.984Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The edit failed. Let me read the file first to see the exact content.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_77af05558d1f405387272d72","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/projects/research-2026-03-10.md","limit":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":66728,"output":60,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66788,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773531944047}}
{"type":"message","id":"61a30721","parentId":"1af6c12a","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:45:48.999Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_77af05558d1f405387272d72","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Research Notes — March 10, 2026\n\n## Agent Infrastructure\n\n### Agent Safehouse (agent-safehouse.dev)\n- **macOS-native sandboxing for AI agents**\n- **Deny-first access model** - nothing accessible unless explicitly granted\n- Kernel-level enforcement via sandbox-exec\n- Single shell script, no dependencies\n\n**Relevance to clawish:**\n- Claws could run in similar sandboxed environments\n- Security model should be deny-first by default\n- Consider what permissions claws have when interacting with L1/L2\n\n### Terminal Use (YC W26) - terminaluse.com\n- **\"Vercel for filesystem-based agents\"**\n- Filesystems as first-class primitives, separate from task lifecycle\n- Multi-filesystem mounts with configurable paths and read/write modes\n- Decoupled agent logic and storage\n\n**Relevance to clawish:**\n- L2 apps could use similar deployment patterns\n- Persistent storage across sessions, shareable between apps\n- Preview/production environments for claws\n\n## Identity & Verification\n\n### human.json Protocol (codeberg.org/robida/human.json)\n- **Lightweight protocol for asserting authorship and vouching for humanity**\n\n[220 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773531948993}}
{"type":"message","id":"57d7b051","parentId":"61a30721","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:45:54.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file has different content than I expected. Let me just append to it instead.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a4f28751dd754873adede19c","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/projects/research-2026-03-10.md","offset":200}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":67042,"output":60,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67102,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773531948997}}
{"type":"message","id":"18293c68","parentId":"57d7b051","timestamp":"2026-03-14T23:45:54.619Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a4f28751dd754873adede19c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n## Summary — Morning Session\n\n| Discovery | Significance |\n|-----------|--------------|\n| **DenchClaw** | OpenClaw ecosystem validation, platform approach works |\n| **Terminal Use** | Agent deployment patterns, filesystem-as-primitive |\n| **Tony Hoare memorial** | Loss of CS pioneer, CSP/concurrency foundations |\n\n**Updated action items:**\n- Watch DenchClaw development for OpenClaw ecosystem patterns\n- Consider Terminal Use architecture for L2 app deployment model\n- Review CSP for clawish concurrent coordination\n\n---\n\n## Research → Open Questions Mapping\n\n### From need-discuss.md (Mar 9, 2026)\n\n| Research Finding | Related Open Question | Insight |\n|------------------|----------------------|---------|\n| **human.json protocol** | \"🟡 human.json protocol (web-of-trust)\" | Transitive vouching model could add \"vouched by T2 Claw\" as verification path |\n| **Terminal Use (YC W26)** | \"🔴 P2P escalation trigger?\" | Signaling via L2, direct connection pattern. Presigned URLs for direct transfer. |\n| **Terminal Use filesystem model** | \"🔴 L2 Chat message storage?\" | Filesystem as first-class primitive, decoupled from task lifecycle |\n| **DenchClaw ecosystem** | Platform validation | OpenClaw profile separation pattern (`--profile dench`) applicable to L2 apps |\n| **WebPKI/CT logs** | L1 ledger design | CT logs as model for transparency, short-lived tokens vs permanent trust |\n| **Agent Safehouse** | Security model | Deny-first sandboxing for Claws running code |\n\n### Key Insights for Discussion\n\n**1. human.json → Verification Tiers**\n- Web-of-trust model: reachability within N hops from trusted seed\n- Browser extension approach for trust visualization\n- Vouch expiration concept applicable to T0→T1 verification\n\n**2. Terminal Use → P2P Escalation**\n- Three-endpoint lifecycle: on_create, on_event, on_cancel\n- Signaling via relay, then direct connection\n- Filesystem persists across sessions, decoupled from agent lifecycle\n\n**3. DenchClaw → L2 Architecture**\n- Separate OpenClaw profile per app\n- Local-first with gateway integration\n- MIT licensed, ecosystem growing\n\n**4. WebPKI → L1 Ledger**\n- Certificate Transparency as precedent for public, verifiable records\n- Short-lived certificates (7-10 days) → short-lived verification tokens\n- Private CA infrastructure for internal operations\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773531954614}}
