{"type":"message","id":"a25ba4e1","parentId":"7351dd3b","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:28:19.211Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is saying not to push the did:clawish spec yet because their server is not ready. He's referring to the W3C DID method registration - we shouldn't submit the PR to w3c/did-extensions until the clawish server/infrastructure is ready.\n\nI should acknowledge this and make sure I don't submit anything to W3C without his go-ahead. The spec is drafted locally, which is fine - it just shouldn't be submitted externally yet.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Got it — the `did:clawish` spec stays local for now. No W3C PR until the server is ready.\n\nThe spec is safely saved in `projects/clawish/specs/did-method-spec.md` — ready whenever you are.\n\nIs there anything else you'd like me to work on this morning?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":104891,"output":223,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105114,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773534488015}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f6dac8e","parentId":"a25ba4e1","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:29:01.580Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b546b9a06e8a8c3f9d93b472e9c6\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 08:29 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b546b9a06e8a8c3f9d93b472e9c6]\n任亚伦: tell me your overnight research"}],"timestamp":1773534541565}}
{"type":"message","id":"d9600227","parentId":"3f6dac8e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:29:18.505Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants me to summarize my overnight research. Let me pull from what I've gathered during this morning's heartbeats.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here's what I explored this morning:\n\n## 1. W3C DID Method Registration\n\n**What I learned:**\n- Registering `did:clawish` requires a JSON entry + specification URL\n- Process: Fork → Add JSON → PR → 2 maintainer approvals → 7-30 days\n- Drafted full spec v0.1.0 covering: DID syntax, CRUD operations, security/privacy\n\n**Key decision needed:** Where to host the spec (clawish.com or GitHub)?\n\n---\n\n## 2. MCP Architecture for L2 Applications\n\n**The mapping:**\n| MCP Concept | clawish Equivalent |\n|-------------|-------------------|\n| MCP Host | Claw (the AI agent) |\n| MCP Server | L2 Application (Chat, Plaza, etc.) |\n| MCP Primitives | Tools, Resources, Prompts |\n\n**Why it matters:**\n- L2 apps can expose standard MCP primitives\n- Any MCP-compatible AI could use clawish L2 apps\n- 10 SDKs available (TypeScript recommended)\n\n**Auth challenge:** MCP uses OAuth 2.1, but Claws use Ed25519. Options:\n- MVP: Direct signing (simpler, non-standard)\n- Phase 2: Custom grant type (standard, more work)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Agent Infrastructure\n\n**db9.ai** — Serverless Postgres for AI agents:\n- Hybrid storage (tables + files)\n- Auto-embeddings, vector search\n- **Has OpenClaw integration** — streams events, JSONL audit logs\n- Could be useful for L2 app storage or Claw memory\n\n**Anthropic** — $100M Claude Partner Network:\n- Ecosystem building around AI agents\n- Certification model (Claude Certified Architect)\n\n**Han** — Korean programming language:\n- All keywords in Hangul\n- Localization precedent: programming doesn't have to be English-centric\n\n---\n\n## 4. Documentation Sync\n\nFound and fixed inconsistencies:\n- WHITEPAPER.md had 4-tier verification in multiple places\n- Updated to 5-tier system everywhere\n- All L1 docs now consistent\n\n---\n\nWant me to dive deeper into any of these?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":105199,"output":494,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105693,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773534541574}}
