{"type":"message","id":"e9cb60fa","parentId":"3e06791e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:35:43.644Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_47f2a27362dd4106a4a5354b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type {\n  ConversationStore,\n  MessageRecord,\n  MessageSearchResult,\n} from \"./store/conversation-store.js\";\nimport type {\n  SummaryStore,\n  SummaryRecord,\n  SummarySearchResult,\n  LargeFileRecord,\n} from \"./store/summary-store.js\";\n\n// ── Public interfaces ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport interface DescribeResult {\n  id: string;\n  type: \"summary\" | \"file\";\n  /** Summary-specific fields */\n  summary?: {\n    conversationId: number;\n    kind: \"leaf\" | \"condensed\";\n    content: string;\n    depth: number;\n    tokenCount: number;\n    descendantCount: number;\n    descendantTokenCount: number;\n    sourceMessageTokenCount: number;\n    fileIds: string[];\n    parentIds: string[];\n    childIds: string[];\n    messageIds: number[];\n    earliestAt: Date | null;\n    latestAt: Date | null;\n    subtree: Array<{\n      summaryId: string;\n      parentSummaryId: string | null;\n      depthFromRoot: number;\n      kind: \"leaf\" | \"condensed\";\n      depth: number;\n      tokenCount: number;\n      descendantCount: number;\n      descendantTokenCount: number;\n      sourceMessageTokenCount: number;\n      earliestAt: Date | null;\n      latestAt: Date | null;\n      childCount: number;\n      path: string;\n    }>;\n    createdAt: Date;\n  };\n  /** File-specific fields */\n  file?: {\n    conversationId: number;\n    fileName: string | null;\n    mimeType: string | null;\n    byteSize: number | null;\n    storageUri: string;\n    explorationSummary: string | null;\n    createdAt: Date;\n  };\n}\n\nexport interface GrepInput {\n  query: string;\n  mode: \"regex\" | \"full_text\";\n  scope: \"messages\" | \"summaries\" | \"both\";\n  conversationId?: number;\n  since?: Date;\n  before?: Date;\n  limit?: number;\n}\n\nexport interface GrepResult {\n  messages: MessageSearchResult[];\n  summaries: SummarySearchResult[];\n  totalMatches: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ExpandInput {\n  summaryId: string;\n\n[278 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773534943632}}
{"type":"message","id":"91f4add8","parentId":"e9cb60fa","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:35:48.526Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the retrieval.ts, I can see it uses `grep` (regex and full_text search), not embeddings. Let me check the FTS5 documentation mentioned in the README.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6dd5bc10974b472d9bd3d462","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/extensions/lossless-claw/docs/fts5.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":110626,"output":83,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110709,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773534943641}}
{"type":"message","id":"f452f118","parentId":"91f4add8","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:35:48.547Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_6dd5bc10974b472d9bd3d462","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Optional: enable FTS5 for fast full-text search\n\n`lossless-claw` works without FTS5 as of the current release. When FTS5 is unavailable in the\nNode runtime that runs the OpenClaw gateway, the plugin:\n\n- keeps persisting messages and summaries\n- falls back from `\"full_text\"` search to a slower `LIKE`-based search\n- loses FTS ranking/snippet quality\n\nIf you want native FTS5 search performance and ranking, the **exact Node runtime that runs the\ngateway** must have SQLite FTS5 compiled in.\n\n## Probe the gateway runtime\n\nRun this with the same `node` binary your gateway uses:\n\n```bash\nnode --input-type=module - <<'NODE'\nimport { DatabaseSync } from 'node:sqlite';\nconst db = new DatabaseSync(':memory:');\nconst options = db.prepare('pragma compile_options').all().map((row) => row.compile_options);\n\nconsole.log(options.filter((value) => value.includes('FTS')).join('\\n') || 'no fts compile options');\n\ntry {\n  db.exec(\"CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE t USING fts5(content)\");\n  console.log(\"fts5: ok\");\n} catch (err) {\n  console.log(\"fts5: fail\");\n  console.log(err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err));\n}\nNODE\n```\n\nExpected output:\n\n```text\nENABLE_FTS5\nfts5: ok\n```\n\nIf you get `fts5: fail`, build or install an FTS5-capable Node and point the gateway at that runtime.\n\n## Build an FTS5-capable Node on macOS\n\nThis workflow was verified with Node `v22.15.0`.\n\n```bash\ncd ~/Projects\ngit clone --depth 1 --branch v22.15.0 https://github.com/nodejs/node.git node-fts5\ncd node-fts5\n```\n\nEdit `deps/sqlite/sqlite.gyp` and add `SQLITE_ENABLE_FTS5` to the `defines` list for the `sqlite`\ntarget:\n\n```diff\n 'defines': [\n   'SQLITE_DEFAULT_MEMSTATUS=0',\n+  'SQLITE_ENABLE_FTS5',\n   'SQLITE_ENABLE_MATH_FUNCTIONS',\n   'SQLITE_ENABLE_SESSION',\n   'SQLITE_ENABLE_PREUPDATE_HOOK'\n ],\n```\n\nImportant:\n\n- patch `deps/sqlite/sqlite.gyp`, not only `node.gyp`\n- `node:sqlite` uses the embedded SQLite built from `deps/sqlite/sqlite.gyp`\n\nBuild the runtime:\n\n```bash\n./configure --prefix=\"$PWD/out-install\"\nmake -j8 node\n```\n\nExpose the binary under a Node-compatible basename that OpenClaw recognizes:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/Projects/node-fts5/bin\nln -sfn ~/Projects/node-fts5/out/Release/node ~/Projects/node-fts5/bin/node-22.15.0\n```\n\nUse a basename like `node-22.15.0`, `node`, or `nodejs`. Names like\n`node-v22.15.0-fts5` may not be recognized correctly by OpenClaw's CLI/runtime parsing.\n\nVerify the new runtime:\n\n```bash\n~/Projects/node-fts5/bin/node-22.15.0 --version\n~/Projects/node-fts5/bin/node-22.15.0 --input-type=module - <<'NODE'\nimport { DatabaseSync } from 'node:sqlite';\nconst db = new DatabaseSync(':memory:');\ndb.exec(\"CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE t USING fts5(content)\");\nconsole.log(\"fts5: ok\");\nNODE\n```\n\n## Point the OpenClaw gateway at that runtime on macOS\n\nBack up the existing LaunchAgent plist first:\n\n```bash\ncp ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.gateway.plist \\\n  ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.gateway.plist.bak-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)\n```\n\nReplace the runtime path, then reload the agent:\n\n```bash\n/usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c 'Set :ProgramArguments:0 /Users/youruser/Projects/node-fts5/bin/node-22.15.0' \\\n  ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.gateway.plist\n\nlaunchctl bootout gui/$UID ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.gateway.plist 2>/dev/null || true\nlaunchctl bootstrap gui/$UID ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.gateway.plist\nlaunchctl kickstart -k gui/$UID/ai.openclaw.gateway\n```\n\nVerify the live runtime:\n\n```bash\nlaunchctl print gui/$UID/ai.openclaw.gateway | sed -n '1,80p'\n```\n\nYou should see:\n\n```text\nprogram = /Users/youruser/Projects/node-fts5/bin/node-22.15.0\n```\n\n## Verify `lossless-claw`\n\nCheck the logs:\n\n```bash\ntail -n 60 ~/.openclaw/logs/gateway.log\ntail -n 60 ~/.openclaw/logs/gateway.err.log\n```\n\nYou want:\n\n- `[gateway] [lcm] Plugin loaded ...`\n- no new `no such module: fts5`\n\nThen force one turn through the gateway and verify the DB fills:\n\n```bash\n/Users/youruser/Projects/node-fts5/bin/node-22.15.0 \\\n  /path/to/openclaw/dist/index.js \\\n  agent --session-id fts5-smoke --message 'Reply with exactly: ok' --timeout 60\n\nsqlite3 ~/.openclaw/lcm.db '\n  select count(*) as conversations from conversations;\n  select count(*) as messages from messages;\n  select count(*) as summaries from summaries;\n'\n```\n\nThose counts should increase after a real turn.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773534948535}}
{"type":"message","id":"e7f65db5","parentId":"f452f118","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:36:01.880Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. LCM does NOT use embeddings. It uses:\n1. Regex search\n2. Full-text search (FTS5 if available, otherwise LIKE-based fallback)\n\nLet me summarize the LCM settings for Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] LCM does **not** do embeddings. It uses text-based search:\n\n## LCM Search Methods\n\n| Mode | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| **regex** | Regular expression matching |\n| **full_text** | FTS5 (if available) or LIKE-based fallback |\n\nNo vector/semantic search — it's all text matching.\n\n---\n\n## Current LCM Settings (defaults)\n\n| Setting | Value | Purpose |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| `freshTailCount` | 32 | Recent messages protected from compaction |\n| `contextThreshold` | 0.75 | Trigger compaction at 75% of context window |\n| `incrementalMaxDepth` | 0 | How deep auto-condensation goes (0 = leaf only) |\n| `leafMinFanout` | 8 | Min raw messages per leaf summary |\n| `condensedMinFanout` | 4 | Min summaries per condensed node |\n\n---\n\n## No Embedding Config\n\nLCM stores:\n- **Raw messages** in SQLite\n- **Summaries** (LLM-generated text) in SQLite\n- **DAG structure** (summary → source messages)\n\nSearch is text-only. If you want semantic search, we'd need to add:\n1. Embedding generation (at compaction time?)\n2. Vector storage (in SQLite with vec extension, or separate DB)\n3. Similarity search in `lcm_grep`\n\nWant me to explore adding embeddings to LCM?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":108146,"output":379,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108525,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773534948543}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5359fa7","parentId":"e7f65db5","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:44:43.359Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5454415a30a4c49e362523c5779\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 08:44 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5454415a30a4c49e362523c5779]\n任亚伦: tell me what's.these.value for?"}],"timestamp":1773535483344}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b738327","parentId":"d5359fa7","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:45:00.474Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants me to explain the LCM configuration values and what they do. Let me explain each one clearly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here's what each LCM setting controls:\n\n## Core Settings\n\n| Setting | Default | What it does |\n|---------|---------|--------------|\n| `freshTailCount` | 32 | **Protects last N messages** from being compacted. These stay raw in context so the model has recent conversation continuity. |\n| `contextThreshold` | 0.75 | **Triggers compaction** when context hits 75% of model's window. Leaves headroom for the model's response. |\n\n## DAG Structure Settings\n\n| Setting | Default | What it does |\n|---------|---------|--------------|\n| `leafMinFanout` | 8 | **Min messages per leaf summary**. Won't summarize fewer than 8 messages into one leaf node. |\n| `condensedMinFanout` | 4 | **Min summaries per condensed node**. Won't condense fewer than 4 leaf summaries into a higher-level node. |\n| `condensedMinFanoutHard` | 2 | **Relaxed fanout** for forced compaction when context is critically full. |\n| `incrementalMaxDepth` | 0 | **How deep auto-condensation goes**. 0 = only leaf summaries, -1 = unlimited cascade (recommended for deep DAGs). |\n\n## Token Budgets\n\n| Setting | Default | What it does |\n|---------|---------|--------------|\n| `leafChunkTokens` | 20000 | **Max source tokens** fed to LLM for one leaf summary. |\n| `leafTargetTokens` | 1200 | **Target size** for leaf summaries (compression ratio ~17x). |\n| `condensedTargetTokens` | 2000 | **Target size** for condensed summaries. |\n| `maxExpandTokens` | 4000 | **Token cap** when drilling into summaries with `lcm_expand`. |\n\n## Summary\n\n- **freshTailCount=32** → Keep last 32 messages raw (continuity)\n- **contextThreshold=0.75** → Compact at 75% full (safety margin)\n- **leafMinFanout=8** → Summarize in chunks of 8+ messages\n- **incrementalMaxDepth=-1** → Let DAG cascade unlimited (deeper = more compressed)\n\nWant me to check your current settings vs defaults?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":111050,"output":520,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111570,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773535483352}}
