{"type":"message","id":"133c7aea","parentId":"d27d991a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:47:36.579Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b545454b714a0c4c9b82bb421bc9\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 08:47 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b545454b714a0c4c9b82bb421bc9]\n任亚伦: dag is?"}],"timestamp":1773535656563}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5cbec0c","parentId":"133c7aea","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:47:49.684Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking what DAG means in the context of LCM.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **DAG = Directed Acyclic Graph**\n\nIn LCM, it's the structure for organizing summaries:\n\n```\n                    [Condensed Summary]\n                   /         |         \\\n          [Leaf 1]       [Leaf 2]       [Leaf 3]\n          /  |  \\         / | \\          / |  \\\n       [msg][msg][msg]  [msg][msg][msg] [msg][msg][msg]\n```\n\n## How it works\n\n1. **Leaf nodes** = summaries of 8+ raw messages\n2. **Condensed nodes** = summaries of 4+ leaf summaries\n3. **Higher levels** = summaries of condensed summaries (cascade unlimited with `incrementalMaxDepth=-1`)\n\n## Why DAG (not flat)\n\n| Flat | DAG |\n|------|-----|\n| One summary for everything | Hierarchical compression |\n| Lose detail at edges | Can drill into any branch |\n| Fixed granularity | Multiple zoom levels |\n\n## The \"lossless\" part\n\n- Raw messages are **never deleted** — just summarized\n- Each summary links to its source messages/summaries\n- `lcm_expand` drills down to recover original detail\n- `lcm_grep` searches across all levels\n\nSo you get **compression + retrievability**. Nothing lost, just organized."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":109817,"output":303,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110120,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773535656571}}
{"type":"message","id":"eece25aa","parentId":"e5cbec0c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:49:13.918Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54546e4344a4c2bff43a98bb700\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 08:49 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54546e4344a4c2bff43a98bb700]\n任亚伦: ok, that's all the setting?"}],"timestamp":1773535753899}}
{"type":"message","id":"84843c4c","parentId":"eece25aa","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:49:34.233Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking if the settings I showed are all the LCM settings. Let me check if there are more settings I haven't covered.\n\nLooking at the README, I see there are also:\n- LCM_LARGE_FILE_TOKEN_THRESHOLD\n- LCM_LARGE_FILE_SUMMARY_PROVIDER\n- LCM_LARGE_FILE_SUMMARY_MODEL\n- LCM_SUMMARY_MODEL\n- LCM_SUMMARY_PROVIDER\n- LCM_AUTOCOMPACT_DISABLED\n- LCM_PRUNE_HEARTBEAT_OK\n\nI should mention these as well.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] There are a few more:\n\n## Large File Handling\n\n| Setting | Default | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `largeFileTokenThreshold` | 25000 | Files bigger than this are stored separately, not in context |\n| `largeFileSummaryProvider` | \"\" | Override provider for large-file summaries |\n| `largeFileSummaryModel` | \"\" | Override model for large-file summaries |\n\n## Summarization Control\n\n| Setting | Default | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `summaryModel` | *(from OpenClaw)* | Which model to use for generating summaries |\n| `summaryProvider` | *(from OpenClaw)* | Which provider for summarization |\n\n## Behavior Flags\n\n| Setting | Default | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `autocompactDisabled` | false | If true, turns off automatic compaction after turns |\n| `pruneHeartbeatOk` | false | If true, deletes `HEARTBEAT_OK` cycles from storage |\n\n## Database\n\n| Setting | Default | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `databasePath` | `~/.openclaw/lcm.db` | Where SQLite database lives |\n\n---\n\nThat's the full list. The core ones you'd actually tune:\n- `freshTailCount`, `contextThreshold`, `incrementalMaxDepth`\n- `leafMinFanout`, `condensedMinFanout`\n- `leafTargetTokens`, `condensedTargetTokens`\n\nThe rest are for special cases (large files, model overrides, debugging)."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":110323,"output":477,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110800,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773535753911}}
{"type":"message","id":"2783ea70","parentId":"84843c4c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:51:49.341Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5454648844acc29ea5e18e44643\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 08:51 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5454648844acc29ea5e18e44643]\n任亚伦: ok, show me what context engine standard about, i think.there are more"}],"timestamp":1773535909324}}
