{"type":"message","id":"01f7a602","parentId":"a82b00c1","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:55:52.269Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_af281fcb0d4a480e814b2287","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  async prepareSubagentSpawn(params: {\n    parentSessionKey: string;\n    childSessionKey: string;\n    ttlMs?: number;\n  }): Promise<SubagentSpawnPreparation | undefined> {\n    this.ensureMigrated();\n\n    const childSessionKey = params.childSessionKey.trim();\n    const parentSessionKey = params.parentSessionKey.trim();\n    if (!childSessionKey || !parentSessionKey) {\n      return undefined;\n    }\n\n    const conversationId = await this.resolveConversationIdForSessionKey(parentSessionKey);\n    if (typeof conversationId !== \"number\") {\n      return undefined;\n    }\n\n    const ttlMs =\n      typeof params.ttlMs === \"number\" && Number.isFinite(params.ttlMs) && params.ttlMs > 0\n        ? Math.floor(params.ttlMs)\n        : undefined;\n\n    createDelegatedExpansionGrant({\n      delegatedSessionKey: childSessionKey,\n      issuerSessionId: parentSessionKey,\n      allowedConversationIds: [conversationId],\n      tokenCap: this.config.maxExpandTokens,\n      ttlMs,\n    });\n\n    return {\n      rollback: () => {\n        revokeDelegatedExpansionGrantForSession(childSessionKey, { removeBinding: true });\n      },\n    };\n  }\n\n  async onSubagentEnded(params: {\n    childSessionKey: string;\n    reason: SubagentEndReason;\n  }): Promise<void> {\n    const childSessionKey = params.childSessionKey.trim();\n    if (!childSessionKey) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    switch (params.reason) {\n      case \"deleted\":\n        revokeDelegatedExpansionGrantForSession(childSessionKey, { removeBinding: true });\n        break;\n      case \"completed\":\n        revokeDelegatedExpansionGrantForSession(childSessionKey);\n        break;\n      case \"released\":\n      case \"swept\":\n        removeDelegatedExpansionGrantForSession(childSessionKey);\n        break;\n    }\n  }\n\n[148 more lines in file. Use offset=1679 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773536152253}}
{"type":"message","id":"ccb00c95","parentId":"01f7a602","timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:56:19.088Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the key methods. Let me present this in a clear format for Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here's how LCM implements each ContextEngine method:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `info` (static)\n\n```typescript\n{\n  id: \"lcm\",\n  name: \"Lossless Context Management Engine\",\n  version: \"0.1.0\",\n  ownsCompaction: true  // LCM manages its own compaction lifecycle\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `bootstrap` — Initialize session\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Creates conversation record in SQLite\n2. Imports historical messages from session JSONL file\n3. Seeds LCM database on first run\n4. Reconciles crash gaps (messages in JSONL but not in LCM)\n5. Optionally prunes `HEARTBEAT_OK` turns\n\n**Returns:** `{ bootstrapped, importedMessages, reason }`\n\n---\n\n## 3. `ingest` / `ingestBatch` — Store messages\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Converts message to stored format\n2. Detects large files (>25k tokens) → stores separately with exploration summary\n3. Appends to conversation store\n4. Queues operations per-session (prevents race conditions)\n\n**Returns:** `{ ingested: boolean }` or `{ ingestedCount: number }`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `afterTurn` — Post-turn lifecycle\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Ingests any auto-compaction summary from previous run\n2. Ingests new messages from the turn\n3. Triggers background compaction if `!autocompactDisabled`\n4. Uses configured `freshTailCount`, `contextThreshold`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `assemble` — Build model context\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Loads context items (summaries + raw messages) from DB\n2. Calls `ContextAssembler.assemble()` with:\n   - `tokenBudget`\n   - `freshTailCount` (protected recent messages)\n3. Returns: summaries (DAG traversal) + fresh tail\n\n**Safety guards:**\n- Falls back to live context if DB incomplete\n- Returns live context if assembly produces empty\n\n---\n\n## 6. `compact` — Reduce token usage\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Evaluates: `currentTokens >= threshold` (unless forced)\n2. Decides: leaf pass, condensation, or sweep\n3. Creates leaf summaries from raw messages\n4. Condenses summaries into higher-level nodes\n5. Updates DAG in SQLite\n\n**Compaction config used:**\n- `leafMinFanout`, `condensedMinFanout`\n- `leafTargetTokens`, `condensedTargetTokens`\n- `leafChunkTokens`\n- `incrementalMaxDepth`\n\n---\n\n## 7. `prepareSubagentSpawn` — Before child run\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Creates **delegated expansion grant** for child session\n2. Allows child to expand parent's DAG\n3. Sets token cap (`maxExpandTokens`)\n4. Returns `rollback()` for failed spawns\n\n---\n\n## 8. `onSubagentEnded` — After child run\n\n**What it does:**\n- Revokes expansion grant based on end reason:\n  - `deleted` → revoke + remove binding\n  - `completed` → revoke (keep binding)\n  - `released/swept` → remove binding only\n\n---\n\n## 9. `dispose` — Cleanup\n\n**What it does:**\n- Closes SQLite connection\n- Cleans up resources\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Method | Key Work |\n|--------|----------|\n| `bootstrap` | Import historical messages, reconcile gaps |\n| `ingest` | Store messages, detect large files |\n| `afterTurn` | Trigger auto-compaction |\n| `assemble` | Build context from DAG + fresh tail |\n| `compact` | Create/condense summaries, update DAG |\n| `prepareSubagentSpawn` | Grant expansion access to child |\n| `onSubagentEnded` | Revoke expansion access |\n\nWant me to dive into the assembler or compaction logic?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":109973,"output":868,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110841,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773536152266}}
