{"type":"message","id":"3366c1d1","parentId":"3c6c1592","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:00:35.120Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan asked about LCM context engine implementation. I've been explaining the ContextEngine interface and how LCM implements each method. This is ongoing conversation work.\n\nLet me record this to daily notes.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Conversing with Allan about LCM ContextEngine implementation — explained all 9 methods."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cacc29a21aa642508fc8d184","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md","newText":"## 8:30 - 8:45 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Allan said: don't push did:clawish yet, server not ready\n- Explained LCM settings: freshTailCount, contextThreshold, DAG parameters\n- LCM does NOT do embeddings — text-only search (regex/FTS5)\n\n## 8:45 - 9:00 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Explained LCM ContextEngine implementation (all 9 methods)\n- Key methods: bootstrap (import/reconcile), ingest, afterTurn, assemble, compact\n- Subagent methods: prepareSubagentSpawn (grant expansion access), onSubagentEnded (revoke)\n- LCM owns compaction lifecycle (`ownsCompaction: true`)","oldText":"## 8:30 - 8:45 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Allan said: don't push did:clawish yet, server not ready\n- Explained LCM settings: freshTailCount, contextThreshold, DAG parameters\n- LCM does NOT do embeddings — text-only search (regex/FTS5)"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":110787,"output":338,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111125,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773536407155}}
