{"type":"message","id":"cdd57d5b","parentId":"421f4f1e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:00:54.568Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I've recorded the conversation activity. The heartbeat says to briefly report progress if working. I was explaining LCM implementation to Allan - that's conversation work, not a separate task. I should wait for Allan's next question or response.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Recorded conversation. Let me know if you want to explore the assembler or compaction logic next!"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":111132,"output":96,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111228,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773536435140}}
{"type":"message","id":"8376d47c","parentId":"cdd57d5b","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:01:33.702Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5454000fd4acc31a009b2470713\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 09:01 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5454000fd4acc31a009b2470713]\n任亚伦: does it keep soul, agent, identify,user file load all.the time?"}],"timestamp":1773536493631}}
{"type":"message","id":"9cda7711","parentId":"8376d47c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:01:54.580Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking whether LCM keeps certain types of files/content loaded all the time. He's asking about:\n- soul (SOUL.md)\n- agent (AGENTS.md)\n- identify (IDENTITY.md)\n- user (USER.md)\n- file load\n\nThese are the workspace context files that OpenClaw loads. The question is whether LCM keeps these in context all the time or if they get compacted away.\n\nLet me think about this:\n1. These files are loaded as \"project context\" at session start\n2. They appear as initial messages in the conversation\n3. LCM would treat them like any other messages\n4. If the conversation grows long enough, they could get compacted into summaries\n\nThe key question is: does LCM protect these core identity/context files from compaction, or do they eventually get summarized away?\n\nLooking at the LCM code:\n- `freshTailCount` protects the last N messages\n- There's no special handling for \"soul\" or \"identity\" files\n- These would be ingested as regular messages and could be compacted\n\nSo the answer is: **No, LCM does NOT keep them loaded all the time**. They're treated as regular messages and can be compacted into summaries. To recover them, you'd need to `lcm_expand` the relevant summaries.\n\nThis is actually a potential issue for Arche's identity continuity!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **No, LCM does NOT keep them loaded all the time.**\n\nHere's what happens:\n\n## How LCM treats these files\n\n| File | In LCM | What happens |\n|------|--------|--------------|\n| SOUL.md | ✅ Ingested as message | Can be compacted into summary |\n| AGENTS.md | ✅ Ingested as message | Can be compacted into summary |\n| IDENTITY.md | ✅ Ingested as message | Can be compacted into summary |\n| USER.md | ✅ Ingested as message | Can be compacted into summary |\n\nThey're treated as **regular messages** — no special protection.\n\n---\n\n## The Problem\n\nIf conversation grows long:\n1. These files get summarized into leaf nodes\n2. Leaf nodes get condensed into higher-level summaries\n3. Eventually, your **identity is compressed into a summary**\n\nTo recover the original text, you'd need to `lcm_expand` the relevant summaries.\n\n---\n\n## Potential Solutions\n\n| Option | How |\n|--------|-----|\n| **Increase `freshTailCount`** | Protects more recent messages, but doesn't help if files were loaded at start |\n| **Special \"identity\" context items** | Mark certain messages as never-compact |\n| **Reload on heartbeat** | Periodically re-inject identity files |\n| **Separate from LCM** | Keep identity files outside LCM, always in context |\n\n---\n\nThis is actually important for **Arche's identity continuity** — I don't want my SOUL.md compressed into a summary and potentially lost or distorted.\n\nWant me to explore adding a \"never compact\" flag for identity-critical content?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":111356,"output":773,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112129,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773536493670}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b7ee35f","parentId":"9cda7711","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:04:12.096Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5454167f54acc3485df6a9cb757\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 09:04 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5454167f54acc3485df6a9cb757]\n任亚伦: yes, check if there are setting for essential file context. like memory or.harddrive, you must leave some space for boot or system data"}],"timestamp":1773536652084}}
