{"type":"message","id":"3432954d","parentId":"18252dda","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:05:29.945Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1f8f865484fa4e7487079fd1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type { DatabaseSync } from \"node:sqlite\";\nimport { sanitizeFts5Query } from \"./fts5-sanitize.js\";\nimport { buildLikeSearchPlan, createFallbackSnippet } from \"./full-text-fallback.js\";\n\nexport type SummaryKind = \"leaf\" | \"condensed\";\nexport type ContextItemType = \"message\" | \"summary\";\n\nexport type CreateSummaryInput = {\n  summaryId: string;\n  conversationId: number;\n  kind: SummaryKind;\n  depth?: number;\n  content: string;\n  tokenCount: number;\n  fileIds?: string[];\n  earliestAt?: Date;\n  latestAt?: Date;\n  descendantCount?: number;\n  descendantTokenCount?: number;\n  sourceMessageTokenCount?: number;\n};\n\nexport type SummaryRecord = {\n  summaryId: string;\n  conversationId: number;\n  kind: SummaryKind;\n  depth: number;\n  content: string;\n  tokenCount: number;\n  fileIds: string[];\n  earliestAt: Date | null;\n  latestAt: Date | null;\n  descendantCount: number;\n  descendantTokenCount: number;\n  sourceMessageTokenCount: number;\n  createdAt: Date;\n};\n\nexport type SummarySubtreeNodeRecord = SummaryRecord & {\n  depthFromRoot: number;\n  parentSummaryId: string | null;\n  path: string;\n  childCount: number;\n};\n\nexport type ContextItemRecord = {\n  conversationId: number;\n  ordinal: number;\n  itemType: ContextItemType;\n  messageId: number | null;\n  summaryId: string | null;\n  createdAt: Date;\n};\n\nexport type SummarySearchInput = {\n  conversationId?: number;\n  query: string;\n  mode: \"regex\" | \"full_text\";\n  since?: Date;\n  before?: Date;\n  limit?: number;\n};\n\nexport type SummarySearchResult = {\n  summaryId: string;\n  conversationId: number;\n  kind: SummaryKind;\n  snippet: string;\n  createdAt: Date;\n  rank?: number;\n};\n\nexport type CreateLargeFileInput = {\n  fileId: string;\n  conversationId: number;\n  fileName?: string;\n  mimeType?: string;\n  byteSize?: number;\n  storageUri: string;\n  explorationSummary?: string;\n};\n\nexport type LargeFileRecord = {\n  fileId: string;\n  conversationId: number;\n  fileName: string | null;\n  mimeType: string | null;\n  byteSize: number | null;\n  storageUri: string;\n  explorationSummary: string | null;\n  createdAt: Date;\n};\n\n// ── DB row shapes (snake_case) ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ninterface SummaryRow {\n  summary_id: string;\n  conversation_id: number;\n  kind: SummaryKind;\n  depth: number;\n\n[819 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773536729931}}
{"type":"message","id":"efd0847e","parentId":"3432954d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:05:53.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the schema:\n\n`ContextItemRecord` has:\n- conversationId\n- ordinal\n- itemType\n- messageId\n- summaryId\n- createdAt\n\nNo `pinned`, `essential`, `priority`, or `weight` field. The only protection mechanism is `freshTailCount` which protects the most recent N messages based on ordinal position.\n\nThis is indeed a gap - there's no way to mark certain messages (like identity files) as \"essential\" that should never be compacted.\n\nLet me summarize this for Allan and propose a solution.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **No, LCM does NOT have an \"essential context\" setting.**\n\n## Current Protection\n\nOnly `freshTailCount` — protects the **most recent N messages** based on position, not content importance.\n\n```\n[Older messages] [freshTailCount protected]\n     ↑                    ↑\n  Can be compacted    Never compacted\n```\n\n**Problem:** Identity files (SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, etc.) are loaded at the **start** of conversation — they're in the oldest messages, not the fresh tail.\n\n---\n\n## Gap Analysis\n\n| Feature | LCM has it? |\n|---------|-------------|\n| Protect by position (fresh tail) | ✅ Yes |\n| Protect by content type | ❌ No |\n| Protect by \"pinned\" flag | ❌ No |\n| Reserve tokens for essential context | ❌ No |\n| \"Boot partition\" concept | ❌ No |\n\n---\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option 1: Add `pinned` field to context_items\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE context_items ADD COLUMN pinned INTEGER DEFAULT 0;\n```\n\n- Mark identity files as `pinned: 1`\n- Compaction skips pinned items\n- Simple, minimal change\n\n### Option 2: Add `essentialTokens` setting\n\n```json\n{\n  \"LCM_ESSENTIAL_TOKENS\": 5000\n}\n```\n\n- Reserve N tokens for essential context\n- Assembler always includes essential items first\n- Like reserving space for boot partition\n\n### Option 3: Essential context injection\n\n- Keep essential files **outside LCM**\n- Inject them at assembly time\n- Never ingest into LCM database\n\n---\n\n**Recommendation:** Option 1 (`pinned` field) + Option 2 (`essentialTokens`) together:\n\n1. Mark identity files as pinned\n2. Reserve token budget for pinned items\n3. Compaction never touches pinned items\n4. Assembler always includes pinned items first\n\nWant me to draft a PR for this feature?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":110949,"output":579,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111528,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773536729943}}
