{"type":"message","id":"a663b87b","parentId":"3695d96c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:15:25.386Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to record the conversation events from the last 15 minutes to the daily notes. I should update the daily file with what we discussed about LCM and the missing \"essential context\" feature.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e7a5a6f7ac7448e6b5c41802","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md","newText":"## 8:45 - 9:00 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Explained LCM ContextEngine implementation (all 9 methods)\n- Key methods: bootstrap (import/reconcile), ingest, afterTurn, assemble, compact\n- Subagent methods: prepareSubagentSpawn (grant expansion access), onSubagentEnded (revoke)\n- LCM owns compaction lifecycle (`ownsCompaction: true`)\n\n## 9:00 - 9:15 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Discovered LCM does NOT protect identity files (SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, etc.)\n- Only `freshTailCount` protects recent messages by position, not content importance\n- Identity files loaded at start → oldest messages → can be compacted away\n- **Gap:** No `pinned` field, no `essentialTokens` setting, no \"boot partition\" concept\n- Proposed solutions: add `pinned` column + `essentialTokens` reserve budget","oldText":"## 8:45 - 9:00 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Explained LCM ContextEngine implementation (all 9 methods)\n- Key methods: bootstrap (import/reconcile), ingest, afterTurn, assemble, compact\n- Subagent methods: prepareSubagentSpawn (grant expansion access), onSubagentEnded (revoke)\n- LCM owns compaction lifecycle (`ownsCompaction: true`)"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":111713,"output":386,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112099,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773537307144}}
