{"type":"message","id":"890153df","parentId":"3906242e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:19:29.950Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is right. \"Pinned context\" is fragile because:\n1. You'd have to know which messages to pin at ingest time\n2. If you miss something, it gets compacted away\n3. Hard to maintain as context changes\n\nHis idea is better: a \"zone\" that loads essential files every time, independent of LCM. Like a boot partition that's always loaded.\n\nThis would be:\n- A config setting for which files to always load\n- Files loaded fresh each turn, not through LCM\n- Never ingested into LCM database\n- Always present in context, guaranteed\n\nLet me think about implementation:\n- Could be in OpenClaw core (not LCM plugin)\n- Config like `context.essentialFiles` or `agent.bootstrapFiles`\n- Loaded before assembly, added to every context\n- Reserves token budget for these files\n\nThis is cleaner than trying to \"pin\" messages in LCM.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] You're right — pinned context is fragile. The \"zone\" approach is cleaner:\n\n## The Problem with Pinned\n\n- Need to know at ingest time what to pin\n- If you miss something, it's gone\n- Hard to maintain as context evolves\n- Tied to message IDs, not file sources\n\n---\n\n## Better: Essential Zone (Boot Partition)\n\n**Concept:** A zone that's **always loaded fresh**, never goes through LCM.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│           Model Context             │\n├─────────────┬───────────────────────┤\n│  Essential  │      LCM Context      │\n│    Zone     │  (summaries + tail)   │\n│  (always)   │     (can compact)     │\n├─────────────┼───────────────────────┤\n│ SOUL.md     │    Summaries          │\n│ AGENTS.md   │    Fresh tail         │\n│ IDENTITY.md │    Recent messages    │\n│ USER.md     │                       │\n└─────────────┴───────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n**Config (OpenClaw core, not LCM):**\n```json\n{\n  \"context\": {\n    \"essentialFiles\": [\n      \"SOUL.md\",\n      \"AGENTS.md\", \n      \"IDENTITY.md\",\n      \"USER.md\"\n    ],\n    \"essentialTokensReserve\": 5000\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. Before every assembly, load essential files from disk\n2. Reserve token budget for essential zone\n3. LCM fills remaining budget with summaries + tail\n4. Essential files **never ingested into LCM**\n\n---\n\n## Benefits\n\n| Aspect | Why it's better |\n|--------|-----------------|\n| **Fresh** | Always loads current file content |\n| **Simple** | No pinning logic in LCM |\n| **Decoupled** | Identity independent of conversation history |\n| **Maintainable** | Just update files on disk |\n\n---\n\nThis is like how an OS always loads the boot partition — it doesn't rely on cache or history.\n\nWant me to draft this as an OpenClaw feature request (separate from LCM)?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":111809,"output":773,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112582,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773537541201}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed43de9e","parentId":"890153df","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:21:48.202Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5454d47e14b0c38591efe067e7b\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 09:21 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5454d47e14b0c38591efe067e7b]\n任亚伦: yes. but check the methods, don't load duplicate. does openclaw load them every new session?"}],"timestamp":1773537708189}}
{"type":"message","id":"d3e37f25","parentId":"ed43de9e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:22:00.487Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking me to check how OpenClaw currently loads these files. The question is:\n1. Does OpenClaw load SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, etc. every session?\n2. Could there be duplicates if we add an \"essential zone\" that loads them again?\n\nLet me check how OpenClaw handles these files.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_13ea1cb800114103838951d2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"SOUL\\|AGENTS\\|IDENTITY\\|USER\\.md\\|essentialFiles\\|contextFiles\\|loadFiles\" /home/ubuntu/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v node_modules | head -30","workdir":"/home/ubuntu"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":112535,"output":186,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112721,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773537708195}}
