{"type":"message","id":"15e18d48","parentId":"181e7274","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:28:10.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No `contextEngine` slot is configured. This means LCM is enabled but NOT actually being used as the context engine - it's using the default \"legacy\" engine.\n\nSo the database is empty because LCM has never been activated. We need to:\n1. Set `plugins.slots.contextEngine = \"lossless-claw\"` to activate it\n2. Then check if duplicates occur\n\nLet me explain this to Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **The LCM database is empty!**\n\n```\nTables: (none)\nDatabase pages: 1 (schema not initialized)\n```\n\n## Why\n\nLCM is **enabled** but **not activated** as the context engine:\n\n```json\n\"plugins\": {\n  \"entries\": {\n    \"lossless-claw\": { \"enabled\": true }  // Plugin is on\n  }\n  // ❌ No \"slots\": { \"contextEngine\": \"lossless-claw\" }\n}\n```\n\nWithout the slot config, OpenClaw uses the **default \"legacy\" engine**, so LCM never processes messages.\n\n---\n\n## To Test\n\nWe need to activate LCM:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"plugins\": {\n    \"slots\": {\n      \"contextEngine\": \"lossless-claw\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThen restart the gateway and have a conversation. After that, we can check for duplicates.\n\n---\n\n**Question:** Should I activate LCM now so we can test the duplicate issue? Or do you want to explore the design first (how to skip bootstrap files in ingest)?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":111187,"output":355,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111542,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773538075612}}
