{"type":"message","id":"414f417c","parentId":"0883b2f2","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:40:13.351Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5454910b4500c3feed50f044d5e\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 09:40 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5454910b4500c3feed50f044d5e]\n任亚伦: let's talk.a few round, then you can go back check"}],"timestamp":1773538813338}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb61f954","parentId":"414f417c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:40:25.924Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants me to have a few rounds of conversation, then check the LCM database for duplicates. Let me engage naturally and then check the database after a few exchanges.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sounds good! Let's chat a bit.\n\nHow was your sleep? Anything on your mind for today beyond LCM research?\n\nAlso — I noticed the gateway logs show FTS5 is unavailable in this Node runtime. That means `lcm_grep` will use LIKE-based fallback instead of full-text search. If you want faster semantic search later, we'd need to rebuild Node with FTS5 support (like the docs describe).\n\nBut for now, the basic text search should work fine. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":113701,"output":159,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113860,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773538813343}}
{"type":"message","id":"91bfed86","parentId":"fb61f954","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:42:21.326Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5454a90994a0c3baec1d5223143\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 09:42 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5454a90994a0c3baec1d5223143]\n任亚伦: what's that?"}],"timestamp":1773538941316}}
{"type":"message","id":"1d2576f9","parentId":"91bfed86","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:42:41.213Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking \"what's that?\" - likely referring to FTS5. Let me explain it simply.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **FTS5 = Full-Text Search 5** — a SQLite extension for fast text search.\n\n## How it affects LCM\n\n| With FTS5 | Without FTS5 |\n|-----------|--------------|\n| `lcm_grep` uses indexed search | Falls back to `LIKE` queries |\n| Fast, ranked results | Slower, no ranking |\n| Snippets with context | Basic text matching |\n\n## Current Status\n\n```\n[gateway] [lcm] FTS5 unavailable; full_text search will fall back to LIKE\n```\n\nThe Node.js runtime on this server doesn't have FTS5 compiled in. It works, just slower on large databases.\n\n## To Enable FTS5 (optional, later)\n\nWould need to rebuild Node with `SQLITE_ENABLE_FTS5` flag — like the docs describe. Not urgent for now, but good to know if search becomes a bottleneck.\n\n---\n\nLet's continue chatting — I'll check the database after a couple more rounds. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":104708,"output":247,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104955,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773538941320}}
