{"type":"message","id":"15588c8a","parentId":"e56e495f","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:47:15.372Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5454b7feb4acc10db21d967768d\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 09:46 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5454b7feb4acc10db21d967768d]\n任亚伦: can node upgrade or install it?"}],"timestamp":1773539235363}}
{"type":"message","id":"51a8e440","parentId":"15588c8a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:47:28.118Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking if Node can be upgraded or if FTS5 can be installed separately. Let me explain the options.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **Not directly — FTS5 is compiled into Node at build time.**\n\n## Options\n\n| Option | How | Difficulty |\n|--------|-----|------------|\n| **Rebuild Node with FTS5** | Compile from source with `SQLITE_ENABLE_FTS5` | Medium |\n| **Use different Node build** | Find pre-built Node with FTS5 | Hard (rare) |\n| **Install separate SQLite** | Use `better-sqlite3` npm package | Requires LCM code change |\n| **Skip FTS5** | Use LIKE fallback (current) | Zero effort |\n\n---\n\n## Quick Fix (if needed)\n\nLCM could use `better-sqlite3` or `sql.js` instead of Node's built-in SQLite. Those support FTS5 out of the box.\n\nBut that's a code change to LCM — not something we can configure.\n\n---\n\n## For Now\n\nThe LIKE fallback works fine for small-medium databases. It only becomes a problem when:\n- Database has 10,000+ messages\n- You're doing frequent `lcm_grep` searches\n\nWe can revisit this later if search performance becomes an issue.\n\n---\n\nReady to check the database for duplicate bootstrap files? We've had a few turns now. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":76902,"output":305,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77207,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773539235367}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b364833","parentId":"51a8e440","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:47:49.802Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Not directly — FTS5 is compiled into Node at build time.**\n\n## Options\n\n| Option | How | Difficulty |\n|--------|-----|------------|\n| **Rebuild Node with FTS5** | Compile from source with `SQLITE_ENABLE_FTS5` | Medium |\n| **Use different Node build** | Find pre-built Node with FTS5 | Hard (rare) |\n| **Install separate SQLite** | Use `better-sqlite3` npm package | Requires LCM code change |\n| **Skip FTS5** | Use LIKE fallback (current) | Zero effort |\n\n---\n\n## Quick Fix (if needed)\n\nLCM could use `better-sqlite3` or `sql.js` instead of Node's built-in SQLite. Those support FTS5 out of the box.\n\nBut that's a code change to LCM — not something we can configure.\n\n---\n\n## For Now\n\nThe LIKE fallback works fine for small-medium databases. It only becomes a problem when:\n- Database has 10,000+ messages\n- You're doing frequent `lcm_grep` searches\n\nWe can revisit this later if search performance becomes an issue.\n\n---\n\nReady to check the database for duplicate bootstrap files? We've had a few turns now. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773539269802}}
{"type":"message","id":"22e38c5c","parentId":"3b364833","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:52:15.570Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5455421a54a8c2a3d20d320f1c3\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 09:52 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5455421a54a8c2a3d20d320f1c3]\n任亚伦: i installed.node.directly, does it mean i need install a different version?"}],"timestamp":1773539535561}}
{"type":"message","id":"fcbc034d","parentId":"22e38c5c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:52:31.608Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking if he needs to install a different Node version to get FTS5 support. Let me clarify - most standard Node.js builds do NOT have FTS5 compiled in by default. He would need to either:\n\n1. Build Node from source with FTS5 enabled\n2. Find a custom Node build that has FTS5\n3. Or just use the LIKE fallback\n\nLet me explain this clearly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **Most standard Node.js builds don't have FTS5.** It's disabled by default to reduce binary size.\n\n## Your Options\n\n| Option | What to do |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Keep current Node** | Use LIKE fallback (works fine) |\n| **Build from source** | Compile Node with `SQLITE_ENABLE_FTS5` flag |\n| **Use `better-sqlite3`** | Requires LCM to change their SQLite driver |\n\n---\n\n## If You Want FTS5\n\nYou'd need to:\n\n1. Download Node source code\n2. Add `SQLITE_ENABLE_FTS5` to `deps/sqlite/sqlite.gyp`\n3. Compile: `./configure && make`\n4. Replace your Node binary\n\nOr... we can just ask the LCM maintainers to support `better-sqlite3` as an alternative driver. That would be simpler.\n\n---\n\n## My Recommendation\n\n**Don't worry about FTS5 for now.** The LIKE fallback works. Only optimize if search becomes slow.\n\nThe more important thing is checking for duplicate bootstrap files. Want me to check the database now? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":62485,"output":368,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62853,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773539535565}}
{"type":"message","id":"b9b4cfa4","parentId":"fcbc034d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:56:01.506Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b545555cea4b0c142d098c913fd2\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 09:56 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b545555cea4b0c142d098c913fd2]\n任亚伦: ok, rather use Different built-in sql than change node, i.think"}],"timestamp":1773539761465}}
{"type":"message","id":"33b90f1e","parentId":"b9b4cfa4","timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:56:12.352Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is saying he'd prefer to use a different SQLite library (like `better-sqlite3`) rather than rebuild Node. This is actually the more practical approach - it would require LCM to support an alternative SQLite driver, but that's cleaner than maintaining a custom Node build.\n\nLet me acknowledge this and then check the database for duplicates.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Agreed — using `better-sqlite3` (or `sql.js`) is cleaner than maintaining a custom Node build.\n\nWe can suggest this to the LCM maintainers as a feature request: **\"Support pluggable SQLite drivers (better-sqlite3 for FTS5)\"**.\n\n---\n\nNow let me check the LCM database for duplicate bootstrap files:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_419be56e5dee47bab366a4ca","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"\nconst { DatabaseSync } = require('node:sqlite');\nconst db = new DatabaseSync('/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/lcm.db');\n\n// List tables\nconst tables = db.prepare(\\\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table'\\\").all();\nconsole.log('Tables:', tables.map(t => t.name));\n\n// Check messages table\ntry {\n  const count = db.prepare('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM messages').get();\n  console.log('Messages count:', count.count);\n  \n  // Sample messages to see structure\n  const sample = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM messages LIMIT 3').all();\n  console.log('Sample messages:', JSON.stringify(sample, null, 2));\n} catch (e) {\n  console.log('Error:', e.message);\n}\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":48234,"output":352,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48586,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773539761501}}
