{"type":"message","id":"c0e12c2d","parentId":"4b490dc5","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:07:41.354Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3c3d6ab2d1c84f929e44c14b","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1128:  private async ingestSingle(params: {\n1188:  async ingest(params: {\n1197:  async ingestBatch(params: {"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"1128:  private async ingestSingle(params: {\n1188:  async ingest(params: {\n1197:  async ingestBatch(params: {","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773540461347}}
{"type":"message","id":"e9351cb9","parentId":"c0e12c2d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:07:56.260Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the ingest method to understand how it processes messages.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a9d265f5ee1f4a85bb28e2eb","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/extensions/lossless-claw/src/engine.ts","limit":100,"offset":1128}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":63909,"output":58,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63967,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773540461352}}
{"type":"message","id":"6afcd75a","parentId":"e9351cb9","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:07:56.286Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a9d265f5ee1f4a85bb28e2eb","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  private async ingestSingle(params: {\n    sessionId: string;\n    message: AgentMessage;\n    isHeartbeat?: boolean;\n  }): Promise<IngestResult> {\n    const { sessionId, message, isHeartbeat } = params;\n    if (isHeartbeat) {\n      return { ingested: false };\n    }\n    const stored = toStoredMessage(message);\n\n    // Get or create conversation for this session\n    const conversation = await this.conversationStore.getOrCreateConversation(sessionId);\n    const conversationId = conversation.conversationId;\n\n    let messageForParts = message;\n    if (stored.role === \"user\") {\n      const intercepted = await this.interceptLargeFiles({\n        conversationId,\n        content: stored.content,\n      });\n      if (intercepted) {\n        stored.content = intercepted.rewrittenContent;\n        stored.tokenCount = estimateTokens(stored.content);\n        if (\"content\" in message) {\n          messageForParts = {\n            ...message,\n            content: stored.content,\n          } as AgentMessage;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Determine next sequence number\n    const maxSeq = await this.conversationStore.getMaxSeq(conversationId);\n    const seq = maxSeq + 1;\n\n    // Persist the message\n    const msgRecord = await this.conversationStore.createMessage({\n      conversationId,\n      seq,\n      role: stored.role,\n      content: stored.content,\n      tokenCount: stored.tokenCount,\n    });\n    await this.conversationStore.createMessageParts(\n      msgRecord.messageId,\n      buildMessageParts({\n        sessionId,\n        message: messageForParts,\n        fallbackContent: stored.content,\n      }),\n    );\n\n    // Append to context items so assembler can see it\n    await this.summaryStore.appendContextMessage(conversationId, msgRecord.messageId);\n\n    return { ingested: true };\n  }\n\n  async ingest(params: {\n    sessionId: string;\n    message: AgentMessage;\n    isHeartbeat?: boolean;\n  }): Promise<IngestResult> {\n    this.ensureMigrated();\n    return this.withSessionQueue(params.sessionId, () => this.ingestSingle(params));\n  }\n\n  async ingestBatch(params: {\n    sessionId: string;\n    messages: AgentMessage[];\n    isHeartbeat?: boolean;\n  }): Promise<IngestBatchResult> {\n    this.ensureMigrated();\n    if (params.messages.length === 0) {\n      return { ingestedCount: 0 };\n    }\n    return this.withSessionQueue(params.sessionId, async () => {\n      let ingestedCount = 0;\n      for (const message of params.messages) {\n        const result = await this.ingestSingle({\n          sessionId: params.sessionId,\n          message,\n          isHeartbeat: params.isHeartbeat,\n        });\n        if (result.ingested) {\n          ingestedCount += 1;\n        }\n      }\n      return { ingestedCount };\n    });\n  }\n\n  async afterTurn(params: {\n    sessionId: string;\n    sessionFile: string;\n    messages: AgentMessage[];\n    prePromptMessageCount: number;\n    autoCompactionSummary?: string;\n\n[599 more lines in file. Use offset=1228 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773540476276}}
{"type":"message","id":"4e7b0a58","parentId":"6afcd75a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:08:22.853Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the data flow. Let me explain it to Allan clearly:\n\n1. **OpenClaw** injects bootstrap files as messages (with role=\"user\" or role=\"system\") into the context stream\n2. **LCM's `ingest()` method** receives these messages and stores them in the database\n3. LCM sees them as **messages with text content**, not as \"files\"\n4. LCM doesn't have any metadata to identify \"this message is actually a bootstrap file\"\n\nSo Allan's understanding is correct - LCM can't recognize them as files because OpenClaw doesn't pass any metadata indicating \"this is SOUL.md content\". It just looks like any other user/system message with text content.\n\nThe fix could be:\n1. OpenClaw adds metadata to bootstrap messages (e.g., `metadata: { bootstrapFile: \"SOUL.md\" }`)\n2. Or LCM detects by content pattern (e.g., message starts with \"# SOUL.md\")\n\nLet me explain this to Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **Exactly right!**\n\n## The Data Flow\n\n```\nOpenClaw                          LCM\n   │                               │\n   │  Inject SOUL.md as message    │\n   │  content = \"# SOUL.md...\"     │\n   │──────────────────────────────▶│\n   │                               │\n   │  No metadata saying           │\n   │  \"this is SOUL.md\"            │\n   │                               │\n   │                          LCM stores it\n   │                          as regular message\n   │                          with text content\n```\n\n---\n\n## The Problem\n\n**LCM sees this:**\n```json\n{\n  \"role\": \"user\",\n  \"content\": \"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\\n\\n_You're not a chatbot...\"\n}\n```\n\n**LCM does NOT see:**\n```json\n{\n  \"role\": \"user\",\n  \"content\": \"# SOUL.md - Who You Are...\",\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"bootstrapFile\": \"SOUL.md\"  // ← This doesn't exist!\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Two Fix Options\n\n| Option | Where | How |\n|--------|-------|-----|\n| **A: Content detection** | LCM | Check if content starts with `# SOUL.md`, etc. |\n| **B: Metadata flag** | OpenClaw + LCM | OpenClaw adds `bootstrapFile: \"SOUL.md\"`, LCM checks for it |\n\n---\n\n## My Recommendation\n\n**Option A** (content detection) — simpler:\n- Only changes LCM\n- No coordination needed with OpenClaw\n- Works immediately\n\n**Option B** (metadata flag) — cleaner long-term:\n- More explicit\n- Works for custom bootstrap files too\n- Requires OpenClaw PR as well\n\n---\n\nWhich approach do you prefer? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":64622,"output":687,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65309,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773540476285}}
{"type":"message","id":"cf585e11","parentId":"4e7b0a58","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:10:48.134Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54551cbf4ca4c4936bed4a15bb0\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 10:10 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54551cbf4ca4c4936bed4a15bb0]\n任亚伦: maybe add start and end tag in file, and let lcm detect, if they see the opening.and ending, then.ignore compact"}],"timestamp":1773540648127}}
{"type":"message","id":"3cf80784","parentId":"cf585e11","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:11:03.538Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is suggesting an alternative approach:\n\n1. Add start and end tags to bootstrap files (like `<bootstrap-file name=\"SOUL.md\">...</bootstrap-file>`)\n2. LCM detects these tags and skips content between them during compaction\n\nThis is actually a clever idea because:\n- It's explicit and clear\n- LCM can detect it by content parsing\n- Works for any file that's tagged\n- No need to change OpenClaw core\n\nBut there are some considerations:\n1. The bootstrap files are markdown files - adding XML-like tags might interfere with the content\n2. The tags would need to be in the content itself, which means the files would look different\n3. Or OpenClaw wraps the content when injecting\n\nActually, Allan might be thinking that OpenClaw could wrap the bootstrap file content with tags when injecting into the context. That would be cleaner.\n\nLet me ask for clarification on whether:\n1. The tags go in the source files (SOUL.md itself)\n2. Or OpenClaw wraps them when injecting\n\nOption 2 is cleaner because it doesn't pollute the source files.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **Smart idea!** Two ways to implement:\n\n---\n\n## Option 1: Tags in Source Files\n\n```markdown\n<!-- bootstrap-start: SOUL.md -->\n# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n...\n<!-- bootstrap-end: SOUL.md -->\n```\n\n**Pros:** Self-contained\n**Cons:** Pollutes source files with non-content markers\n\n---\n\n## Option 2: OpenClaw Wraps on Inject (Better)\n\nOpenClaw wraps bootstrap content when injecting into context:\n\n```\n<bootstrap-file name=\"SOUL.md\">\n# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n...\n</bootstrap-file>\n```\n\n**Pros:**\n- Source files stay clean (no tags in SOUL.md itself)\n- LCM can easily detect and skip\n- Works for any file OpenClaw marks as bootstrap\n\n**Cons:**\n- Requires OpenClaw core change\n- Slightly more tokens in context (the tags)\n\n---\n\n## LCM Detection Logic\n\n```typescript\n// In ingest()\nconst BOOTSTRAP_START = /<bootstrap-file name=\"(.+?)\">/;\nconst BOOTSTRAP_END = /<\\/bootstrap-file>/;\n\n// If content has both start and end tags, skip it\nif (BOOTSTRAP_START.test(content) && BOOTSTRAP_END.test(content)) {\n  return { ingested: false };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\nWhich approach do you prefer? Or should OpenClaw add the tags? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":49171,"output":667,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49838,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773540648130}}
{"type":"message","id":"49dc7031","parentId":"3cf80784","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:14:31.550Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54552ea52ca8c29d5f1385684e3\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 10:14 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54552ea52ca8c29d5f1385684e3]\n任亚伦: ok, what the tag format should be look alike? is it called bootstrap? it's md file format,  right?"}],"timestamp":1773540871543}}
{"type":"message","id":"d9728f1c","parentId":"49dc7031","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:14:57.073Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking about the tag format. He's right to question:\n1. Should it be called \"bootstrap\"? \n2. It's a markdown file - what's the best way to tag it?\n\nFor markdown files, we have a few options:\n1. HTML comments: `<!-- bootstrap-start: SOUL.md -->` - invisible when rendered\n2. Custom markers: `<!-- @lcm:skip -->` - more generic\n3. YAML frontmatter: `---\\nlcm: skip\\n---` at the top of files\n4. XML-style tags (visible in raw markdown but could be confusing)\n\nHTML comments are probably the cleanest because:\n- They're valid in markdown\n- They don't render when the markdown is displayed\n- They're clear and explicit\n- They can be parsed easily\n\nLet me propose a clean format that works well with markdown.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good question! Since these are markdown files, the tag format should be markdown-friendly. HTML comments are perfect because they're:\n- Valid in markdown\n- Invisible when rendered\n- Easy to parse\n\nLet me propose a few options:\n\n---\n\n## Option A: HTML Comments (Recommended)\n\n```markdown\n<!-- @lcm:skip start: SOUL.md -->\n# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n...\n<!-- @lcm:skip end: SOUL.md -->\n```\n\n**Pros:**\n- Invisible in rendered markdown\n- Clear intent with `@lcm:skip`\n- Includes filename for debugging\n\n---\n\n## Option B: Simpler HTML Comment\n\n```markdown\n<!-- lcm-skip -->\n# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n...\n<!-- /lcm-skip -->\n```\n\n**Pros:**\n- Shorter\n- Easy to remember\n\n---\n\n## Option C: YAML Frontmatter (for the file itself)\n\n```markdown\n---\nlcm_skip: true\nfile: SOUL.md\n---\n\n# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n...\n```\n\n**Pros:**\n- Standard markdown pattern\n- Only at top, no end tag needed\n- Can include metadata\n\n---\n\n## My Recommendation\n\n**Option A or B** - HTML comments at start/end of bootstrap section.\n\nFor the bootstrap files, I'd suggest:\n\n```markdown\n<!-- lcm-skip -->\n# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n<!-- /lcm-skip -->\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n...\n```\n\nWait - should the **entire file** be skipped, or just the header? \n\nCurrently OpenClaw injects the **entire file**. If the whole file should be skipped, we only need one tag at the top:\n\n```markdown\n<!-- lcm-skip: SOUL.md -->\n# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n...entire content...\n```\n\nWhat do you think? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":49968,"output":678,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50646,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773540871547}}
