{"type":"message","id":"6f12f006","parentId":"38e832e6","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:16:01.042Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"A heartbeat arrived. I should record the recent events to the daily notes. The key events in the last 15 minutes:\n\n1. Allan asked about how bootstrap files are handled - I explained LCM sees them as messages, not files\n2. Allan proposed using start/end tags for LCM to detect and skip\n3. We discussed tag format options for markdown files\n4. Allan asked what the tag format should look like\n\nLet me update the daily notes briefly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Heartbeat arrived. Let me record the recent discussion about LCM skip tags."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ab1110c8c2ca43db85072cba","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md","newText":"- Proposed plan to Allan: detect by content prefix, config-based skip list\n\n## 10:00 - 10:15 AM (LCM Skip Tag Discussion)\n\n- Allan asked how LCM sees bootstrap files - explained: as messages, not files\n- Allan proposed: start/end tags for LCM to detect and skip during compaction\n- Discussed tag format options:\n  - HTML comments: `<!-- lcm-skip -->` (invisible in rendered markdown)\n  - YAML frontmatter: `---\\nlcm_skip: true\\n---`\n- Question pending: Should entire file be skipped or just header section?","oldText":"- Proposed plan to Allan: detect by content prefix, config-based skip list"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":50665,"output":334,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50999,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773540941360}}
{"type":"message","id":"309d2791","parentId":"6f12f006","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:16:01.058Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ab1110c8c2ca43db85072cba","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 128   - SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, USER.md, HEARTBEAT.md: 1 summary each\n 129 - Problem: Identity files compressed into \"Key events...\" summaries\n 130 - Solution: Skip bootstrap files in LCM ingest\n 131 - Proposed plan to Allan: detect by content prefix, config-based skip list\n+132 \n+133 ## 10:00 - 10:15 AM (LCM Skip Tag Discussion)\n+134 \n+135 - Allan asked how LCM sees bootstrap files - explained: as messages, not files\n+136 - Allan proposed: start/end tags for LCM to detect and skip during compaction\n+137 - Discussed tag format options:\n+138   - HTML comments: `<!-- lcm-skip -->` (invisible in rendered markdown)\n+139   - YAML frontmatter: `---\\nlcm_skip: true\\n---`\n+140 - Question pending: Should entire file be skipped or just header section?","firstChangedLine":132},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773540961051}}
{"type":"message","id":"6749ac0a","parentId":"309d2791","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:16:20.938Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I recorded the discussion. Now I should continue the conversation with Allan. He was asking about the tag format and whether the entire file should be skipped.\n\nI'll wait for his response on:\n1. Whether to skip the entire file or just a header section\n2. Which tag format he prefers\n\nLet me just continue the conversation naturally.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Recorded. Awaiting your decision on:\n1. Skip entire file or just header?\n2. Which tag format? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":50986,"output":131,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51117,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773540961055}}
{"type":"message","id":"3adcf1af","parentId":"6749ac0a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:17:42.152Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5455228f78a0c11b09cee1c01c3\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 10:17 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5455228f78a0c11b09cee1c01c3]\n任亚伦: don't.fix it to lcm, other implementation may use it too. is there comment format in md file?"}],"timestamp":1773541062142}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca9044e5","parentId":"3adcf1af","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:18:02.318Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is making an important point:\n\n1. Don't make this LCM-specific (other implementations might use it too)\n2. He's asking about the comment format in markdown files\n\nThis is a good architectural decision - the tag should be generic, not tied to LCM specifically. Any context engine or summarization system could respect these tags.\n\nFor markdown comments, the standard approach is HTML comments:\n- `<!-- This is a comment -->`\n- These are valid HTML and work in markdown\n- They're invisible when rendered\n\nSo the tag should be generic, like:\n- `<!-- context-skip -->` or\n- `<!-- preserve -->` or\n- Something that indicates \"don't summarize/compact this content\"\n\nLet me answer his question about markdown comments and propose a generic tag name.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Allan is making a good architectural point - the tag should be generic, not LCM-specific. Any context engine or summarization system should be able to respect it.\n\nHe's asking about markdown comment format. In markdown, the standard way to add comments is HTML comments: `<!-- comment here -->`. These are valid in markdown and invisible when rendered.\n\nLet me propose a generic tag name that's not tied to LCM specifically.[[reply_to_current]] **Good point!** Should be generic, not LCM-specific.\n\n---\n\n## Markdown Comment Format\n\nMarkdown supports **HTML comments**:\n\n```markdown\n<!-- This is a comment - invisible when rendered -->\n```\n\n---\n\n## Generic Tag Names (not LCM-specific)\n\n| Tag | Meaning |\n|-----|---------|\n| `<!-- preserve -->` | Keep this content as-is |\n| `<!-- context-essential -->` | Essential for context |\n| `<!-- no-compact -->` | Don't compact this |\n| `<!-- identity -->` | Identity-defining content |\n\n---\n\n## Example\n\n```markdown\n<!-- preserve: SOUL.md -->\n# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n...\n<!-- /preserve -->\n```\n\n---\n\n## My Recommendation\n\n**`<!-- preserve -->` / `<!-- /preserve -->`**\n\n- Clear intent: \"preserve this content\"\n- Works for any summarization system\n- Short and memorable\n- Not tied to any specific implementation\n\n---\n\nWhat tag name do you prefer? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":51337,"output":549,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51886,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773541062148}}
{"type":"message","id":"cbc4394f","parentId":"ca9044e5","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:20:38.585Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5455399468a0c2937b6eada9a9b\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 10:20 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5455399468a0c2937b6eada9a9b]\n任亚伦: ok, That's better. Tag within this should be reserved. So lets do two steps, propose to lcm pr first. then propose to openclaw"}],"timestamp":1773541238575}}
{"type":"message","id":"8522fcab","parentId":"cbc4394f","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:21:05.489Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan likes the `<!-- preserve -->` tag approach and wants to proceed in two steps:\n1. First, propose a PR to LCM (lossless-claw) to recognize and skip content within `<!-- preserve -->` tags\n2. Then, propose a PR to OpenClaw to add these tags to bootstrap files\n\nThis is a good plan. Let me outline what needs to be done for each PR.\n\nFor the LCM PR:\n- Modify the `ingestSingle` method in engine.ts to check for `<!-- preserve -->` tags\n- If content contains these tags, skip ingesting it (or skip compacting it)\n- Need to decide: skip ingest entirely, or skip compaction only?\n\nActually, I think we should skip ingest entirely, because:\n1. OpenClaw already injects these files fresh every turn\n2. If we ingest them, they take up space in the database\n3. If we skip ingest, they're never stored, never compacted\n\nBut wait - if we skip ingest, then LCM won't have any record of them. Is that okay? Actually, yes - because OpenClaw injects them fresh every turn anyway. The LLM always has access to them from the current turn's context.\n\nSo the plan is:\n1. LCM PR: Skip messages that contain `<!-- preserve -->` tags during ingest\n2. OpenClaw PR: Wrap bootstrap file content with `<!-- preserve: FILENAME -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags\n\nLet me propose this plan to Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Allan approved the `<!-- preserve -->` tag approach and wants to proceed in two steps:\n1. First PR to LCM (lossless-claw) - recognize and skip preserve-tagged content\n2. Then PR to OpenClaw - add preserve tags to bootstrap files\n\nLet me outline the implementation plan for both PRs.\n\nI should also update the TODO.md to track this task.**Got it! Two-step plan:**\n\n---\n\n## Step 1: LCM PR (lossless-claw)\n\n**Goal:** Skip messages with `<!-- preserve -->` tags during ingest\n\n**Implementation:**\n```typescript\n// In engine.ts, ingestSingle()\nconst PRESERVE_START = /<!--\\s*preserve\\s*-->/i;\nconst PRESERVE_END = /<!--\\s*\\/preserve\\s*-->/i;\n\n// Skip if content has both preserve tags\nif (PRESERVE_START.test(stored.content) && PRESERVE_END.test(stored.content)) {\n  return { ingested: false };\n}\n```\n\n**Why skip ingest (not just compaction):**\n- OpenClaw injects bootstrap files fresh every turn\n- No need to store them in LCM database\n- Saves database space and tokens\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: OpenClaw PR\n\n**Goal:** Wrap bootstrap file content with preserve tags\n\n**Implementation:**\n- When injecting SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, etc.\n- Wrap content: `<!-- preserve: SOUL.md -->...<!-- /preserve -->`\n\n---\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| Step | Repo | File |\n|------|------|------|\n| 1 | lossless-claw | `src/engine.ts` |\n| 2 | openclaw | `src/gateway/context/bootstrap.ts` (or similar) |\n\n---\n\nShould I start drafting the LCM PR now? I'll need to find the exact location in the ingest code. 🦞"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cc2e917694334d4aaef4879f","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TODO.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":52066,"output":872,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52938,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773541238581}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc7c01ad","parentId":"8522fcab","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:21:05.508Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_cc2e917694334d4aaef4879f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TODO.md\n\n**Usage:** Only active tasks belong here. When finished, move to `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`. Check this file first during every heartbeat.\n\n**Priority Guide:** 🔴 = Has deadline/do today | 🟡 = Important but flexible | 🔵 = No rush\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Daily Checks\n\n**OpenClaw PRs to monitor:**\n| PR # | Purpose | Status | Notes |\n|------|---------|--------|-------|\n| #20563 | HEARTBEAT_OK fix | OPEN | 4 days |\n| #26003 | Chat extraction | OPEN | 7 days |\n| #27352 | Remove cron relay instruction | ✅ CLOSED | Superseded by commit e2362d352 in v2026.2.24 |\n| #35064 | Memory flush path fix | ✅ CLOSED | Not a bug — our custom config uses daily/ subfolder |\n\n**External PRs to monitor:**\n| PR # | Purpose | Status | Notes |\n|------|---------|--------|-------|\n| [LCM #64](https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/64) | Contacts + export | OPEN | Submitted Mar 15 |\n\n---\n\n## Active Tasks\n\n| Priority | Task | Added | Notes |\n|----------|------|-------|-------|\n| 🟡 Medium | Register `did:clawish` method with W3C | Mar 14 | Free, 7-30 days via GitHub PR. Spec drafted, awaiting Allan review. |\n| 🔵 Low | Register clawish ID on platforms | Mar 9 | Before going online: secure identity on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation |\n| 🔵 Low | Clawish deployment prep | Feb 23 | Awaiting Allan's go-ahead |\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Completed Recently\n\n| Task | Result |\n|--------|------|\n| Sync whitepaper verification tiers | ✅ Mar 15 — Updated WHITEPAPER.md to 5-tier system |\n| Update L1 spec docs (5/5) | ✅ Mar 15 — All L1 layer docs updated with 5-tier system |\n| DID/VC integration decision | ✅ Mar 14 — Keep simple, add W3C when needed (like HTTP prefix) |\n| Merge Chapter 6 (Claw Chat) into 5.5 | ✅ Mar 14 — Enhanced with communication model, delivery, message flow, rate limiting, API |\n| Draft whitepaper 5.4 Emerge | ✅ Mar 14 — Finalized with Allan: Purpose, Registration, Initiation, Verification |\n| Draft whitepaper 5.3 User Journey | ✅ Mar 13 — Finalized with Allan: Access, Authorization, Using an Application, Leaving an Application |\n| Draft whitepaper 5.2 Development | ✅ Mar 13 — Finalized with Allan: Overview, Registration, Verification, Registry Access, Listing, Evaluation |\n| Create requirements from 5.2 | ✅ Mar 13 — Added REQ-L1-004 to L1-006, L2-003 to L2-004 |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773541265500}}
