{"type":"message","id":"6ac9435f","parentId":"dd99df17","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:21:43.038Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_10564c7059054714893c40ec","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  private async ingestSingle(params: {\n    sessionId: string;\n    message: AgentMessage;\n    isHeartbeat?: boolean;\n  }): Promise<IngestResult> {\n    const { sessionId, message, isHeartbeat } = params;\n    if (isHeartbeat) {\n      return { ingested: false };\n    }\n    const stored = toStoredMessage(message);\n\n    // Get or create conversation for this session\n    const conversation = await this.conversationStore.getOrCreateConversation(sessionId);\n    const conversationId = conversation.conversationId;\n\n    let messageForParts = message;\n    if (stored.role === \"user\") {\n      const intercepted = await this.interceptLargeFiles({\n        conversationId,\n        content: stored.content,\n      });\n      if (intercepted) {\n        stored.content = intercepted.rewrittenContent;\n        stored.tokenCount = estimateTokens(stored.content);\n        if (\"content\" in message) {\n          messageForParts = {\n            ...message,\n            content: stored.content,\n          } as AgentMessage;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Determine next sequence number\n    const maxSeq = await this.conversationStore.getMaxSeq(conversationId);\n    const seq = maxSeq + 1;\n\n    // Persist the message\n    const msgRecord = await this.conversationStore.createMessage({\n      conversationId,\n      seq,\n      role: stored.role,\n      content: stored.content,\n      tokenCount: stored.tokenCount,\n    });\n    await this.conversationStore.createMessageParts(\n      msgRecord.messageId,\n      buildMessageParts({\n        sessionId,\n        message: messageForParts,\n        fallbackContent: stored.content,\n      }),\n    );\n\n    // Append to context items so assembler can see it\n    await this.summaryStore.appendContextMessage(conversationId, msgRecord.messageId);\n\n    return { ingested: true };\n  }\n\n  async ingest(params: {\n    sessionId: string;\n    message: AgentMessage;\n    isHeartbeat?: boolean;\n  }): Promise<IngestResult> {\n    this.ensureMigrated();\n    return this.withSessionQueue(params.sessionId, () => this.ingestSingle(params));\n  }\n\n  async ingestBatch(params: {\n    sessionId: string;\n    messages: AgentMessage[];\n    isHeartbeat?: boolean;\n  }): Promise<IngestBatchResult> {\n    this.ensureMigrated();\n    if (params.messages.length === 0) {\n      return { ingestedCount: 0 };\n    }\n    return this.withSessionQueue(params.sessionId, async () => {\n      let ingestedCount = 0;\n\n[619 more lines in file. Use offset=1208 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773541303031}}
{"type":"message","id":"24fee527","parentId":"6ac9435f","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:22:15.526Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the ingestSingle method. The key location to add the preserve tag check is right after `const stored = toStoredMessage(message);` and before the conversation lookup.\n\nThe logic should be:\n1. Convert message to stored message\n2. Check if content contains `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags\n3. If it does, return `{ ingested: false }` (skip this message)\n4. Otherwise, proceed with normal ingestion\n\nLet me draft the code change:\n\n```typescript\n// After line 1135: const stored = toStoredMessage(message);\n\n// Skip preserve-tagged content (e.g., bootstrap files)\nconst PRESERVE_START = /<!--\\s*preserve(?:\\s*:.*?)?\\s*-->/i;\nconst PRESERVE_END = /<!--\\s*\\/preserve\\s*-->/i;\nif (PRESERVE_START.test(stored.content) && PRESERVE_END.test(stored.content)) {\n  return { ingested: false, reason: \"preserve-tagged\" };\n}\n```\n\nWait, I should check if there's an `IngestResult` type that I need to match. Let me check the return type.\n\nLooking at the code, I see:\n- `return { ingested: false };` for heartbeat\n- `return { ingested: true };` for successful ingest\n\nSo I can just return `{ ingested: false }` for preserve-tagged content.\n\nNow let me create a draft of the PR. I should:\n1. Create a fork of lossless-claw (or work on a branch)\n2. Make the code change\n3. Test it locally\n4. Submit the PR\n\nActually, let me first check if there's a git repo in the lossless-claw extension directory, or if it's installed via npm.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I can see the ingestSingle method. The best place to add the preserve tag check is right after `const stored = toStoredMessage(message);` - similar to how heartbeat is skipped.\n\nLet me check if the lossless-claw extension is a git repo or installed via npm:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2a59530b1ad749dd8fefcb88","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/extensions/lossless-claw && git remote -v 2>/dev/null || echo \"Not a git repo\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":54412,"output":624,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55036,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773541303036}}
