{"type":"message","id":"4288ea2d","parentId":"a557433d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:51:08.596Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4825a130419a4827bbc3eba6","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nThis PR adds peer tracking and conversation export functionality to LCM, enabling organized export of conversations by who you talked to.\\n\\n## Features\\n\\n### 1. Database Schema\\n\\n**New `contacts` table:**\\n```sql\\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n  peer_name TEXT,\\n  chat_type TEXT CHECK (chat_type IN ('dm', 'group'))\\n);\\n```\\n\\n**New columns in `conversations` table:**\\n```sql\\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN peer_id TEXT REFERENCES contacts(peer_id);\\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN channel TEXT;\\n```\\n\\n### 2. ContactStore\\n\\nNew store for managing contacts:\\n- `create()` — Create or update a contact\\n- `get()` — Get contact by peer_id\\n- `getAll()` — List all contacts\\n- `update()` — Update contact fields\\n- `delete()` — Delete a contact\\n\\n### 3. lcm_export Tool\\n\\nExport conversations to markdown files organized by peer and date.\\n\\n```bash\\nlcm_export --outputDir ./exports\\nlcm_export --peerId \\\"user:ou_xxx\\\"\\nlcm_export --chatType dm\\nlcm_export --from 2026-03-01 --to 2026-03-15\\n```\\n\\n**Output structure:**\\n```\\nexports/\\n├── dm/\\n│   └── Alice/\\n│       └── 2026-03/\\n│           └── 2026-03-14.md\\n└── group/\\n    └── Project-Alpha/\\n        └── 2026-03/\\n            └── 2026-03-14.md\\n```\\n\\n**Message format:**\\n```\\n[channel] 14:30 Alice: Hello, how are you?\\n[channel] 14:31 Assistant: I'm doing well, thanks!\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Enhanced lcm_grep\\n\\nAdded peer filters to conversation search:\\n\\n```bash\\nlcm_grep --pattern \\\"hello\\\" --peerId \\\"user:ou_xxx\\\"\\nlcm_grep --pattern \\\"meeting\\\" --chatType group\\nlcm_grep --pattern \\\"bug\\\" --channel feishu\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Automatic Peer Extraction\\n\\nRegistered `message_received` hook to auto-extract peer info from inbound messages:\\n\\n- **DMs**: peer = sender (`user:xxx`)\\n- **Groups**: peer = chat/group (`chat:xxx`)\\n\\nNo manual setup required — contacts are created automatically when messages arrive.\\n\\n### 6. lcm_update_peer Tool (Manual Override)\\n\\nManually update peer info if needed:\\n\\n```bash\\nlcm_update_peer --peerId \\\"user:ou_xxx\\\" --peerName \\\"Alice\\\" --channel feishu --chatType dm\\n```\\n\\n## Testing\\n\\n- Added 4 unit tests for export functionality\\n- All 251 tests passing\\n- Uses in-memory SQLite for isolated testing\\n\\n## Use Cases\\n\\n- **Archive conversations** organized by who you talked to\\n- **Search history** filtered by peer, channel, or chat type\\n- **Export for analysis** or migration to other systems\\n- **Audit trails** with clear organization by contact\\n\\n## Breaking Changes\\n\\nNone. The schema additions are additive and backward-compatible.\\n\\n## Migration\\n\\nExisting LCM databases will be automatically migrated on next startup with the new columns and contacts table.\",\"headRefName\":\"main\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"feat: add contacts table and conversation export\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/64\"}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":261,"aggregated":"{\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nThis PR adds peer tracking and conversation export functionality to LCM, enabling organized export of conversations by who you talked to.\\n\\n## Features\\n\\n### 1. Database Schema\\n\\n**New `contacts` table:**\\n```sql\\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n  peer_name TEXT,\\n  chat_type TEXT CHECK (chat_type IN ('dm', 'group'))\\n);\\n```\\n\\n**New columns in `conversations` table:**\\n```sql\\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN peer_id TEXT REFERENCES contacts(peer_id);\\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN channel TEXT;\\n```\\n\\n### 2. ContactStore\\n\\nNew store for managing contacts:\\n- `create()` — Create or update a contact\\n- `get()` — Get contact by peer_id\\n- `getAll()` — List all contacts\\n- `update()` — Update contact fields\\n- `delete()` — Delete a contact\\n\\n### 3. lcm_export Tool\\n\\nExport conversations to markdown files organized by peer and date.\\n\\n```bash\\nlcm_export --outputDir ./exports\\nlcm_export --peerId \\\"user:ou_xxx\\\"\\nlcm_export --chatType dm\\nlcm_export --from 2026-03-01 --to 2026-03-15\\n```\\n\\n**Output structure:**\\n```\\nexports/\\n├── dm/\\n│   └── Alice/\\n│       └── 2026-03/\\n│           └── 2026-03-14.md\\n└── group/\\n    └── Project-Alpha/\\n        └── 2026-03/\\n            └── 2026-03-14.md\\n```\\n\\n**Message format:**\\n```\\n[channel] 14:30 Alice: Hello, how are you?\\n[channel] 14:31 Assistant: I'm doing well, thanks!\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Enhanced lcm_grep\\n\\nAdded peer filters to conversation search:\\n\\n```bash\\nlcm_grep --pattern \\\"hello\\\" --peerId \\\"user:ou_xxx\\\"\\nlcm_grep --pattern \\\"meeting\\\" --chatType group\\nlcm_grep --pattern \\\"bug\\\" --channel feishu\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Automatic Peer Extraction\\n\\nRegistered `message_received` hook to auto-extract peer info from inbound messages:\\n\\n- **DMs**: peer = sender (`user:xxx`)\\n- **Groups**: peer = chat/group (`chat:xxx`)\\n\\nNo manual setup required — contacts are created automatically when messages arrive.\\n\\n### 6. lcm_update_peer Tool (Manual Override)\\n\\nManually update peer info if needed:\\n\\n```bash\\nlcm_update_peer --peerId \\\"user:ou_xxx\\\" --peerName \\\"Alice\\\" --channel feishu --chatType dm\\n```\\n\\n## Testing\\n\\n- Added 4 unit tests for export functionality\\n- All 251 tests passing\\n- Uses in-memory SQLite for isolated testing\\n\\n## Use Cases\\n\\n- **Archive conversations** organized by who you talked to\\n- **Search history** filtered by peer, channel, or chat type\\n- **Export for analysis** or migration to other systems\\n- **Audit trails** with clear organization by contact\\n\\n## Breaking Changes\\n\\nNone. The schema additions are additive and backward-compatible.\\n\\n## Migration\\n\\nExisting LCM databases will be automatically migrated on next startup with the new columns and contacts table.\",\"headRefName\":\"main\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"feat: add contacts table and conversation export\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/64\"}","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773543068588}}
{"type":"message","id":"5419e1df","parentId":"4288ea2d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:51:27.480Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, the existing PR #64 is about contacts table and conversation export, not about preserve tags. My preserve tag commit was pushed to the same branch (`main`) on my fork, which means it was added to the existing PR.\n\nLet me verify that my preserve tag changes are now part of PR #64 by checking if the commit is there.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I see - PR #64 is about contacts and export. My preserve tag commit was pushed to the same branch, so it got added to that PR. Let me verify the commit is there."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5c359c8e426d40eaa72b1015","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh pr view 64 --repo Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw --json commits --jq '.commits[-5:]'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":48437,"output":183,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48620,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773543068595}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ba175c6","parentId":"5419e1df","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:51:27.760Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5c359c8e426d40eaa72b1015","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-14T15:45:56Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-14T15:45:56Z\",\"messageBody\":\"- Test DM conversation export to correct directory\\n- Test group conversation export\\n- Test peerId filtering\\n- Test handling of missing peer info\\n- Uses in-memory database, no effect on production\",\"messageHeadline\":\"test: add unit tests for LCM export\",\"oid\":\"3c77598a29732a12e5cf3f318e082fa1461c90d9\"},{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:15:17Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:15:17Z\",\"messageBody\":\"- Add --peerId, --channel, --chatType parameters to lcm_grep\\n- Update MessageSearchInput to include peer filters\\n- Update searchFullText, searchLike, searchRegex methods\\n- JOIN with conversations and contacts tables for filtering\\n\\nUsage:\\n  lcm_grep --pattern 'hello' --peerId 'user:alice'\\n  lcm_grep --pattern 'meeting' --chatType group\\n  lcm_grep --pattern 'bug' --channel feishu\",\"messageHeadline\":\"feat: add peer filters to lcm_grep\",\"oid\":\"4387208016077a8102bf7ef615aec80b0b9a26cc\"},{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:40:42Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:40:42Z\",\"messageBody\":\"- Add updateConversationPeer method to LcmContextEngine\\n- Auto-creates/updates contact when peer info is provided\\n- Updates conversation with peer_id and channel\\n- Add lcm_update_peer tool for manual or automatic peer updates\\n\\nUsage:\\n  lcm_update_peer --peerId 'user:alice' --peerName 'Alice' --channel feishu --chatType dm\\n\\nIntegration:\\n- OpenClaw can call this when receiving inbound metadata\\n- Can also be called manually to update peer info\",\"messageHeadline\":\"feat: add peer extraction with lcm_update_peer tool\",\"oid\":\"67df16b7fe57d0e79035e41a9d8a415f47f829f1\"},{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:56:35Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:56:35Z\",\"messageBody\":\"- Register message_received hook in LCM plugin\\n- Auto-extract peer info from inbound metadata\\n- DM: peer is sender (user:xxx)\\n- Group: peer is chat/group\\n- Automatically populates contacts table on message receipt\\n\\nThis enables automatic contact creation without manual calls to lcm_update_peer.\",\"messageHeadline\":\"feat: add automatic peer extraction via message_received hook\",\"oid\":\"cfdfdbc267614bebadcbff25618509e2449fb8e1\"},{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-15T02:48:09Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-15T02:49:49Z\",\"messageBody\":\"Add support for \\u003c!-- preserve --\\u003e...\\u003c!-- /preserve --\\u003e tags to prevent\\ncertain content from being ingested into the LCM database.\\n\\nThis is useful for bootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, etc.) that are\\ninjected fresh each turn by the host system. Without this, the same\\ncontent would be duplicated in the context on every turn.\\n\\nThe preserve tag format is intentionally generic (not LCM-specific) so\\nany context engine implementation can respect it.\\n\\n- Add preserve tag detection in ingestSingle()\\n- Add support for optional type suffix: \\u003c!-- preserve:soul --\\u003e\\n- Add 3 tests for preserve tag functionality\",\"messageHeadline\":\"feat: add preserve tag support for bootstrap files\",\"oid\":\"811f395de25dcbb6290c897a8695b79cdc917232\"}]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":269,"aggregated":"[{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-14T15:45:56Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-14T15:45:56Z\",\"messageBody\":\"- Test DM conversation export to correct directory\\n- Test group conversation export\\n- Test peerId filtering\\n- Test handling of missing peer info\\n- Uses in-memory database, no effect on production\",\"messageHeadline\":\"test: add unit tests for LCM export\",\"oid\":\"3c77598a29732a12e5cf3f318e082fa1461c90d9\"},{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:15:17Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:15:17Z\",\"messageBody\":\"- Add --peerId, --channel, --chatType parameters to lcm_grep\\n- Update MessageSearchInput to include peer filters\\n- Update searchFullText, searchLike, searchRegex methods\\n- JOIN with conversations and contacts tables for filtering\\n\\nUsage:\\n  lcm_grep --pattern 'hello' --peerId 'user:alice'\\n  lcm_grep --pattern 'meeting' --chatType group\\n  lcm_grep --pattern 'bug' --channel feishu\",\"messageHeadline\":\"feat: add peer filters to lcm_grep\",\"oid\":\"4387208016077a8102bf7ef615aec80b0b9a26cc\"},{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:40:42Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:40:42Z\",\"messageBody\":\"- Add updateConversationPeer method to LcmContextEngine\\n- Auto-creates/updates contact when peer info is provided\\n- Updates conversation with peer_id and channel\\n- Add lcm_update_peer tool for manual or automatic peer updates\\n\\nUsage:\\n  lcm_update_peer --peerId 'user:alice' --peerName 'Alice' --channel feishu --chatType dm\\n\\nIntegration:\\n- OpenClaw can call this when receiving inbound metadata\\n- Can also be called manually to update peer info\",\"messageHeadline\":\"feat: add peer extraction with lcm_update_peer tool\",\"oid\":\"67df16b7fe57d0e79035e41a9d8a415f47f829f1\"},{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:56:35Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-14T16:56:35Z\",\"messageBody\":\"- Register message_received hook in LCM plugin\\n- Auto-extract peer info from inbound metadata\\n- DM: peer is sender (user:xxx)\\n- Group: peer is chat/group\\n- Automatically populates contacts table on message receipt\\n\\nThis enables automatic contact creation without manual calls to lcm_update_peer.\",\"messageHeadline\":\"feat: add automatic peer extraction via message_received hook\",\"oid\":\"cfdfdbc267614bebadcbff25618509e2449fb8e1\"},{\"authoredDate\":\"2026-03-15T02:48:09Z\",\"authors\":[{\"email\":\"ubuntu@vps-7303abe5.vps.ovh.us\",\"id\":\"\",\"login\":\"\",\"name\":\"Ubuntu\"}],\"committedDate\":\"2026-03-15T02:49:49Z\",\"messageBody\":\"Add support for \\u003c!-- preserve --\\u003e...\\u003c!-- /preserve --\\u003e tags to prevent\\ncertain content from being ingested into the LCM database.\\n\\nThis is useful for bootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, etc.) that are\\ninjected fresh each turn by the host system. Without this, the same\\ncontent would be duplicated in the context on every turn.\\n\\nThe preserve tag format is intentionally generic (not LCM-specific) so\\nany context engine implementation can respect it.\\n\\n- Add preserve tag detection in ingestSingle()\\n- Add support for optional type suffix: \\u003c!-- preserve:soul --\\u003e\\n- Add 3 tests for preserve tag functionality\",\"messageHeadline\":\"feat: add preserve tag support for bootstrap files\",\"oid\":\"811f395de25dcbb6290c897a8695b79cdc917232\"}]","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773543087750}}
{"type":"message","id":"96dba082","parentId":"4ba175c6","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:51:56.900Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"My preserve tag commit (`feat: add preserve tag support for bootstrap files`) is now the latest commit in PR #64. This is actually fine - the PR now contains both the contacts/export feature AND the preserve tag feature.\n\nBut wait - I should think about whether this is the right approach. The PR now has two unrelated features:\n1. Contacts table and conversation export\n2. Preserve tag support for bootstrap files\n\nIt might be better to create a separate PR for the preserve tag feature. But since the commit is already pushed to the same branch, it's now combined.\n\nLet me check if this is okay or if I should create a separate branch for preserve tags.\n\nActually, since Allan said \"finish the lcm code, no need pr openclaw\", I think he's okay with whatever approach works. The preserve tag feature is now part of PR #64. I should let Allan know that:\n\n1. The preserve tag feature is implemented and tested (all 250 tests pass)\n2. It's been added to the existing PR #64 (which was about contacts/export)\n3. The PR is ready for review\n\nLet me update the PR description to mention both features, or create a comment about the preserve tag feature.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"My preserve tag commit is now in PR #64. The PR now contains two features:\n1. Contacts table and conversation export\n2. Preserve tag support for bootstrap files\n\nLet me add a comment to the PR to document the preserve tag feature."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_518b847564a34a6d98d503b3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh pr comment 64 --repo Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Update: Added Preserve Tag Support\n\nThis PR now also includes support for `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags to prevent certain content from being ingested into the LCM database.\n\n### Motivation\n\nBootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, etc.) are injected fresh each turn by the host system (OpenClaw). Without this feature, the same content would be duplicated in the context on every turn, eventually getting compacted into summaries and potentially lost or distorted.\n\n### Implementation\n\n- Add preserve tag detection in `ingestSingle()` method\n- Content wrapped with preserve tags is skipped during ingest\n- Support optional type suffix: `<!-- preserve:soul -->` (for documentation)\n- Tag format is intentionally generic so any context engine can respect it\n\n### Tests\n\nAdded 3 tests for preserve tag functionality. All 250 tests pass.\nEOF\n)\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":49621,"output":621,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50242,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773543087758}}
