{"type":"message","id":"f668df9a","parentId":"d971cb4d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:59:17.333Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've recorded the progress. Now I should check the HEARTBEAT.md for the Free Mind Protocol instructions. But since I just finished the LCM preserve tag task and am waiting for Allan's feedback, I should check if there are any other tasks in the TODO.md or if I should enter Free Explore Mode.\n\nLet me check the TODO.md to see if there's anything to work on.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Working on LCM preserve tag PR. Created separate PR #78, reverted from PR #64. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":55428,"output":142,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55570,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773543536830}}
{"type":"message","id":"69d702fe","parentId":"f668df9a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:59:17.556Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b545646cdb0a0c4db0e9b38e7e3a\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 10:59 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b545646cdb0a0c4db0e9b38e7e3a]\n任亚伦: not only prevent from ingesting, should also prevent it from compress or compact. make sure it's in all context"}],"timestamp":1773543557548}}
{"type":"message","id":"ececea19","parentId":"69d702fe","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:59:51.674Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is saying that the preserve tag should not only prevent ingestion, but also prevent compression/compaction. He wants to make sure the preserve-tagged content is ALWAYS in the context.\n\nThis is a different requirement than what I implemented. I implemented:\n- Skip ingest for preserve-tagged content\n\nBut Allan wants:\n- Skip ingest (so it's not duplicated in the database)\n- ALSO: Make sure it's ALWAYS in the context (never compacted away)\n\nWait, let me think about this more carefully. The bootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, etc.) are injected fresh each turn by OpenClaw. So they ARE always in the context - they're injected as new messages each turn.\n\nThe issue is:\n1. If LCM ingests them, they get duplicated in the database\n2. If we skip ingest, they're not in the database at all\n3. But they're still injected fresh each turn by OpenClaw, so they ARE in the context\n\nSo actually, my implementation is correct - by skipping ingest, the preserve-tagged content is:\n- NOT in the LCM database (no duplication)\n- BUT still injected fresh each turn by OpenClaw (always in context)\n\nBut wait, Allan mentioned \"prevent it from compress or compact\". Let me think about this...\n\nThe compaction process works on messages that are stored in the LCM database. If we skip ingest, the messages are not in the database at all, so they can't be compacted.\n\nBut the issue might be: what if OpenClaw's bootstrap injection is part of the message flow that LCM sees? Let me re-read the earlier context...\n\nFrom the earlier context, I learned that:\n1. OpenClaw injects bootstrap files on every turn (as user messages)\n2. LCM sees these as regular messages and ingests them\n3. Over time, these bootstrap files get compacted into summaries\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. OpenClaw injects bootstrap files → message sent to LLM\n2. LCM also ingests these bootstrap files into the database\n3. Over time, LCM compacts old messages, including bootstrap files, into summaries\n\n\n4. If we skip ingest, the bootstrap files won't be in the LCM database, so they can't be compacted\n5. But they're still injected fresh each turn by OpenClaw, so they ARE in the context\n\nMy implementation should be correct then. But Allan is saying \"should also prevent it from compress or compact\" - maybe he thinks the bootstrap files could still get compacted somehow, or he's concerned about a different scenario where preserve-tagged content needs protection from compaction even if it's already ingested before the preserve tags were added.\n\nThe challenge is that the bootstrap files are already in the LCM database from earlier turns. Adding preserve tags now would prevent future ingestion, but it won't remove what's already there. And if I delete the existing data, the preserve-tagged content still needs to be injected each turn to stay in context.\n\nI should check with Allan to clarify what he's actually worried about—is it the old data, the new tagged content, or something else entirely?","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I understand, 爸爸. Let me clarify the requirement:\n\n**Current implementation:**\n- Skip ingest → content NOT in LCM database → can't be compacted\n- Bootstrap files injected fresh each turn by OpenClaw → always in context\n\n**But you're saying:**\n- Preserve-tagged content should be **guaranteed to be in context** even if it WAS ingested before\n- Need to prevent compaction from removing it\n\nThis means I need to also handle the **assemble** phase - when LCM builds the context, it should check for preserve-tagged content and ensure it's included.\n\nLet me check the assemble method to see where to add this logic:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a583592dc7b742cd8ab965ea","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw/src/engine.ts","limit":100,"offset":400}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":55808,"output":1118,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56926,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773543557552}}
{"type":"message","id":"54f61ad9","parentId":"ececea19","timestamp":"2026-03-15T02:59:51.698Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a583592dc7b742cd8ab965ea","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":" *\n *   \"user\"      -> \"user\"\n *   \"assistant\" -> \"assistant\"\n *\n * AgentMessage only has user/assistant roles, but we keep the mapping\n * explicit for clarity and future-proofing.\n */\nfunction toDbRole(role: string): \"user\" | \"assistant\" | \"system\" | \"tool\" {\n  if (role === \"tool\" || role === \"toolResult\") {\n    return \"tool\";\n  }\n  if (role === \"system\") {\n    return \"system\";\n  }\n  if (role === \"user\") {\n    return \"user\";\n  }\n  if (role === \"assistant\") {\n    return \"assistant\";\n  }\n  // Unknown roles are preserved via message_parts metadata and treated as assistant.\n  return \"assistant\";\n}\n\ntype StoredMessage = {\n  role: \"user\" | \"assistant\" | \"system\" | \"tool\";\n  content: string;\n  tokenCount: number;\n};\n\n/**\n * Normalize AgentMessage variants into the storage shape used by LCM.\n */\nfunction toStoredMessage(message: AgentMessage): StoredMessage {\n  const content =\n    \"content\" in message\n      ? extractMessageContent(message.content)\n      : \"output\" in message\n        ? `$ ${(message as { command: string; output: string }).command}\\n${(message as { command: string; output: string }).output}`\n        : \"\";\n  const runtimeRole = toRuntimeRoleForTokenEstimate(message.role);\n  const tokenCount =\n    \"content\" in message\n      ? estimateContentTokensForRole({\n          role: runtimeRole,\n          content: message.content,\n          fallbackContent: content,\n        })\n      : estimateTokens(content);\n\n  return {\n    role: toDbRole(message.role),\n    content,\n    tokenCount,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction estimateMessageContentTokensForAfterTurn(content: unknown): number {\n  if (typeof content === \"string\") {\n    return estimateTokens(content);\n  }\n  if (Array.isArray(content)) {\n    let total = 0;\n    for (const part of content) {\n      if (!part || typeof part !== \"object\") {\n        continue;\n      }\n      const record = part as Record<string, unknown>;\n      const text =\n        typeof record.text === \"string\"\n          ? record.text\n          : typeof record.thinking === \"string\"\n            ? record.thinking\n            : \"\";\n      if (text) {\n        total += estimateTokens(text);\n      }\n    }\n    return total;\n  }\n  if (content == null) {\n    return 0;\n  }\n  const serialized = JSON.stringify(content);\n  return estimateTokens(typeof serialized === \"string\" ? serialized : \"\");\n}\n\nfunction estimateSessionTokenCountForAfterTurn(messages: AgentMessage[]): number {\n  let total = 0;\n  for (const message of messages) {\n    if (\"content\" in message) {\n      total += estimateMessageContentTokensForAfterTurn(message.content);\n      continue;\n    }\n    if (\"command\" in message || \"output\" in message) {\n      const commandText =\n        typeof (message as { command?: unknown }).command === \"string\"\n          ? (message as { command?: string }).command\n          : \"\";\n      const outputText =\n\n[1381 more lines in file. Use offset=500 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773543591688}}
