{"type":"message","id":"53fc3a92","parentId":"fa5da56e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:00:39.183Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4e30737f010647fb9c3e80cb","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  async assemble(params: {\n    sessionId: string;\n    messages: AgentMessage[];\n    tokenBudget?: number;\n  }): Promise<AssembleResult> {\n    try {\n      this.ensureMigrated();\n\n      const conversation = await this.conversationStore.getConversationBySessionId(\n        params.sessionId,\n      );\n      if (!conversation) {\n        return {\n          messages: params.messages,\n          estimatedTokens: 0,\n        };\n      }\n\n      const contextItems = await this.summaryStore.getContextItems(conversation.conversationId);\n      if (contextItems.length === 0) {\n        return {\n          messages: params.messages,\n          estimatedTokens: 0,\n        };\n      }\n\n      // Guard against incomplete bootstrap/coverage: if the DB only has\n      // raw context items and clearly trails the current live history, keep\n      // the live path to avoid dropping prompt context.\n      const hasSummaryItems = contextItems.some((item) => item.itemType === \"summary\");\n      if (!hasSummaryItems && contextItems.length < params.messages.length) {\n        return {\n          messages: params.messages,\n          estimatedTokens: 0,\n        };\n      }\n\n      const tokenBudget =\n        typeof params.tokenBudget === \"number\" &&\n        Number.isFinite(params.tokenBudget) &&\n        params.tokenBudget > 0\n          ? Math.floor(params.tokenBudget)\n          : 128_000;\n\n      const assembled = await this.assembler.assemble({\n        conversationId: conversation.conversationId,\n        tokenBudget,\n        freshTailCount: this.config.freshTailCount,\n      });\n\n      // If assembly produced no messages for a non-empty live session,\n      // fail safe to the live context.\n      if (assembled.messages.length === 0 && params.messages.length > 0) {\n        return {\n          messages: params.messages,\n          estimatedTokens: 0,\n        };\n      }\n\n      const result: AssembleResultWithSystemPrompt = {\n        messages: assembled.messages,\n        estimatedTokens: assembled.estimatedTokens,\n        ...(assembled.systemPromptAddition\n          ? { systemPromptAddition: assembled.systemPromptAddition }\n          : {}),\n      };\n      return result;\n    } catch {\n      return {\n        messages: params.messages,\n        estimatedTokens: 0,\n      };\n    }\n  }\n\n  /** Evaluate whether incremental leaf compaction should run for a session. */\n  async evaluateLeafTrigger(sessionId: string): Promise<{\n    shouldCompact: boolean;\n    rawTokensOutsideTail: number;\n    threshold: number;\n\n[446 more lines in file. Use offset=1435 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773543639170}}
{"type":"message","id":"74742d36","parentId":"53fc3a92","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:01:15.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The `assemble` method uses the `assembler` to build the context from the database. The context is built from:\n1. Context items stored in the database (raw messages and summaries)\n2. The live messages passed to the method\n\nThe issue is that if we skip ingest, the preserve-tagged content won't be in the database at all. So when `assemble` is called, it won't include the preserve-tagged content from the database.\n\nBut wait - the preserve-tagged content is injected by OpenClaw as live messages each turn. So it will be in `params.messages`, not in the database.\n\nActually, let me re-read the code:\n1. `assemble` takes `params.messages` (live messages) and returns them if no context items\n2. If context items exist, it uses the assembler to build from database\n\nSo the flow is:\n- Live messages (including bootstrap files) are in `params.messages`\n- LCM adds stored context from database\n- The result is the combination\n\nThe issue is: if we skip ingest, bootstrap files are in `params.messages` (live) but NOT in the database. This should be fine - they're still in the context.\n\nBut Allan's concern might be:\n1. If the bootstrap files WERE ingested before (old data), they might get compacted\n2. We need to ensure they're always present, even if compacted\n\nActually, I think I understand now. Allan wants to make sure that:\n1. Preserve-tagged content is NEVER ingested (done)\n2. Preserve-tagged content is NEVER compacted (need to check if this is an issue)\n\nBut if we never ingest, there's nothing to compact. The preserve-tagged content is only in the live messages (`params.messages`), not in the database.\n\nWait, but there's another issue: what if the bootstrap files were ingested BEFORE the preserve tags were added? In that case, they're already in the database and might get compacted.\n\