{"type":"message","id":"cb9c8485","parentId":"663955eb","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:04:14.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the `selectOldestLeafChunk` function.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fba5b338d6b54011aad48d20","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw/src/compaction.ts","limit":80,"offset":640}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":61789,"output":60,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61849,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773543831587}}
{"type":"message","id":"82cd9b7e","parentId":"cb9c8485","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:04:14.058Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fba5b338d6b54011aad48d20","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  private async selectOldestLeafChunk(conversationId: number): Promise<LeafChunkSelection> {\n    const contextItems = await this.summaryStore.getContextItems(conversationId);\n    const freshTailOrdinal = this.resolveFreshTailOrdinal(contextItems);\n    const threshold = this.resolveLeafChunkTokens();\n\n    let rawTokensOutsideTail = 0;\n    for (const item of contextItems) {\n      if (item.ordinal >= freshTailOrdinal) {\n        break;\n      }\n      if (item.itemType !== \"message\" || item.messageId == null) {\n        continue;\n      }\n      rawTokensOutsideTail += await this.getMessageTokenCount(item.messageId);\n    }\n\n    const chunk: ContextItemRecord[] = [];\n    let chunkTokens = 0;\n    let started = false;\n    for (const item of contextItems) {\n      if (item.ordinal >= freshTailOrdinal) {\n        break;\n      }\n\n      if (!started) {\n        if (item.itemType !== \"message\" || item.messageId == null) {\n          continue;\n        }\n        started = true;\n      } else if (item.itemType !== \"message\" || item.messageId == null) {\n        break;\n      }\n\n      if (item.messageId == null) {\n        continue;\n      }\n      const messageTokens = await this.getMessageTokenCount(item.messageId);\n      if (chunk.length > 0 && chunkTokens + messageTokens > threshold) {\n        break;\n      }\n\n      chunk.push(item);\n      chunkTokens += messageTokens;\n      if (chunkTokens >= threshold) {\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n\n    return { items: chunk, rawTokensOutsideTail, threshold };\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Resolve recent summary continuity for a leaf pass.\n   *\n   * Collects up to two most recent summary context items that precede the\n   * compacted raw-message chunk and returns their combined content.\n   */\n  private async resolvePriorLeafSummaryContext(\n    conversationId: number,\n    messageItems: ContextItemRecord[],\n  ): Promise<string | undefined> {\n    if (messageItems.length === 0) {\n      return undefined;\n    }\n\n    const startOrdinal = Math.min(...messageItems.map((item) => item.ordinal));\n    const priorSummaryItems = (await this.summaryStore.getContextItems(conversationId))\n      .filter(\n        (item) =>\n          item.ordinal < startOrdinal &&\n          item.itemType === \"summary\" &&\n          typeof item.summaryId === \"string\",\n      )\n      .slice(-2);\n\n    if (priorSummaryItems.length === 0) {\n      return undefined;\n    }\n\n    const summaryContents: string[] = [];\n\n[614 more lines in file. Use offset=720 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773543854044}}
{"type":"message","id":"b8ae2990","parentId":"82cd9b7e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:04:45.474Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The `selectOldestLeafChunk` function selects messages for compaction. It:\n1. Gets all context items\n2. Calculates the fresh tail ordinal (messages to protect)\n3. Iterates through items, skipping those in the fresh tail\n4. Builds a chunk of messages to compact\n\nI need to add a check to also skip messages that have preserve tags. This means:\n1. When iterating through messages, check if the message content has preserve tags\n2. If it does, skip it (don't include in the chunk)\n\nBut wait - if we skip ingest for preserve-tagged content, they won't be in the database at all. So this check would never find any preserve-tagged messages in the database.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully:\n\n**Scenario 1: Fresh installation with preserve tags from the start**\n- Preserve-tagged content is never ingested\n- It's never in the database\n- It can't be compacted\n- ✅ Works correctly\n\n**Scenario 2: Existing data without preserve tags**\n- Old bootstrap files were already ingested\n- They're in the database\n- They might get compacted\n- ❌ Problem: old data could be lost\n\n**Scenario 3: Adding preserve tags later**\n- Old bootstrap files are already in the database\n- Future injections have preserve tags and won't be ingested\n- Old data is still in the database and might get compacted\n- ❌ Problem: old data could be lost\n\nSo Allan is right - I need to also handle the compaction case. Even though new preserve-tagged content won't be ingested, old data might still be in the database.\n\nI need to:\n1. Add a check in `selectOldestLeafChunk` to skip messages with preserve tags\n2. Also add the same check in other compaction selection functions\n\nLet me also check if there's a way to get the message content in the selection function.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","tex