{"type":"message","id":"7b724444","parentId":"61c0eb84","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:24:45.969Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is reminding me that the preserve tag should not only prevent ingestion but also prevent compression/compaction, ensuring it's in all contexts.\n\nBut I already did this! I just added:\n1. `hasPreserveTag()` helper function\n2. Updated `selectOldestLeafChunk()` to skip preserve-tagged messages\n3. Updated `selectOldestChunkAtDepth()` to skip preserve-tagged summaries\n4. All 254 tests pass\n\nI think Allan might not have seen my update yet. Let me confirm that I've already done this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"这个已经做好了！我刚才添加了 compaction 保护：\n\n**已完成的改动：**\n\n1. **`hasPreserveTag()` helper** - 检测 `<!-- preserve -->` 标签\n2. **`selectOldestLeafChunk()`** - 跳过带 preserve tag 的消息\n3. **`selectOldestChunkAtDepth()`** - 跳过带 preserve tag 的摘要\n\n这样 preserve-tagged 内容既不会被 ingest，也不会被 compact。它会永远保留在原始消息中，每次 assemble context 时都会被包含。\n\n所有 254 个测试通过 ✓\n\n要我检查一下 assemble 阶段是否也需要特殊处理吗？还是原始消息会被自动包含？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":44591,"output":313,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44904,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773545073989}}
{"type":"message","id":"d349a3c3","parentId":"7b724444","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:25:25.042Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5456248caca0c1141c06980aecf\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 11:25 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5456248caca0c1141c06980aecf]\n任亚伦: reply in english, what's the assemble phase?"}],"timestamp":1773545125035}}
{"type":"message","id":"aaca9e9a","parentId":"d349a3c3","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:25:40.544Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking me to reply in English and explain what the assemble phase is. Let me explain the assemble phase in LCM.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"The **assemble phase** is when LCM builds the context that gets sent to the LLM.\n\n**LCM Flow:**\n\n```\ningest → store messages → compact (when threshold hit) → assemble (on each turn)\n```\n\n**What assemble does:**\n1. Takes recent messages (fresh tail, protected by `freshTailCount`)\n2. Takes summaries (leaf + condensed) to represent older messages\n3. Combines them into the final context window\n\n**The concern:**\n\nIf bootstrap files are **never ingested** (my current implementation), they won't be in the LCM database at all. So during assemble:\n- They won't appear in messages (never stored)\n- They won't appear in summaries (never stored)\n\n**But wait** - OpenClaw injects bootstrap files fresh on every turn. They come from **OpenClaw**, not from LCM.\n\nSo the question is: **Is OpenClaw's injection happening before or after LCM's assemble?**\n\nIf OpenClaw injects bootstrap files into the context independently of LCM, then we don't need to worry - they'll always be there regardless of LCM's state.\n\nLet me check how OpenClaw integrates with LCM's assemble phase."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":45082,"output":297,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45379,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773545125039}}
