{"type":"message","id":"acbfce84","parentId":"4da9f8d1","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:38:31.355Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that the assemble method takes `params.messages` as input - these are the live messages from the current session. If there's no conversation or no context items, it just returns `params.messages` unchanged.\n\nThis tells me that OpenClaw passes the current live messages (including bootstrap files) to LCM's assemble, and LCM returns the assembled context. But the question is: does LCM's assemble include the live messages in the output, or does it only return messages from the database?\n\nLet me check the full assemble method to understand the flow.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8380133487714e34be6c9331","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"async assemble\" /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw/src/engine.ts -A 60 | head -80"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":49612,"output":210,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49822,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773545890889}}
