enBudget =\n1348-        typeof params.tokenBudget === \"number\" &&\n1349-        Number.isFinite(params.tokenBudget) &&\n1350-        params.tokenBudget > 0\n1351-          ? Math.floor(params.tokenBudget)\n1352-          : 128_000;\n1353-\n1354-      const assembled = await this.assembler.assemble({\n1355-        conversationId: conversation.conversationId,\n1356-        tokenBudget,\n1357-        freshTailCount: this.config.freshTailCount,\n1358-      });\n1359-\n1360-      // If assembly produced no messages for a non-empty live session,\n1361-      // fail safe to the live context.\n1362-      if (assembled.messages.length === 0 && params.messages.length > 0) {\n1363-        return {\n1364-          messages: params.messages,\n1365-          estimatedTokens: 0,\n1366-        };\n1367-      }\n1368-\n1369-      const result: AssembleResultWithSystemPrompt = {\n1370-        messages: assembled.messages,","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773545911373}}
{"type":"message","id":"5e15935a","parentId":"86d9623a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:39:03.398Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! The assemble method:\n1. Gets the conversation from the database\n2. Gets context items from the database\n3. Calls the assembler to build the context\n4. Returns the assembled messages\n\nBut the key insight is: **if there's no conversation or no context items, it returns `params.messages` (the live messages from OpenClaw)**.\n\nBut if there ARE context items, it returns `assembled.messages` from the LCM database - NOT the live messages from OpenClaw!\n\nThis means: **OpenClaw's bootstrap files are only included if LCM has no context items yet.** Once LCM starts storing messages, LCM's assemble takes over and the live messages are ignored.\n\nWait, let me re-read this more carefully. The `params.messages` are the live messages from the current session. If there's no conversation in LCM yet, it returns the live messages. But once there IS a conversation, it returns the assembled messages from LCM.\n\nBut this doesn't make sense - the live messages should always be included, right? Let me check the assembler to see if it includes fresh messages.\n\nActually, looking at the code again:\n- Line 1322-1325: If no conversation, return live messages\n- Line 1329-1334: If no context items, return live messages\n- Line 1340-1345: If no summaries and context items < live messages, return live messages\n- Line 1354-1358: Call assembler with tokenBudget and freshTailCount\n- Line 1362-1367: If assembler produced no messages but live has some, return live\n- Line 1369-1370: Return assembled.messages\n\nThe key is `freshTailCount` - this is passed to the assembler. The assembler should include the fresh tail (recent messages) in the assembled context.\n\nBut wait - the assembler gets messages from the database, not from the live params. So if bootstrap files were never ingested (because of preserve tag), they won't be in the database, and they won't be in the assembled context.\n\nThis is the problem! If we skip ingest for preserve-tagged content, it won't be in LCM's database, and assemble won't include it.\n \nHold on - I need to think about this differently. OpenClaw injects bootstrap files on every turn, and these live messages are passed to assemble. But looking at the flow, the assembled result only pulls from LCM's stored messages, not the live ones. So bootstrap files get lost once LCM takes over. Unless OpenClaw has a separate mechanism for injecting bootstrap files after LCM's assemble completes.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I see the issue now. Let me check how OpenClaw integrates with the context engine to understand where bootstrap files are injected:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_af06aaa649ef439791c38233","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"bootstrap\\|contextEngine\" /home/ubuntu/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/ --include=\"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v node_modules | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":50355,"output":867,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51222,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773545911380}}
