{"type":"message","id":"667bd220","parentId":"e9549cb3","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:47:47.898Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that OpenClaw has `resolveBootstrapContextForRun` which builds bootstrap context files. Let me check how this integrates with the context engine's assemble.\n\nActually, I think the key insight is that OpenClaw injects bootstrap files as part of the live context, not as part of LCM's assembled context. Let me check if OpenClaw calls the context engine's assemble and then combines it with bootstrap files.\n\nActually, looking at the earlier conversation with Allan, I discovered that:\n1. OpenClaw injects bootstrap files on every turn\n2. These are passed to LCM's assemble as `params.messages`\n3. LCM's assemble returns assembled messages from its database\n4. The live messages (params.messages) are only used as fallback\n\nSo if LCM has a conversation, it returns assembled messages from the database, not the live messages. This means bootstrap files injected by OpenClaw would be lost if they're not in LCM's database.\n\nBut wait - maybe OpenClaw injects bootstrap files AFTER LCM's assemble? Let me check the flow more carefully.\n\nActually, let me just test the current implementation to see if it works. Allan said to check and test it.\n\nLet me:\n1. Check if OpenClaw injects bootstrap files after LCM's assemble\n2. If not, fix the implementation to ingest preserve-tagged content but not compact it","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check if OpenClaw injects bootstrap files **after** the context engine's assemble:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7a3240372a9e46ccba293342","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"contextEngine\\|assemble\" /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw/node_modules/openclaw/dist/runner-*.js 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":67433,"output":48