{"type":"message","id":"b2205a0d","parentId":"59441510","timestamp":"2026-03-15T03:54:13.897Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! Bootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, HEARTBEAT.md, AGENTS.md) ARE being ingested into the LCM database:\n- SOUL.md: 22 messages\n- IDENTITY.md: 17 messages\n- USER.md: 13 messages\n- HEARTBEAT.md: 38 messages\n- AGENTS.md: 16 messages\n\nThis means OpenClaw is injecting bootstrap files, and they ARE being ingested by LCM. The current preserve tag implementation (skip ingest) is NOT being applied to bootstrap files because they don't have the `<!-- preserve -->` tags yet.\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. OpenClaw injects bootstrap files as messages\n2. LCM ingests them (without preserve tags)\n3. LCM may compact them into summaries\n\nThe preserve tag feature is designed to:\n1. Wrap bootstrap files with `<!-- preserve -->` tags (OpenClaw PR - not done yet)\n2. LCM skips ingest for preserve-tagged content (current implementation)\n3. LCM skips compaction for preserve-tagged content (current implementation)\n\nBut if we skip ingest, bootstrap files won't be in LCM's database, and they won't appear in assembled context.\n\nWait - I need to re-think this. Let me check how OpenClaw integrates with LCM's assemble. The key is: does OpenClaw combine bootstrap files with LCM's assembled context, or does LCM's assemble control the entire context?\n\nActually, looking at the LCM assemble code again:\n- `params.messages` are passed in\n- If no conversation, return `params.messages`\n- If conversation, return assembled messages from database\n\nSo if LCM has a conversation, it returns assembled messages from its database, NOT the live messages from OpenClaw.\n\nThis means:\n- If we skip ingest for bootstrap files → they won't be in database → they won't appear in assembled context\n- OpenClaw must inject bootstrap files AFTER LCM's assemble for this to work\n\n\n- I should check if OpenClaw has a mechanism to inject bootstrap files after LCM returns the assembled context","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I see bootstrap files ARE being ingested into LCM's database (22 SOUL.md, 17 IDENTITY.md, etc.). This means the preserve tag skip logic hasn't been applied to bootstrap files yet (they don't have the tags).\n\nLet me check the actual integration between OpenClaw and LCM's assemble to understand the flow:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f8601514a4ff40cbbefc6071","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ubuntu/.openclaw && grep -r \"assemble\\|bootstrap\" node_modules/openclaw/dist/plugins-*.js 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":71894,"output":739,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72633,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773546816099}}
