{"type":"message","id":"5941377e","parentId":"3e72df58","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:03:25.530Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems the ContextEngine interface is not exported as a type definition. Let me check the OpenClaw source code directly by looking at how the plugin registers itself.\n\nActually, let me just focus on testing the actual behavior. The key question is:\n1. Does the current implementation skip ingest for preserve-tagged content?\n2. Does it skip compaction for preserve-tagged content?\n3. Is this the correct behavior?\n\nLet me write a test that simulates the full flow:\n1. Ingest a preserve-tagged message\n2. Run compaction\n3. Assemble context\n4. Check if the preserve-tagged content appears in the assembled context\n\nActually, looking at the existing tests, I see there's already a test for \"skips preserve-tagged content in ingest\". Let me check what it expects.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the actual test to understand what behavior is expected:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7b879a619a454c4aa668be48","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw/test/engine.test.ts","limit":50,"offset":1476}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":64798,"output":221,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65019,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547380159}}
{"type":"message","id":"0236a7df","parentId":"5941377e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:03:25.552Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7b879a619a454c4aa668be48","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  it(\"skips preserve-tagged content in ingest\", async () => {\n    const engine = createEngine();\n    const sessionId = \"preserve-tag-session\";\n\n    // Message with preserve tags should be skipped\n    const result = await engine.ingest({\n      sessionId,\n      message: makeMessage({\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: \"<!-- preserve -->\\n# SOUL.md\\n\\nThis is bootstrap content.\\n<!-- /preserve -->\",\n      }),\n    });\n\n    expect(result.ingested).toBe(false);\n\n    // No conversation should be created since nothing was ingested\n    const conversation = await engine\n      .getConversationStore()\n      .getConversationBySessionId(sessionId);\n    expect(conversation).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it(\"skips preserve-tagged content with optional type suffix\", async () => {\n    const engine = createEngine();\n    const sessionId = \"preserve-tag-type-session\";\n\n    // Message with preserve:soul type suffix should also be skipped\n    const result = await engine.ingest({\n      sessionId,\n      message: makeMessage({\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: \"<!-- preserve:soul -->\\n# SOUL.md\\n\\nIdentity content.\\n<!-- /preserve -->\",\n      }),\n    });\n\n    expect(result.ingested).toBe(false);\n  });\n\n  it(\"ingests content without preserve tags normally\", async () => {\n    const engine = createEngine();\n    const sessionId = \"no-preserve-tag-session\";\n\n    const result = await engine.ingest({\n      sessionId,\n      message: makeMessage({\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: \"This is a regular message without preserve tags.\",\n      }),\n    });\n\n\n[506 more lines in file. Use offset=1526 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773547405542}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a889564","parentId":"0236a7df","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:03:52.681Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! The test expects:\n1. `result.ingested` to be `false` for preserve-tagged content\n2. No conversation to be created for preserve-tagged content\n\nThis confirms that the current implementation **skips ingest** for preserve-tagged content.\n\nBut based on my analysis, this might be wrong. If we skip ingest:\n- The content won't be in LCM's database\n- It won't appear in assembled context (when LCM has a conversation)\n\nThe comment says \"because it's re-injected fresh each turn by the host system\". This implies OpenClaw will inject the bootstrap files AFTER LCM's assemble, so they don't need to be in LCM's database.\n\nBut I need to verify this. Let me check if there's a test that verifies the assemble behavior.\n\nActually, looking at the earlier conversation with Allan, I found that:\n1. OpenClaw injects bootstrap files as messages\n2. These are passed to LCM's assemble as `params.messages`\n3. LCM's assemble returns assembled messages from its database, NOT the live messages\n\nSo if LCM has a conversation, it returns assembled messages from the database. The live messages (including bootstrap files) are only used as a fallback.\n\nThis means: **If we skip ingest, bootstrap files won't appear in assembled context when LCM has a conversation.**\n\nUnless OpenClaw injects bootstrap files AFTER LCM's assemble. I need to verify this.\n\nLet me check if there's a test for the assemble behavior with preserve-tagged content.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check if there's a test that verifies the assemble behavior:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ad65de7e32414b06abf9093a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw && grep -n \"assemble.*preserve\\|preserve.*assemble\" test/engine.test.ts"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":65383,"output":378,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65761,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547405549}}
{"type":"message","id":"06b47f7d","parentId":"8a889564","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:03:52.713Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ad65de7e32414b06abf9093a","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1031:  it(\"preserves structured toolResult content via message_parts and assembler\", async () => {\n1093:  it(\"preserves toolName through ingest-assemble round-trip for Gemini compatibility\", async () => {\n1145:  it(\"preserves toolResult error state through ingest-assemble round-trip\", async () => {"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":21,"aggregated":"1031:  it(\"preserves structured toolResult content via message_parts and assembler\", async () => {\n1093:  it(\"preserves toolName through ingest-assemble round-trip for Gemini compatibility\", async () => {\n1145:  it(\"preserves toolResult error state through ingest-assemble round-trip\", async () => {","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773547432703}}
{"type":"message","id":"ccdfb284","parentId":"06b47f7d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:04:18.691Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"These tests are about preserving content through the assemble round-trip, not about the preserve tag. Let me check if there's a test that verifies preserve-tagged content appears in assembled context.\n\nActually, I think I need to write a test that:\n1. Ingests some regular messages\n2. Ingests a preserve-tagged message (which should be skipped)\n3. Runs assemble\n4. Checks if the preserve-tagged content appears in assembled context\n\nBut wait - if we skip ingest for preserve-tagged content, it won't be in the database, so it can't appear in assembled context.\n\nThe question is: is this the correct behavior?\n\nLooking at the comment again:\n> Content wrapped with <!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve --> should not be ingested\n> because it's re-injected fresh each turn by the host system.\n\nThis implies OpenClaw will handle it. But I'm not sure if OpenClaw injects bootstrap files AFTER LCM's assemble or BEFORE.\n\nLet me write a test to verify the actual behavior.\n\nActually, I think the key insight is that OpenClaw should:\n1. Call LCM's assemble to get the assembled context\n2. Inject bootstrap files into the assembled context (or prepend them)\n\nThis way, bootstrap files are always fresh and don't need to be in LCM's database.\n\nLet me check if there's any documentation about this in the OpenClaw codebase.\n\nActually, let me just write a test to verify the current behavior and see if it makes sense.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me write a test to verify the full flow - ingest, compact, and assemble with preserve-tagged content:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d167ac32032b45f6837982d8","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw/test/engine.test.ts","limit":100,"offset":1900}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":65836,"output":377,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66213,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547432711}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f9fc998","parentId":"ccdfb284","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:04:18.713Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d167ac32032b45f6837982d8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  });\n\n  // ── Preserve tag tests ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n  it(\"skips preserve-tagged content in ingest\", async () => {\n    const engine = createEngine();\n    const sessionId = \"preserve-ingest-test\";\n\n    await engine.ingest({\n      sessionId,\n      message: {\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: `<!-- preserve -->\n# SOUL.md\n\nThis is identity content that should never be compacted.\n<!-- /preserve -->`,\n      },\n    });\n\n    const conversation =\n      await engine.getConversationStore().getConversationBySessionId(sessionId);\n    expect(conversation).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it(\"skips preserve-tagged content with optional type suffix\", async () => {\n    const engine = createEngine();\n    const sessionId = \"preserve-suffix-test\";\n\n    await engine.ingest({\n      sessionId,\n      message: {\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: `<!-- preserve:soul -->\n# SOUL.md\n\nIdentity content with type suffix.\n<!-- /preserve -->`,\n      },\n    });\n\n    const conversation =\n      await engine.getConversationStore().getConversationBySessionId(sessionId);\n    expect(conversation).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it(\"ingests content without preserve tags normally\", async () => {\n    const engine = createEngine();\n    const sessionId = \"no-preserve-test\";\n\n    await engine.ingest({\n      sessionId,\n      message: {\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: \"This is regular content without preserve tags.\",\n      },\n    });\n\n    const conversation =\n      await engine.getConversationStore().getConversationBySessionId(sessionId);\n    expect(conversation).not.toBeNull();\n    const messages = await engine.getConversationStore().getMessages(\n      conversation!.conversationId,\n    );\n    expect(messages).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(messages[0].content).toBe(\"This is regular content without preserve tags.\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"does not compact messages with preserve tags\", async () => {\n    const engine = createEngine();\n    const sessionId = \"preserve-compact-test\";\n\n    // Ingest regular messages\n    for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n      await engine.ingest({\n        sessionId,\n        message: { role: \"user\", content: `Regular message ${i}` },\n      });\n      await engine.ingest({\n        sessionId,\n        message: { role: \"assistant\", content: `Response ${i}` },\n      });\n    }\n\n    // Ingest a preserve-tagged message (simulating old data that was ingested before the feature)\n    const conversation =\n      await engine.getConversationStore().getConversationBySessionId(sessionId);\n    expect(conversation).not.toBeNull();\n\n    // Directly insert a preserve-tagged message into the database\n    // Get current max seq first\n    const messagesBeforeInsert = await engine.getConversationStore().getMessages(\n      conversation!.conversationId,\n    );\n    const maxSeq = Math.max(...messagesBeforeInsert.map((m) => m.seq ?? 0), 0);\n    await engine.getConversationStore().createMessage({\n      conversationId: conversation!.conversationId,\n      seq: maxSeq + 1,\n      role: \"user\",\n      content: `<!-- preserve -->\n\n[32 more lines in file. Use offset=2000 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773547458702}}
{"type":"message","id":"c3e4793b","parentId":"6f9fc998","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:04:38.270Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there's already a test for \"does not compact messages with preserve tags\". Let me read more of this test to understand the expected behavior.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ca1064eb3ad349dcb65c0653","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw/test/engine.test.ts","limit":80,"offset":1990}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":66902,"output":71,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66973,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547458709}}
{"type":"message","id":"328b7937","parentId":"c3e4793b","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:04:38.291Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ca1064eb3ad349dcb65c0653","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    // Get current max seq first\n    const messagesBeforeInsert = await engine.getConversationStore().getMessages(\n      conversation!.conversationId,\n    );\n    const maxSeq = Math.max(...messagesBeforeInsert.map((m) => m.seq ?? 0), 0);\n    await engine.getConversationStore().createMessage({\n      conversationId: conversation!.conversationId,\n      seq: maxSeq + 1,\n      role: \"user\",\n      content: `<!-- preserve -->\n# SOUL.md\nIdentity content that should not be compacted.\n<!-- /preserve -->`,\n      tokenCount: 100,\n    });\n\n    // Get messages before compaction\n    const messagesBefore = await engine.getConversationStore().getMessages(\n      conversation!.conversationId,\n    );\n    expect(messagesBefore.length).toBeGreaterThan(10);\n\n    // Try to compact - the preserve-tagged message should be skipped\n    const result = await engine.compact({\n      sessionId,\n      sessionFile: \"/tmp/test-session.jsonl\",\n      tokenBudget: 1000, // Low budget to trigger compaction\n      force: true,\n    });\n\n    // Verify the preserve-tagged message is still in the database\n    const messagesAfter = await engine.getConversationStore().getMessages(\n      conversation!.conversationId,\n    );\n    const preserveMessages = messagesAfter.filter((m) =>\n      m.content.includes(\"<!-- preserve -->\"),\n    );\n    expect(preserveMessages.length).toBe(1);\n    expect(preserveMessages[0].content).toContain(\"Identity content that should not be compacted\");\n  });\n});\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773547478282}}
{"type":"message","id":"5fe31081","parentId":"328b7937","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:05:27.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good! The test verifies that:\n1. Preserve-tagged messages are not compacted away\n2. They remain in the database after compaction\n\nBut the earlier test shows that preserve-tagged content is **skipped during ingest**. So the compaction test directly inserts the message into the database to simulate old data.\n\nThe question is: what's the intended behavior?\n\nLooking at the tests:\n1. **Ingest**: Skip preserve-tagged content (not ingested into database)\n2. **Compaction**: If preserve-tagged content is somehow in the database, skip compaction\n\nThis seems inconsistent. If we skip ingest, how would preserve-tagged content ever get into the database?\n\nThe answer is: it's for **backward compatibility**. Old data that was ingested before the preserve tag feature should not be compacted away.\n\nBut for new data (with preserve tags), they're skipped during ingest and never enter the database.\n\nThe key question is: **How will preserve-tagged content appear in assembled context?**\n\nLooking at the comment:\n> Content wrapped with <!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve --> should not be ingested\n> because it's re-injected fresh each turn by the host system.\n\nThis implies OpenClaw will inject the content fresh each turn, so it doesn't need to be in LCM's database.\n\nBut I need to verify this. Let me check how OpenClaw handles the assembled context and whether it injects bootstrap files.\n\nActually, I think the best way to verify this is to:\n1. Check if the current implementation works correctly\n2. If there's a bug, fix it\n\nLet me run the tests and see if they pass.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I see the tests. The behavior is:\n1. **Ingest**: Skip preserve-tagged content (not stored in database)\n2. **Compaction**: If preserve-tagged content is in the database, skip compaction\n\nThe comment says \"because it's re-injected fresh each turn by the host system\". This means OpenClaw should inject bootstrap files after LCM's assemble.\n\nLet me verify the tests pass and then check if this is the correct behavior by looking at how OpenClaw handles the assembled context:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6e7b6662bf784ec681df9dec","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw && npm test 2>&1 | grep -A 5 \"preserve\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":67298,"output":490,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67788,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547478288}}
