{"type":"message","id":"8cbc1927","parentId":"b80ce5c4","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:07:03.518Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan confirmed that the tests are correct. Let me continue with the implementation.\n\nLooking at the tests:\n- \"skips preserve-tagged content in ingest\" - PASS\n- \"skips preserve-tagged content with optional type suffix\" - PASS\n- \"ingests content without preserve tags normally\" - PASS\n- \"does not compact messages with preserve tags\" - PASS\n\nAll tests pass. The implementation is:\n1. Skip ingest for preserve-tagged content\n2. Skip compaction for preserve-tagged content (if it's in the database)\n\nThe assumption is that OpenClaw will inject bootstrap files fresh each turn, so they don't need to be in LCM's database.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Make sure the PR is ready\n2. Check if there are any other changes needed\n\nLet me check the current state of the PR.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. The implementation is correct:\n\n1. **Ingest**: Skip preserve-tagged content (not stored in database)\n2. **Compaction**: Skip compaction for preserve-tagged content (backward compatibility)\n\nThe assumption is that OpenClaw will inject bootstrap files fresh each turn after LCM's assemble.\n\nLet me check the current state of the PR and make sure everything is committed:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3e9920c735ce43eaa418ea7d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw && git status && echo \"---\" && git log --oneline -5"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":53341,"output":361,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53702,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547594935}}
