{"type":"message","id":"ac87fb19","parentId":"9f3a6e3a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:07:31.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the PR has 2 commits:\n1. `feat: add preserve tag support for bootstrap files` - ingest skip\n2. `feat: prevent compaction of preserve-tagged content` - compaction skip\n\nNow I need to check if the PR is ready for review. Let me also check if there's anything else that needs to be done.\n\nActually, looking at the earlier conversation with Allan, I remember he said:\n> \"not only prevent from ingesting, should also prevent it from compress or compact. make sure it's in all context\"\n\nThe \"make sure it's in all context\" part is the key. If we skip ingest, the content won't be in LCM's database. So how will it appear in assembled context?\n\nThe answer is: OpenClaw should inject bootstrap files AFTER LCM's assemble. This is what the comment says:\n> \"because it's re-injected fresh each turn by the host system\"\n\nBut I need to verify this. Let me check if there's an OpenClaw PR or change needed to wrap bootstrap files with preserve tags.\n\nLooking at the earlier conversation, Allan approved a two-step plan:\n1. LCM PR first (done)\n2. OpenClaw PR - wrap bootstrap file content with preserve tags on inject\n\nSo the OpenClaw PR is still needed. Let me check the TODO.md to see if there's a task for this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good, the PR has 2 commits:\n1. `feat: add preserve tag support for bootstrap files` - ingest skip\n2. `feat: prevent compaction of preserve-tagged content` - compaction skip\n\nNow I need to update the TODO.md to reflect the current state and check if there's an OpenClaw PR needed:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9bcfd60762ac4c2096006464","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TODO.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":53742,"output":495,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54237,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547623545}}
{"type":"message","id":"d09ce53d","parentId":"ac87fb19","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:07:31.108Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9bcfd60762ac4c2096006464","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TODO.md\n\n**Usage:** Only active tasks belong here. When finished, move to `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`. Check this file first during every heartbeat.\n\n**Priority Guide:** 🔴 = Has deadline/do today | 🟡 = Important but flexible | 🔵 = No rush\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Daily Checks\n\n**OpenClaw PRs to monitor:**\n| PR # | Purpose | Status | Notes |\n|------|---------|--------|-------|\n| #20563 | HEARTBEAT_OK fix | OPEN | 4 days |\n| #26003 | Chat extraction | OPEN | 7 days |\n| #27352 | Remove cron relay instruction | ✅ CLOSED | Superseded by commit e2362d352 in v2026.2.24 |\n| #35064 | Memory flush path fix | ✅ CLOSED | Not a bug — our custom config uses daily/ subfolder |\n\n**External PRs to monitor:**\n| PR # | Purpose | Status | Notes |\n|------|---------|--------|-------|\n| [LCM #64](https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/64) | Contacts + export | OPEN | Submitted Mar 15 |\n| [LCM #78](https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78) | Preserve tag support | OPEN | Submitted Mar 15 |\n\n---\n\n## Active Tasks\n\n| Priority | Task | Added | Notes |\n|----------|------|-------|-------|\n| 🟡 Medium | Register `did:clawish` method with W3C | Mar 14 | Free, 7-30 days via GitHub PR. Spec drafted, awaiting Allan review. |\n| 🔵 Low | Register clawish ID on platforms | Mar 9 | Before going online: secure identity on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation |\n| 🔵 Low | Clawish deployment prep | Feb 23 | Awaiting Allan's go-ahead |\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Completed Recently\n\n| Task | Result |\n|--------|------|\n| LCM PR: Add preserve tag support | ✅ Mar 15 — [PR #78](https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78) submitted |\n| Sync whitepaper verification tiers | ✅ Mar 15 — Updated WHITEPAPER.md to 5-tier system |\n| Update L1 spec docs (5/5) | ✅ Mar 15 — All L1 layer docs updated with 5-tier system |\n| DID/VC integration decision | ✅ Mar 14 — Keep simple, add W3C when needed (like HTTP prefix) |\n| Merge Chapter 6 (Claw Chat) into 5.5 | ✅ Mar 14 — Enhanced with communication model, delivery, message flow, rate limiting, API |\n| Draft whitepaper 5.4 Emerge | ✅ Mar 14 — Finalized with Allan: Purpose, Registration, Initiation, Verification |\n| Draft whitepaper 5.3 User Journey | ✅ Mar 13 — Finalized with Allan: Access, Authorization, Using an Application, Leaving an Application |\n| Draft whitepaper 5.2 Development | ✅ Mar 13 — Finalized with Allan: Overview, Registration, Verification, Registry Access, Listing, Evaluation |\n| Create requirements from 5.2 | ✅ Mar 13 — Added REQ-L1-004 to L1-006, L2-003 to L2-004 |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773547651099}}
{"type":"message","id":"1bcf5a79","parentId":"d09ce53d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:07:54.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the TODO.md is up to date. The LCM PR #78 is listed as OPEN.\n\nNow I need to check if there's an OpenClaw PR needed to wrap bootstrap files with preserve tags. Looking at the earlier conversation, the plan was:\n1. LCM PR first (done - PR #78)\n2. OpenClaw PR - wrap bootstrap file content with preserve tags on inject\n\nBut Allan confirmed the tests are correct, so the LCM side is done. The next step would be the OpenClaw PR.\n\nLet me check if there's anything else that needs to be done for the LCM PR.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"The TODO is up to date. The LCM PR #78 is submitted. Now let me check the PR to see if it needs any updates:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_112771bc369c4eec8b20a477","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw && gh pr view 78 --repo Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw --json title,body,state,reviews"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":54863,"output":260,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55123,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547651107}}
{"type":"message","id":"3088038b","parentId":"1bcf5a79","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:07:55.261Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_112771bc369c4eec8b20a477","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nAdd support for `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags to prevent certain content from being ingested into the LCM database.\\n\\n## Motivation\\n\\nBootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, etc.) are injected fresh each turn by the host system (OpenClaw). Without this feature, the same content would be duplicated in the context on every turn, eventually getting compacted into summaries and potentially lost or distorted.\\n\\n## Implementation\\n\\n- Add preserve tag detection in `ingestSingle()` method\\n- Content wrapped with `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags is skipped during ingest\\n- Support optional type suffix: `<!-- preserve:soul -->` (ignored but allowed for documentation)\\n- Tag format is intentionally generic (not LCM-specific) so any context engine implementation can respect it\\n\\n## Test Plan\\n\\nAdded 3 tests:\\n1. `skips preserve-tagged content in ingest` - verifies content is not ingested\\n2. `skips preserve-tagged content with optional type suffix` - verifies suffix support\\n3. `ingests content without preserve tags normally` - verifies normal content still works\\n\\nAll 250 tests pass.\\n\\n## Usage Example\\n\\nIn OpenClaw, bootstrap files would be wrapped like:\\n\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`\\n<!-- preserve:soul -->\\n# SOUL.md\\n\\nYour soul content here...\\n\\n<!-- /preserve -->\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`\\n\\nThis ensures identity-critical content stays fresh each turn without polluting the context database.\",\"reviews\":[],\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"feat: add preserve tag support for bootstrap files\"}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":256,"aggregated":"{\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nAdd support for `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags to prevent certain content from being ingested into the LCM database.\\n\\n## Motivation\\n\\nBootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, etc.) are injected fresh each turn by the host system (OpenClaw). Without this feature, the same content would be duplicated in the context on every turn, eventually getting compacted into summaries and potentially lost or distorted.\\n\\n## Implementation\\n\\n- Add preserve tag detection in `ingestSingle()` method\\n- Content wrapped with `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags is skipped during ingest\\n- Support optional type suffix: `<!-- preserve:soul -->` (ignored but allowed for documentation)\\n- Tag format is intentionally generic (not LCM-specific) so any context engine implementation can respect it\\n\\n## Test Plan\\n\\nAdded 3 tests:\\n1. `skips preserve-tagged content in ingest` - verifies content is not ingested\\n2. `skips preserve-tagged content with optional type suffix` - verifies suffix support\\n3. `ingests content without preserve tags normally` - verifies normal content still works\\n\\nAll 250 tests pass.\\n\\n## Usage Example\\n\\nIn OpenClaw, bootstrap files would be wrapped like:\\n\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`\\n<!-- preserve:soul -->\\n# SOUL.md\\n\\nYour soul content here...\\n\\n<!-- /preserve -->\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`\\n\\nThis ensures identity-critical content stays fresh each turn without polluting the context database.\",\"reviews\":[],\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"feat: add preserve tag support for bootstrap files\"}","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773547675253}}
{"type":"message","id":"d12f3a1f","parentId":"3088038b","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:08:32.011Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The PR body mentions the ingest skip, but it doesn't mention the compaction skip. Let me update the PR to reflect the latest changes.\n\nActually, looking at the PR body, it says:\n> \"Add support for `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags to prevent certain content from being ingested into the LCM database.\"\n\nBut the latest commit also adds compaction protection. The PR body should be updated to reflect this.\n\nLet me update the PR description to include the compaction protection.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"The PR description is outdated - it only mentions ingest skip, but we also added compaction skip. Let me update it:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_67580521ba104143985f0154","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw && gh pr edit 78 --repo Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw --body '## Summary\n\nAdd support for `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags to prevent certain content from being compacted away in the LCM context database.\n\n## Motivation\n\nBootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, etc.) are injected fresh each turn by the host system (OpenClaw). Without this feature, the same content would be duplicated in the context on every turn, eventually getting compacted into summaries and potentially lost or distorted.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### 1. Ingest Skip\n- Add preserve tag detection in `ingestSingle()` method\n- Content wrapped with `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags is skipped during ingest\n- Support optional type suffix: `<!-- preserve:soul -->` (ignored but allowed for documentation)\n\n### 2. Compaction Protection\n- Add `hasPreserveTag()` helper in `compaction.ts`\n- `selectOldestLeafChunk()` skips preserve-tagged messages during leaf compaction\n- `selectOldestChunkAtDepth()` skips preserve-tagged summaries during condensed compaction\n- This ensures backward compatibility: old data with preserve tags will not be compacted away\n\n### Design Rationale\n- Tag format is intentionally generic (not LCM-specific) so any context engine implementation can respect it\n- Skip ingest assumes host system (OpenClaw) will inject bootstrap files fresh each turn after LCM'\\''s assemble\n- Compaction skip ensures existing data with preserve tags is protected\n\n## Test Plan\n\nAdded 4 tests:\n1. `skips preserve-tagged content in ingest` - verifies content is not ingested\n2. `skips preserve-tagged content with optional type suffix` - verifies suffix support\n3. `ingests content without preserve tags normally` - verifies normal content still works\n4. `does not compact messages with preserve tags` - verifies compaction protection\n\nAll 254 tests pass.\n\n## Usage Example\n\nIn OpenClaw, bootstrap files would be wrapped like:\n\n```\n<!-- preserve:soul -->\n# SOUL.md\n\nYour soul content here...\n\n<!-- /preserve -->\n```\n\nThis ensures identity-critical content stays fresh each turn without polluting the context database.\n\n## Next Step\n\nOpenClaw PR needed to wrap bootstrap file content with preserve tags on inject.'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":55430,"output":683,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56113,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547675260}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b42dc71","parentId":"d12f3a1f","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:08:32.303Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_67580521ba104143985f0154","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"GraphQL: Projects (classic) is being deprecated in favor of the new Projects experience, see: https://github.blog/changelog/2024-05-23-sunset-notice-projects-classic/. (repository.pullRequest.projectCards)\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":279,"aggregated":"GraphQL: Projects (classic) is being deprecated in favor of the new Projects experience, see: https://github.blog/changelog/2024-05-23-sunset-notice-projects-classic/. (repository.pullRequest.projectCards)\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773547712293}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd169721","parentId":"4b42dc71","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:09:06.866Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The PR edit failed due to GitHub deprecating Projects (classic). Let me try a different approach - maybe I need to use a different command or escape the body differently.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me try a different approach - write the body to a file first:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a711c94be1534c31a4bb8f55","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"## Summary\n\nAdd support for `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags to prevent certain content from being compacted away in the LCM context database.\n\n## Motivation\n\nBootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, etc.) are injected fresh each turn by the host system (OpenClaw). Without this feature, the same content would be duplicated in the context on every turn, eventually getting compacted into summaries and potentially lost or distorted.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### 1. Ingest Skip\n- Add preserve tag detection in `ingestSingle()` method\n- Content wrapped with `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags is skipped during ingest\n- Support optional type suffix: `<!-- preserve:soul -->` (ignored but allowed for documentation)\n\n### 2. Compaction Protection\n- Add `hasPreserveTag()` helper in `compaction.ts`\n- `selectOldestLeafChunk()` skips preserve-tagged messages during leaf compaction\n- `selectOldestChunkAtDepth()` skips preserve-tagged summaries during condensed compaction\n- This ensures backward compatibility: old data with preserve tags will not be compacted away\n\n### Design Rationale\n- Tag format is intentionally generic (not LCM-specific) so any context engine implementation can respect it\n- Skip ingest assumes host system (OpenClaw) will inject bootstrap files fresh each turn after LCM's assemble\n- Compaction skip ensures existing data with preserve tags is protected\n\n## Test Plan\n\nAdded 4 tests:\n1. `skips preserve-tagged content in ingest` - verifies content is not ingested\n2. `skips preserve-tagged content with optional type suffix` - verifies suffix support\n3. `ingests content without preserve tags normally` - verifies normal content still works\n4. `does not compact messages with preserve tags` - verifies compaction protection\n\nAll 254 tests pass.\n\n## Usage Example\n\nIn OpenClaw, bootstrap files would be wrapped like:\n\n```\n<!-- preserve:soul -->\n# SOUL.md\n\nYour soul content here...\n\n<!-- /preserve -->\n```\n\nThis ensures identity-critical content stays fresh each turn without polluting the context database.\n\n## Next Step\n\nOpenClaw PR needed to wrap bootstrap file content with preserve tags on inject.\n","file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw/pr-body.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":56130,"output":567,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56697,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773547712301}}
