{"type":"message","id":"c21f394a","parentId":"4fbe0233","timestamp":"2026-03-15T04:32:08.669Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking me to:\n1. Acknowledge that the GitHub CLI issue is fine (just a CLI problem, not a blocker)\n2. Remove LCM from the config since it doesn't support preserve tags yet\n\nWait, but LCM is what I just added preserve tag support to! PR #78 adds preserve tag support to LCM. So the current version of LCM (0.3.0) doesn't have preserve tag support, but once PR #78 is merged and released, it will.\n\nBut Allan is saying to remove LCM from the config since it doesn't support preserve yet. This makes sense - we should wait until PR #78 is merged and a new version is released before enabling LCM.\n\nLet me:\n1. Acknowledge the GitHub CLI issue is fine\n2. Remove the LCM config from openclaw.json\n\nI need to edit the openclaw.json file to remove the LCM context engine slot configuration.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. Allan wants me to:\n1. Acknowledge the GitHub CLI issue is fine\n2. Remove LCM from the config since it doesn't support preserve tags yet (waiting for PR #78 to be merged and released)\n\nLet me remove the LCM config from openclaw.json.明白，移除 LCM 配置，等 PR #78 合并发布后再启用。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_eeee4e95ef1c419483ffbedf","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/openclaw.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":45849,"output":376,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46225,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773549109263}}
