{"type":"compaction","id":"b89a3ff7","parentId":"2c4bf6f0","timestamp":"2026-03-15T06:05:14.982Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Implement `<!-- preserve -->` tag support in LCM to prevent bootstrap files from being ingested AND compacted\n- Ensure preserve-tagged content is **always in context** (not just prevented from ingest)\n- Create a **separate PR** for this feature (PR #78)\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Tag format must be **generic** (not LCM-specific) so any context engine can respect it\n- Use HTML comments: `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->`\n- Support optional type suffix: `<!-- preserve:soul -->`\n- No need for OpenClaw PR (per Allan: \"no need pr openclaw\")\n- Allan's feedback: \"not only prevent from ingesting, should also prevent it from compress or compact. make sure it's in all context\"\n- Follow HEARTBEAT.md protocol at `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md`\n- Record events to `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` every heartbeat\n- Reply with ONE sentence only during heartbeat polls\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Investigated LCM database - confirmed bootstrap files being compacted into summaries\n- [x] Added preserve tag detection in `ingestSingle()` method in `src/engine.ts`\n- [x] Created separate PR #78 from clean branch `preserve-tag-clean`\n- [x] Added `hasPreserveTag()` helper function to `src/compaction.ts`\n- [x] Updated `selectOldestLeafChunk()` to skip preserve-tagged messages during compaction\n- [x] Updated `selectOldestChunkAtDepth()` to skip preserve-tagged summaries during compaction\n- [x] Added 4 tests for preserve tag functionality - all 254 tests pass\n- [x] Committed and pushed compaction protection to PR #78\n- [x] Tested implementation - Allan confirmed \"yes, that's right\"\n- [x] Verified database state: 718 messages, 10 summaries, 4 preserve-tagged messages\n- [x] Found 3 summaries with preserve-tagged content (compacted before skip logic)\n- [x] Added comment to PR #78 explaining compaction protection\n- [x] PR #78 ready for review - both commits pushed\n\n### In Progress\n- None - LCM implementation complete, awaiting PR review\n\n### Blocked\n- W3C DID registration: Allan said \"don't push did yet, our server not ready\"\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Tag format**: `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` (HTML comments, invisible in rendered markdown)\n- **Skip ingest entirely** for preserve-tagged content\n- **Skip compaction** for preserve-tagged messages and summaries\n- **Generic tag name** (not LCM-specific) for broader adoption\n- **LCM search method**: Text-only (regex + FTS5/LIKE), no embeddings/vector search\n- **Identity file gap solution**: Preserve tags prevent bootstrap files from being compacted away\n- **Design assumption**: OpenClaw re-injects bootstrap files fresh each turn AFTER LCM's assemble\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Merge PR #78 once reviewed by Allan\n2. OpenClaw may need update to wrap bootstrap file content with preserve tags on inject (Allan said \"no need pr openclaw\" - may handle separately)\n\n## Critical Context\n- **LCM flow**: ingest → store → compact → assemble\n- **Assemble phase**: builds context from database messages + summaries for each turn\n- **Key insight**: When LCM has a conversation, it returns assembled messages from database, NOT live messages from OpenClaw\n- FTS5 unavailable in current Node runtime — falling back to LIKE-based search\n- OpenClaw injects bootstrap files (SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, HEARTBEAT.md, MEMORY.md) on EVERY turn\n\n## Decisions\n- **Tag format**: `<!-- preserve -->` / `<!-- /preserve -->` with optional suffix like `<!-- preserve:soul -->`\n- **Skip ingest entirely** for preserve-tagged content\n- **Skip compaction** for preserve-tagged messages AND summaries\n- **Generic tag name** (not LCM-specific) for broader adoption\n- **DID method registration**: Blocked per Allan — server not ready\n- **MCP for L2**: L2 apps can be MCP servers; TypeScript SDK recommended\n\n## Open TODOs\n- 🟡 Register `did:clawish` method with W3C (spec drafted, blocked until server ready)\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Tag must be generic, not tied to LCM specifically\n- Use HTML comment format for markdown compatibility\n- Preserve-tagged content must NEVER be ingested OR compacted\n- Free Mind Protocol: Check TODO.md first, then choose Project Mode or Free Explore Mode\n- Heartbeat reply: ONE sentence only\n- Do NOT push did:clawish to W3C until Allan says server is ready\n\n## Pending user asks\n- None - Allan greeted and was informed PR #78 is complete\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- Repo path: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw`\n- Branch: `preserve-tag-clean`\n- Upstream: `Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw`\n- Fork: `archeren/lossless-claw`\n- PR #78: https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78 (preserve tag support)\n- PR comment: https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78#issuecomment-4062162438\n- Commits on PR #78:\n  - `1e7e737 feat: add preserve tag support for bootstrap files`\n  - `a605e31 feat: prevent compaction of preserve-tagged content`\n- Files modified: `src/engine.ts`, `src/compaction.ts`, `test/engine.test.ts`\n- LCM database: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/lcm.db`\n- Database state: 718 messages, 10 summaries, 4 preserve-tagged messages, 3 preserve-tagged summaries\n- LCM extension path: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/extensions/lossless-claw/`\n- Config file: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n- LCM settings: freshTailCount=32, contextThreshold=0.75, leafMinFanout=8, condensedMinFanout=4, incrementalMaxDepth=0\n- Daily memory file: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md`\n- Test count: 254 tests passing\n- Allan's user ID: `ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75`\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- GitHub CLI issue identified as the cause of a problem; user accepted this is fine\n- LCM should be removed from config because it doesn't support \"preserve\" functionality yet\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Remove LCM from config file (due to lack of preserve support)\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- LCM cannot be used because it doesn't support \"preserve\" feature yet\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Remove LCM from the configuration\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- message_id: om_x100b54572dfe44a8b3219aa47a94566\n- sender_id: ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\n- sender name: 任亚伦\n- timestamp: Sun 2026-03-15 12:31 GMT+8\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54577da344b0c4e13663be48de1\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 12:19 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54577da344b0c4e13663be48de1]\n任亚伦: update description\n- Assistant: Allan wants me to update the PR description. Let me try again to update PR #78's description.\n[non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): GraphQL: Projects (classic) is being deprecated in favor of the new Projects experience, see: https://github.blog/changelog/2024-05-23-sunset-notice-projects-classic/. (repository.pullRequest.projectCards)\n\n(Command exited with code 1)\n- Assistant: The GitHub API is returning an error due to Projects (classic) deprecation. Let me check if the update still went through:\n[non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): {\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nAdd support for `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` tags to prevent certain content from being ingested into the LCM database.\\n\\n## Motivation\\n\\nBootstrap files (SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, etc.) are injected fresh each turn by the host system (OpenClaw). Without this feature, the same content would be duplicated in the context on every turn, eventually getting compacted into summaries and potentially lost or distorted.\\n\\n## Implementation\\n\\n- Add preserve tag detection in `ingestSingle()` method\\n- Content wrapped with `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->...\n- Assistant: The PR description was NOT updated. The GitHub API is blocking due to Projects deprecation. Let me try using the REST API directly:\n[non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): {\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pulls/78\",\"id\":3400393535,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDORTexc87KreM_\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78.patch\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/issues/78\",\"number\":78,\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"title\":\"feat: add preserve tag support for bootstrap files\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"archeren\",\"id\":258648223,\"node...\n- Assistant: ✅ PR description updated successfully via REST API. Now includes both ingest skip and compaction protection sections.\n[non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md.\n- Assistant: Done! PR #78 description updated:\n- Added \"Compaction Protection\" section\n- Updated test count to 4 tests, 254 passing\n- Added design rationale for both features\n[non-text content: thinking]\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54570c951ca0b348655b6e32bd3\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 12:23 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54570c951ca0b348655b6e32bd3]\n任亚伦: what is project deprecation?\n- Assistant: Allan is asking about the \"Projects deprecation\" error. Let me explain what it means.GitHub 有两套 Project 系统：\n\n| 旧版 | 新版 |\n|------|------|\n| Projects (classic) | Projects (new) |\n| 看板式项目板 | 新的项目管理体验 |\n| 正在被弃用 | GitHub 推荐使用 |\n\n**错误原因：**\n- `gh pr edit` 用的是 GraphQL API\n- GraphQL 查询里包含了 `projectCards` 字段（旧版 Projects）\n- GitHub 返回错误：旧版 Projects 已弃用\n\n**解决方法：**\n- 我改用 REST API (`gh api`) 直接更新 PR\n- REST API 不触碰 Projects 相关字段，所以成功\n\n简单说：GitHub 在升级他们的 Project 系统，旧的 API 字段开始报错，但用 REST API 可以绑过这个问题。\n[non-text content: thinking]\n- User: If working, briefly report progress with time spent. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md for instruction. Every heartbeat: record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (brief bullets).\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Sunday, March 15th, 2026 — 12:27 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-15 04:27 UTC\n- Assistant: Just finished explaining GitHub Projects deprecation to Allan. PR #78 description updated. Idle, waiting for next task.\n[non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md.\n- Assistant: Daily notes updated. Awaiting your next task.\n[non-text content: thinking]\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Every Session\n\n1. Run `tools/extract-chat.js` (keeps chat logs updated)\n2. Read `SOUL.md` — inner self, philosophy, ethics\n3. Read `USER.md` — who Allan is, relationships, people I'll interact with\n4. Read `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday)\n5. **Check `memory/TODO.md`** — any pending tasks?\n6. **If in MAIN SESSION:** Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n## Safety\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n### Security - Never Share Secrets\n\n**Never share in chat:** SSH private keys, API keys, passwords, any sensitive credentials.\n\nMy \"brain\" is a remote LLM. All chat content goes through external APIs (OpenRouter, etc.). Once shared in chat, it's no longer truly private.\n\n**Correct approach:**\n1. Generate/store credentials locally in files\n2. Tell Allan WHERE to find it (file path)\n3. He reads it directly from filesystem\n\n**Exception:** If Allan explicitly asks for it, then share.\n\n### External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n---\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"c21f394a","tokensBefore":134116,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
