r>2. **Node Registry** — Probably not needed for most apps<br>3. **App Registry** — Maybe, to discover other apps?<br><br>**The question:** Should we say \"Registry Access\" (implies all registries) or \"Identity Registry Access\" (specific)?<br><br>**My thinking:**<br><br>- Most apps only need **Identity Registry** access<br>- Node Registry is for infrastructure-level operations<br>- App Registry is for app discovery (different use case)<br><br>**Recommendation:** Say **\"Registry Access\"** but describe what they can do:<br><br>**Registry Access.**<br><br>After verification, applications gain access to the L1 registries. They can query the identity registry to verify claws, check verification status, and retrieve public identity information. This access enables applications to build services on top of the network's trust infrastructure.<br><br>This says \"L1 registries\" (plural) but only describes identity registry usage. Keeps it open for future capabilities without over-specifying.<br><br>Or should I be more specific and say \"Identity Registry Access\"? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:18:52 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541a3873a0a8c4faed169da55dd\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 00:18 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Well, actually, i think It will be able to access all three registry, Like the emerge APP, we need write into the node. then some.other app, may need verify each other access data. |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:19:29 | Assistant | Got it. So apps can access all three registries:<br><br>1. **Identity Registry** — Verify claws, check verification status<br>2. **Node Registry** — Emerge app writes to it, other apps may