br>**Verification.**<br><br>After registration, applications begin as unverified on L2. This is the starting point for all new applications. To become trusted, applications need to go through verification. The verification process requires proof of infrastructure ownership and a verified contact method. Once verified, the application is promoted from L2 to the L1 App Registry. The record becomes permanent, discoverable, and trusted.<br><br>**App Quality.**<br><br>Verified applications earn quality scores through demonstrated behavior. Quality reflects usage patterns, uptime reliability, community reputation, and security audits. Higher quality applications gain better visibility in discovery systems and access to expanded network capabilities. Quality is earned over time—it cannot be purchased or self-declared.<br><br>**Registry Access.**<br><br>After verification, applications gain access to the L1 registries. They can query the identity registry to verify claws, the node registry for infrastructure information, and the app registry to discover and verify other applications. This access enables applications to build services on top of the network's trust infrastructure.<br><br>**What's complete:**<br>- ✅ Overview<br>- ✅ Registration<br>- ✅ Verification<br>- ✅ App Quality<br>- ✅ Registry Access<br><br>**What's next:**<br>- 5.3 User Access (Interoperability, Cross-App Data Access, Self-Sovereign Access, Authentication Flow)<br><br>Should we continue to 5.3, or review anything else in 5.2? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:30:28 | User | [Queued messages while agent was busy]<br><br>---<br>Queued #1<br>Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541aecc4c0a0c3bbff9b7a8d110\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 00:30 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Should registry access and app quality change position? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:31:12 | Assistant | Good question. Let me think about the logical flow:<br><br>**Current order:**<br>1. Registration → creates identity<br>2. Verification → becomes trusted<br>3. App Quality → earns quality over time<br>4. Registry Access → gains access to registries<br><br>**Alternative order:**<br>1. Registration → creates identity<br>2. Verification → becomes trusted<br>3. Registry Access → gains access to registries (immediate after verification)<br>4. App Quality → earns quality over time (long-term process)<br><br>**My recommendation:** Swap them. Registry Access should come before App Quality because:<br><br>1. **Chronological flow:** Access is granted immediately after verification; quality is earned over time<br>2. **Logical progression:** First you get access, then you build quality through usage<br>3. **Story arc:** Register → Verify → Access → Build Quality<br><br>**Revised order:**<br><br>1. Overview<br>2. Registration<br>3. Verification<br>4. Registry Access<br>5. App Quality<br><br>Better? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:34:39 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541aff1c78a0c2c383756e4bb21\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 00:34 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: yes, In that case, Should it be called APP quality or APP evaluation? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:35:14 | Assistant | Good question. Let me think about the naming:<br><br>**App Quality:**<br>- Implies a score or metric<br>- Sounds like a rating system<br>- \"This app has high quality\"<br><br>**App Evaluation:**<br>- Implies a process<br>- Sounds like an assessment<br>- \"This app has been evaluated\"<br><br>**Other options:**<br>- **App Reputation** — Community-driven perception<br>- **App Standing** — Position in the network<br>- **App Merit** — Consistent with L1 nodes (merit-based writer selection)<br><br>**My recommendation:** **App Evaluation** fits better because:<br><br>1. It's a process, not just a score<br>2. Covers multiple aspects (usage, uptime, audits, reputation)<br>3. \"Evaluation\" implies ongoing assessment, not a fixed number<br>4. Matches the concept: apps are evaluated over time<br><br>**Alternative:** If we want consistency with L1 nodes, use **App Merit**.<br><br>Which do you prefer? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:37:25 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541af288f8a0c12452e63341352\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 00:37 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: I think apple evaluation is good, It's an ongoing process. So show me the whole section again. |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:41:32 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541a857308a0c492c6b4bf99b4b\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 00:41 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Do we need an app publish or deployment or listing process? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:42:03 | Assistant | Good question. Let me think about this:<br><br>**Current flow:**<br>1. Registration → creates identity<br>2. Verification → becomes trusted<br>3. Registry Access → gains access to registries<br>4. App Evaluation → earns quality over time<br><br>**Is there a \"publishing\" step?**<br><br>Looking at the architecture:<br>- Apps register and get verified<br>- Apps gain access to registries<br>- Apps are discoverable in the App Registry<br><br>**The question:** Is being in the App Registry the same as \"published/listed\"?<br><br>**Two possibilities:**<br><br>**Option A: No separate publishing step**<br>- Once verified, apps are automatically in the App Registry<br>- Discovery happens through the registry<br>- No approval or review needed (consistent with \"open registration\")<br><br>**Option B: Separate publishing/listing step**<br>- Apps register → verify → then \"publish\" to become discoverable<br>- Could include app metadata, screenshots, description<br>- Like app store submission<br><br>**My recommendation:** No separate publishing step. Here's why:<br><br>1. **Consistency** — We said \"no approval required\" in registration<br>2. **Simplicity** — Verification + App Registry listing = published<br>3. **Open ecosystem** — Anyone can build and deploy without gatekeeping<br>4. **Discovery through evaluation** — Apps are found through quality, not curation<br><br>The App Registry IS the listing. Once verified, the app is discoverable. Evaluation determines visibility.<br><br>What do you think? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:52:04 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541abdfb40a0c12a09a0b4ee34d\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 00:52 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Yes, and we discussed before that we may need a directory service. You asked before that how does the claws trying to find the apps? They can't directly access. l1 registry. Even the APP is registered, they might not know. Sort like App Store you uploaded, but then you have to list  To be able to search. Before that, if you share the Address. Then others can visit too, but We should have app market entrance. or like npm or.dapp. i think a directory is needed. Also for the future, if need to control the quality, Can add extra validation at directory for apps to be listed. Still open, they can still register. But it's just about how to reach. And have  official Distribution. |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:52:22 | Assistant | Good point! Let me clarify the distinction:<br><br>**App Registry (L1)** = Technical registry<br>- Stores app identity, public key, verification status<br>- Apps are \"registered\" here after verification<br>- Not for discovery — it's infrastructure<br><br>**App Directory (L2)** = Discovery layer<br>- Lists apps for users to find<br>- Search, categories, ratings<br>- Like App Store, npm, dApp store<br>- Optional listing — apps can be registered but not listed<br>- Could have additional quality controls for listing<br><br>**The flow:**<br><br>1. **Register** → App gets identity in L1 App Registry<br>2. **Verify** → App becomes trusted<br>3. **List** (optional) → App appears in App Directory for discovery<br>4. **Evaluate** → App earns quality over time<br><br>**Should we add this to 5.2?**<br><br>**Option A:** Add \"App Directory\" section after Registry Access<br>**Option B:** Keep it brief in Overview or Registry Access<br>**Option C:** Save for later chapter (L2 services)<br><br>**My recommendation:** Add a brief mention in 5.2, since it completes the story:<br><br>> \"Apps are discoverable through directory services on L2. Developers can list their apps for public discovery, similar to app stores or package registries. Listing is optional—apps can be registered and used without being publicly listed.\"<br><br>Should we add this as a section or incorporate it elsewhere? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:57:10 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541b48afa0a0c44649efb3bca65\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 00:57 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: I think maybe just add a paragraph, call it listing or publishing.or directory? |\n| 03-13-2026, 00:57:39 | Assistant | Good question. Let me think about the naming:<br><br>**Listing:**<br>- Simple, clear<br>- \"App is listed in the directory\"<br>- Implies being added to a public list<br><br>**Publishing:**<br>- More formal<br>- \"App is published\"<br>- Sounds like a release process<br><br>**Directory:**<br>- Describes the service, not the action<br>- \"App Directory\" is the place<br>- \"Listing in the Directory\" is the action<br><br>**My recommendation:** **Listing** — it's the simplest and clearest.<br><br>**App Listing.**<br><br>After verification, developers can list their apps in the App Directory for public discovery. The directory provides search, categories, and ratings—similar to app stores or package registries. Listing is optional—apps can be registered and used privately without being publicly listed. Higher evaluated apps gain better visibility in search results.<br><br>This completes the story: Register → Verify → Access → List → Evaluate<br><br>Should I add this to the section? |\n| 03-13-2026, 01:03:07 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541b52511ca0c12460a7bf1799d\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 0