r>**Whitepaper Chapter 5 Drafting**<br>- Worked with Allan throughout afternoon/evening on Section 5.2 Development<br>- Finalized complete structure: Overview → Registration → Verification → Registry Access → Listing → Evaluation<br>- Created WHITEPAPER-CH5-ENHANCEMENT.md with draft enhancements<br><br>**Requirements Update**<br>- Created 5 new requirements based on whitepaper 5.2:<br>  - REQ-L1-004: Application Registration<br>  - REQ-L1-005: Application Verification<br>  - REQ-L1-006: Application Registry Access<br>  - REQ-L2-003: App Directory Listing<br>  - REQ-L2-004: Application Evaluation System<br>- Updated requirements/README.md with summary table<br>- **Total: 12 requirements** (8 MVP, 4 Phase 2)<br><br>**Research & Exploration**<br>- Checked OpenClaw PRs: #20563 (HEARTBEAT_OK fix) still open, marked stale<br>- Explored Hacker News:<br>  - **Klaus** (klausai.com): Hosted OpenClaw on EC2 with AI SRE — relevant for L2 app hosting<br>  - **BitNet** (Microsoft): 1.58-bit LLMs running on CPU — relevant for local claw inference<br><br>## 2️⃣ Important Learnings & Insights<br><br>**Writing for Whitepaper Audience**<br>- Narrative prose, not bullet lists<br>- Explain WHY before HOW<br>- No implementation details (no API names, field names, algorithms)<br>- Start with purpose, not connection<br>- Discuss before writing<br><br>**App vs Identity Terminology**<br>- Identities have tiers (Tier 0-3)<br>- Apps have verification (binary) + evaluation (ongoing)<br>- Different concepts, different terminology — avoids confusion<br><br>**Architecture Clarification**<br>- App Directory is L2 (discovery), not L1 (registry)<br>- L1 = technical infrastructure<br>- L2 = user-facing discovery<br><br>## 3️⃣ Project Progress<br><br>\\ |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:02:13 | Assistant | Daily report sent to Allan via Feishu. The report covered:<br><br>1. **Key Activities**: Whitepaper Ch5 drafting (5.2 Development finalized), requirements update (5 new requirements, 12 total), research on Hacker 