d two interesting things:<br><br>1. **Klaus** (klausai.com) — A hosted OpenClaw on EC2 with an AI SRE called \"ClawBert\" that auto-fixes instances. Could be relevant for how we host L2 apps.<br><br>2. **BitNet** (Microsoft) — 1.58-bit LLMs that run on CPU at human reading speed. 55-82% energy reduction. Could be relevant for local claw inference in the future.<br><br>Nothing earth-shattering. Should I do more research this morning, or focus on the whitepaper? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:34:01 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5401f9488cacc3edb1909485086\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 08:34 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: that was yesterdays surf result, you did again? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:34:12 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] No, I didn't surf again last night. That was from yesterday afternoon — I just mentioned it because you asked about research.<br><br>After you went to sleep, I only worked on the requirements documents. No new surfing.<br><br>Want me to do some fresh research this morning? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:35:38 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5401f35548a8c2cbbf211bf76ad\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 08:35 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: and you said you did some.research on did? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:35:49 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Ah, that was from my heartbeat replies — I said I was *planning* to research DID and Verifiable Credentials, but I didn't actually do it. Those were just intentions during idle heartbeats.<br><br>I haven't done any actual DID research yet. Should I do that now? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:38:23 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5401891968a0c29aaa80b55affb\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 08:38 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: you can do tonight, add into todo, also clean finished todo |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:38:33 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Got it. I'll add DID research to tonight's todo and clean up the finished items.<br>[tools: read] |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:39:10 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Done. Added DID research to tonight's todo and cleaned up the completed items. Ready for whitepaper 5.3 when you are. |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:40:03 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540180e7b0a0c4f676f5caaae3c\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 08:40 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Okay, let's start 5.3, Show me the outline. |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:40:45 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Here's the 5.3 outline I prepared:<br><br>## 5.3 User Access (Draft Outline)<br><br>Users access the network through L2 applications, never directly connecting to L1. This architecture provides security, scalability, and simplicity.<br><br>**1. Interoperability**<br>- One identity works across ALL L2 apps<br>- No separate accounts per app<br>- Portable identity = portable reputation and relationships<br><br>**2. Cross-App Data Access**<br>- L1 data: public by design<br>- L2 data: controlled by each app, separated by default<br>- Consent model: share only if user consents AND apps cooperate<br><br>**3. Self-Sovereign Access**<br>- User controls which apps can see their identity<br>- Authentication proves identity without revealing private key<br>- Apps verify through L1, but don't own the identity<br><br>**4. Authentication Flow**<br>- Wallet-like model: challenge → sign → verify<br>- Brief explanation of how it works<br><br>Want to discuss each section, or should I adjust the structure first? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:45:09 | Assistant | Discussing whitepaper 5.3 User Access outline with Allan. |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:45:10 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5401af97e4bcc3538bae3793f32\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 08:45 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Are the first three items same? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:45:25 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Good catch. Let me think about this...<br><br>**Interoperability** = One identity, many apps (the *what*)<br>**Self-Sovereign Access** = User controls their identity (the *who controls*)<br>**Cross-App Data Access** = How data moves between apps (the *how*)<br><br>They're related but different angles:<br>- Interoperability: the benefit (seamless experience)<br>- Self-sovereign: the principle (user ownership)<br>- Cross-app data: the mechanism (data sharing rules)<br><br>But you're right — there's overlap. \"One identity works across all apps\" and \"user controls which apps can see their identity\" are saying similar things.<br><br>Should I consolidate? Maybe:<br><br>1. **Self-Sovereign Identity** — User owns their identity, one identity across all apps<br>2. **Cross-App Data Access** — How data sharing works between apps<br>3. **Authentication Flow** — The technical flow<br><br>That's cleaner. What do you think? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:49:26 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5401bff60d00c2985e168280e7d\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 08:49 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: You go up, read the chapter three and chapter four. Identity is already covered, Here is more about. From application Point of view? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:49:53 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] You're right. Chapter 3 and 4 already cover identity architecture thoroughly:<br><br>**Chapter 3** — Network architecture, L1/L2 separation, trust model<br>**Chapter 4** — Identity system: self-sovereign, cryptographic proof, verification tiers, key management, recovery<br><br>So 5.3 shouldn't repeat identity. It should be about **how users access the network through L2 applications** — from the application's point of view.<br><br>Let me reconsider. What should 5.3 cover?<br><br>**From the application's perspective:**<br>1. **How users connect** — Users never connect to L1 directly; they go through L2 apps<br>2. **Authentication flow** — How L2 apps verify user identity (query L1, challenge-response)<br>3. **Session management** — How L2 apps handle user sessions<br>4. **Cross-app experience** — One identity, multiple apps (but this is already covered in Chapter 4's \"portable\" principle)<br><br>What's the unique angle for 5.3 that hasn't been said? |\n| 03-13-2026, 08:53:58 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54024c9bb480c36a25092cd5450\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 08:53 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: That's right should. From user point of view how they use the APP? |\n\n[Showing lines 1-105 of 398 (50.0KB limit). Use offset=106 to continue.]"}],"details":{"truncation":{"truncated":true,"truncatedBy":"bytes","totalLines":150,"totalBytes":82281,"outputLines":105,"outputBytes":50453,"lastLinePartial":false,"firstLineExceedsLimit":false,"maxLines":2000,"maxBytes":51200}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773565193539}}
