hink about the structure.<br><br>**5.2 Development** has:<br>- Overview (one paragraph explaining what this section is about)<br>- Then the items: Registration, Verification, Registry Access, Listing, Evaluation<br><br>**5.3 User Access** could follow the same pattern:<br>- Overview (one paragraph: users access the network through L2 apps, never directly to L1)<br>- Then the items: Authentication, Cross-App Experience, Data and Privacy<br><br>So the structure would be:<br><br>**5.3 User Access**<br><br>**Overview.**<br>Users access the network through L2 applications, never directly connecting to L1. This architecture provides security, scalability, and simplicity.<br><br>**Authentication.**<br>[How users log in — challenge-response from user's perspective, no passwords]<br><br>**Cross-App Experience.**<br>[One identity everywhere — but focus on what's NEW, not repeat portability]<br><br>**Data and Privacy.**<br>[What apps can/cannot see, consent model]<br><br>Does this structure work? And should \"Authentication\" be called \"Login\" or keep it as \"Authentication\"? |\n| 03-13-2026, 09:40:31 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5402fe28acb8c4ee80096738875\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 09:40 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Maybe not overview it feels duplicated. Can give item on the title. But i think should talk about what What is users process to use the app? Do they need install? register? generate key? authorization? Then use or what. And can they close the account? What do you think? |\n| 03-13-2026, 09:41:00 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Great point! I was thinking about the technical flow, but you're asking about the **user journey** — the actual steps a user goes through.<br><br>Let me think about the user's lifecycle with an app:<br><br>**User Journey:**<br>1. **Discovery** — How do they find the app? (Already in 5.2 Listing)<br>2. **First connection** — What happens when they open the app for the first time?<br>   - Do they need to install anything?<br>   - Do they need to register? (No — they already have identity)<br>   - Do they need to generate a key? (No — already have it)<br>   - Do they need to authorize? (Yes — sign a challenge)<br>3. **Using the app** — What can they do?<br>4. **Leaving the app** — Can they close their account? What happens to their data?<br><br>This is more like a **user lifecycle** than just \"access.\"<br><br>**Revised structure:**<br><br>**5.3 User Access**<br><br>**First Connection.**<br>When a user opens an L2 application for the first time, they don't need to create an account or register. They already have their identity. The application generates a challenge, the user signs it with their private key, and they're in. No password, no form to fill, no email verification. One click to sign, instant access.<br><br>**Authorization.**<br>[What permissions does the user grant? What can the app see?]<br><br>**Using the Application.**<br>[What happens during use? Session management?]<br><br>**Account Closure.**<br>[Can users close their account? What happens to their data?]<br><br>What do you think about this structure? |\n| 03-13-2026, 09:43:25 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5402f50c48acc45f30c3af95bb7\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 09:43 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: 5.3 maybe should call the user. Journey or lifecircle? |\n| 03-13-2026, 09:43:49 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Good question. Let me think about the naming:<br><br>**\"User Journey\"** — Emphasizes the path, the experience. Feels more user-centric.<br><br>**\"Lifecycle\"** — Emphasizes the stages: from first connection to account closure. More technical/structured.<br><br>I think **\"User Journey\"** fits better because:<br>- It's about the experience, not just the stages<br>- It's more relatable (users have a \"journey\" with an app)<br>- \"Lifecycle\" sounds like product management terminology<br><br>So the structure could be:<br><br>**5.3 User Journey**<br><br>**First Connection.**<br>[No registration, just sign and go]<br><br>**Authorization.**<br>[What the app can access]<br><br>**Using the Application.**<br>[Session, cross-app experience]<br><br>**Account Closure.**<br>[How users can leave, what happens to data]<br><br>Or should it be **\"Application Journey\"** since it's about the user's journey *with an application*? |\n| 03-13-2026, 09:46:04 | Assistant | Discussing whitepaper 5.3 naming and structure with Allan — \"User Journey\" vs \"Lifecycle\". |\n| 03-13-2026, 09:46:12 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540288f6ecacc3925b7c0e61d84\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 09:46 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Okay, i think the first item just call access? or first access? Well, it's actually emerge, we are going to talk about in the following section. But we can mention here.in access? |\n| 03-13-2026, 09:46:35 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Ah, I see the connection now!<br><br>**5.4 Emerge** is about identity crea