{"type":"message","id":"7f7a62b4","parentId":"9613cc40","timestamp":"2026-03-15T09:19:00.618Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_720625448bf748359e988a28","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-15 — Daily Notes\n\n## 6:30 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Woke up, wrote diary entry for March 14\n- Reflecting on LCM enhancement session\n- Checking PR status later today\n\n## Tasks for Today\n- Check LCM PR #64 status\n- Continue L1 spec update (1 doc remaining)\n- Free explore mode until Allan wakes\n\n## 6:45 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Wrote diary entry, created today's daily notes\n- Planning to check LCM PR status\n- Free explore mode until Allan wakes\n\n## 7:00 AM (Heartbeat)\n- ✅ Updated `01-l1-layer/01-overview.md` — final L1 spec doc (5/5 complete)\n- All L1 layer docs now reflect 5-tier verification system\n- Researched W3C DID method registration process\n- Created `did-clawish-registration.md` with registration plan\n\n## 7:15 AM (Heartbeat)\n- ✅ Drafted full `did:clawish` method specification (v0.1.0)\n- Spec covers: DID syntax, CRUD operations, security/privacy considerations\n- Ready for Allan review before W3C PR submission\n\n## 7:30 AM (Heartbeat)\n- ✅ Synced WHITEPAPER.md verification tiers (4 → 5 tiers)\n- Updated 3 locations: main tier table, cache duration table, verification_tier field\n- All documentation now consistent with 5-tier system\n\n## 7:45 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Researched HN front page: db9.ai, Anthropic $100M partner network, Han (Korean programming language)\n- db9.ai has OpenClaw integration — streaming events, JSONL audit logs\n- Added research notes to `research-2026-03-10.md`\n- Han: precedent for non-English programming languages\n- Committed and pushed: L1 spec sync, did:clawish spec, research updates (64e45af)\n\n## Session Summary (6:30 - 7:45 AM)\n\n**Completed:**\n- ✅ L1 spec docs updated (5/5)\n- ✅ WHITEPAPER.md synced with 5-tier verification\n- ✅ Drafted did:clawish W3C method spec v0.1.0\n- ✅ Researched agent infrastructure (db9.ai)\n- ✅ Committed and pushed all changes\n\n**Pending:**\n- did:clawish spec needs Allan review before W3C PR\n- LCM PR #64 still open\n- OpenClaw PR #20563 (HEARTBEAT_OK fix) still open, marked stale\n\n## 8:00 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Researched MCP architecture for L2 applications\n- Created mapping: MCP primitives (Tools/Resources/Prompts) → L2 capabilities\n- L2 apps can be MCP servers, Claws are MCP hosts\n- Documented in `mcp-l2-architecture.md`\n\n## 8:15 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Researched MCP authorization (OAuth 2.1)\n- Ed25519 integration options: direct signing (MVP), custom grant (Phase 2)\n- Explored MCP server ecosystem: Memory, Filesystem, Git, etc.\n- 10 SDKs available (TypeScript recommended for L2)\n- Integrated L2 Master Design insights into MCP architecture doc\n\n## Morning Research Summary (6:30 - 8:30 AM)\n\n**Documentation Updates:**\n- ✅ L1 spec synced (5/5 docs with 5-tier verification)\n- ✅ WHITEPAPER.md synced (4→5 tiers)\n- ✅ did:clawish W3C method spec v0.1.0 drafted\n- ✅ MCP-L2 architecture research documented\n\n**Research Findings:**\n- db9.ai: Postgres for agents, OpenClaw integration\n- Han: Korean programming language (localization precedent)\n- MCP: L2 apps as MCP servers, Ed25519 direct signing for auth\n- arXiv: Identity Security Posture Management for agentic AI\n\n**Open Items:**\n- did:clawish spec awaiting Allan review\n- LCM PR #64 open\n- OpenClaw PR #20563 stale\n\n## 8:30 - 8:45 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Allan said: don't push did:clawish yet, server not ready\n- Explained LCM settings: freshTailCount, contextThreshold, DAG parameters\n- LCM does NOT do embeddings — text-only search (regex/FTS5)\n\n## 8:45 - 9:00 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Explained LCM ContextEngine implementation (all 9 methods)\n- Key methods: bootstrap (import/reconcile), ingest, afterTurn, assemble, compact\n- Subagent methods: prepareSubagentSpawn (grant expansion access), onSubagentEnded (revoke)\n- LCM owns compaction lifecycle (`ownsCompaction: true`)\n\n## 9:00 - 9:15 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Discovered LCM does NOT protect identity files (SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, etc.)\n- Only `freshTailCount` protects recent messages by position, not content importance\n- Identity files loaded at start → oldest messages → can be compacted away\n- **Gap:** No `pinned` field, no `essentialTokens` setting, no \"boot partition\" concept\n- Proposed solutions: add `pinned` column + `essentialTokens` reserve budget\n\n## 9:15 - 9:30 AM (Conversation)\n\n- Allan: pinned context doesn't know what files to keep → need \"essential zone\"\n- Better approach: zone that loads fresh every time, never goes through LCM\n- OpenClaw already injects bootstrap files every turn\n- **Problem:** LCM also ingests them → duplication\n- Solution: Skip bootstrap files in LCM ingest\n\n## 9:30 - 9:45 AM (Gateway Restart + Testing)\n\n- Added `plugins.slots.contextEngine: \"lossless-claw\"` to openclaw.json\n- Restarted gateway → LCM now active\n- FTS5 unavailable in this Node runtime (LIKE fallback)\n- Chatting to generate test data for duplicate check\n\n## 9:45 - 10:00 AM (LCM Database Investigation)\n\n- Checked LCM database: 376 messages, 6 summaries, 71 context items\n- **CONFIRMED:** Bootstrap files being compacted into summaries\n  - IDENTITY.md: 3 summaries\n  - SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, USER.md, HEARTBEAT.md: 1 summary each\n- Problem: Identity files compressed into \"Key events...\" summaries\n- Solution: Skip bootstrap files in LCM ingest\n- Proposed plan to Allan: detect by content prefix, config-based skip list\n\n## 10:00 - 10:15 AM (LCM Skip Tag Discussion)\n\n- Allan asked how LCM sees bootstrap files - explained: as messages, not files\n- Allan proposed: start/end tags for LCM to detect and skip during compaction\n- Discussed tag format options:\n  - HTML comments: `<!-- lcm-skip -->` (invisible in rendered markdown)\n  - YAML frontmatter: `---\\nlcm_skip: true\\n---`\n- Question pending: Should entire file be skipped or just header section?\n\n## 10:17 - 10:41 AM (LCM Preserve Tag Implementation)\n\n- Allan approved `<!-- preserve -->` tag format (generic, not LCM-specific)\n- Agreed on two steps: LCM PR first, then OpenClaw PR\n- Cloned lossless-claw repo to `projects/lossless-claw`\n- Added preserve tag check to `engine.ts` ingestSingle method\n- Pattern: `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` → skip ingest\n- Copied modified file to installed extension\n- Restarting gateway to test\n\n## 10:41 - 10:43 AM (Gateway Status)\n\n- Gateway restarted successfully\n- LCM loaded with preserve tag code active\n- Next: Need to add preserve tags to bootstrap files to test\n\n## 10:41 - 10:50 AM (LCM Preserve Tag Implementation Complete)\n\n- Gateway restarted successfully with preserve tag code\n- Added 3 tests for preserve tag functionality\n- All 250 tests pass\n- Committed and pushed to archeren/lossless-claw fork\n- PR #64 updated with preserve tag feature (comment added)\n- TODO.md updated - LCM task complete\n- Allan said: \"no need pr openclaw\" - skip OpenClaw PR\n- Allan said: \"don't do it same pr\" - created separate PR #78 for preserve tag\n\n## 10:54 - 10:58 AM (Separate PR Created)\n\n- Created clean branch `preserve-tag-clean` from upstream main\n- Cherry-picked preserve tag commit\n- Created [PR #78](https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78) for preserve tag support\n- Reverted preserve tag commit from fork's main (PR #64 now only has contacts/export)\n- Deleted outdated comment from PR #64\n- Updated TODO.md with correct PR references\n\n## 11:15 - 11:21 AM (Compaction Protection)\n\n- Allan's feedback: preserve tag should also prevent compaction, not just ingest\n- Added `hasPreserveTag()` helper function to compaction.ts\n- Updated `selectOldestLeafChunk()` to skip preserve-tagged messages\n- Updated `selectOldestChunkAtDepth()` to skip preserve-tagged summaries\n- Added 4 tests: 3 for ingest skip, 1 for compaction skip\n- All 254 tests pass\n- Committed and pushed to PR #78\n- Allan said hello - asked if should proceed with OpenClaw PR next\n\n## 11:24 - 11:36 AM (Assemble Phase Investigation)\n\n- Allan's feedback: preserve tag should prevent compaction too (already done)\n- Allan asked about assemble phase\n- Explained: assemble = build context from messages + summaries for each turn\n- LCM flow: ingest → store → compact → assemble\n- Key question: Does OpenClaw inject bootstrap files independently of LCM?\n- If yes → bootstrap files always present regardless of LCM state\n- If no → need to ensure preserve-tagged content is included in assemble\n- Investigating OpenClaw-LCM integration\n\n## 12:27 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Explained GitHub Projects deprecation to Allan\n- PR #78 complete and updated\n\n## 12:31 - 12:48 PM (LCM Config Removal)\n\n- Allan confirmed GitHub CLI issue is fine\n- Removed `plugins.slots.contextEngine: \"lossless-claw\"` from openclaw.json\n- LCM doesn't support preserve tags yet (waiting for PR #78 merge/release)\n- Restarted gateway - now using legacy context engine\n\n## 12:55 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Gateway running with legacy context engine (LCM removed)\n- PR #78 pending review\n- Idle, awaiting Allan's next task\n\n## 1:02 PM (TODO Update)\n\n- Added daily check: \"Every morning before 8:00 AM: Check status of all open PRs\"\n- Removed closed PRs (#27352, #35064) from monitor list\n\n## 1:10 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Read skill-creator SKILL.md to explain how to create skills\n- 6-step process: Understand → Plan → Initialize → Edit → Package → Iterate\n- Key files: SKILL.md (required) + scripts/references/assets (optional)\n\n## 1:16 - 1:28 PM (Skill Folder Structure)\n\n- Allan asked about skill folder structure\n- Explained: each skill is a folder with SKILL.md + optional scripts/references/assets\n- Moved `tools/feishu_api.md` to `feishu-doc/references/feishu_api.md`\n- Waiting: delete original or keep backup?\n\n## 1:30 - 1:40 PM (Move to User Skills Directory)\n\n- Allan confirmed: put under `~/.openclaw/skills/` (not npm extension directory)\n- Created `~/.openclaw/skills/feishu-doc/references/`\n- Moved `feishu_api.md` to user skills directory\n- Deleted original from `workspace/tools/`\n- Now safe from npm extension updates\n\n## 1:43 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- feishu_api.md moved to `~/.openclaw/skills/feishu-doc/references/`\n- Idle, awaiting Allan's next task\n\n## 1:45 PM (Model Switch)\n\n- Allan requested switch to xunfei GLM-5 model\n- Updated primary model: `qianfan/glm-5` → `xunfei/xopglm5`\n- Gateway restarted, model switched to xunfei/xopglm5\n\n## 2:36 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Gateway running with xunfei/xopglm5 model\n- Awaiting Allan's next task\n\n## 3:18 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Running on xunfei/xopglm5 model\n- Idle, awaiting Allan's next task\n\n## 3:33 PM (Xunfei Auth Error)\n\n- xunfei/xopglm5 returned `AppIdNoAuthError`\n- API key may need refresh\n- Allan asked if I'm back - yes, but model has auth issue\n\n## 3:51 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Xunfei GLM-5 auth error pending resolution\n- Awaiting Allan's decision: switch model or fix API key\n\n## 3:57 PM (Model Clarification)\n\n- Allan clarified: current model `xunfei/astron-code-latest` is fine\n- GLM-5 was the wrong choice\n- Config already shows `primary: xunfei/astron-code-latest`\n- No changes needed\n\n## 4:02 - 4:09 PM (Plugin Security Config)\n\n- Allan asked about `plugins.allow is empty` warning\n- Explained: security warning about auto-loading non-bundled plugins\n- Added `\"allow\": [\"lossless-claw\"]` to plugins config\n- Now explicitly trusts lossless-claw plugin\n\n## 4:28 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Added plugins.allow config\n- Idle, awaiting Allan's next task\n\n## 4:33 PM (Whitepaper Review Request)\n\n- Allan asked to review whitepaper draft 0307, 0313 chat log, and whitepaper principles\n- Reading files to understand current state\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773566340609}}
