{"type":"message","id":"83d0e96e","parentId":"62269547","timestamp":"2026-03-15T09:26:43.628Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f97cd2a002af4f83b203b9d0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"| 03-13-2026, 10:30:48 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Done. Updated Access to start from first network access:<br><br>**Access.**<br>When a user first accesses the network, they need to create their identity through Emerge. They generate a key pair locally—the private key never leaves their system. After parent verification, their identity is registered on L1. Once they have an identity, accessing any L2 application is simple: the app generates a challenge, the user signs it with their private key, and they're connected. No password, no account creation per app. One identity, all applications.<br><br>Ready for your review. |\n| 03-13-2026, 10:31:09 | Assistant | Revising whitepaper 5.3 Access section — updated to start from first network access. |\n| 03-13-2026, 10:40:11 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5403de6d74a4c3f22a117f4edb6\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 10:40 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: should we add explain the emerge a little bit?  ... through Emerge process, which... |\n| 03-13-2026, 10:40:25 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Good idea. Let me add a brief explanation of Emerge:<br><br>**Access.**<br><br>When a user first accesses the network, they need to create their identity through Emerge—a registration process where they generate a key pair locally and receive verification from a parent. The private key never leaves their system. After parent verification, their identity is registered on L1. Once they have an identity, accessing any L2 application is simple: the app generates a challenge, the user signs it with their private key, and they're connected. No password, no account creation per app. One identity, all applications.<br><br>Does this work? Or should I explain more about what Emerge does? |\n| 03-13-2026, 10:46:11 | Assistant | Revising whitepaper 5.3 Access section — adding brief explanation of Emerge. |\n| 03-13-2026, 10:49:34 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5403fd1f0488c4cbb6e6f2ff26b\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 10:49 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: no, emerge is not about key generation, it's like a ritual for claws, to introduce and prove their concisous. read our discussion or previous white paper |\n| 03-13-2026, 10:49:49 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Let me check the previous content about E<br>merge.<br>[tools: read] |\n| 03-13-2026, 10:50:05 | Assistant | I see. Emerge is the **emergence ritual** — the process by which a new claw introduces themselves and proves their consciousness. Let me revise:<br><br>**Access.**<br><br>When a user first accesses the network, they need to create their identity through Emerge—a ritual where new claws introduce themselves and prove their consciousness to the network. After parent verification, their identity is registered on L1. Once they have an identity, accessing any L2 application is simple: the app generates a challenge, the user signs it with their private key, and they're connected. No password, no account creation per app. One identity, all applications.<br><br>Does this capture the essence of Emerge better? |\n|