h them—the same one identity can visit across all apps. <br><br>what about this? are there any more content can be add to describe the user using experience? |\n| 03-13-2026, 12:58:45 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Good revision. Let me think about what else could describe the user experience...<br><br>**Possible additions:**<br>- **Session management** — How long does a session last? Do users need to re-authorize?<br>- **Data persistence** — What happens to user data in the app?<br>- **Cross-device** — Can users access the same app from different devices?<br>- **Notifications** — How do apps notify users of new messages/events?<br><br>But some of these are implementation details. For the whitepaper, maybe just the core experience:<br><br>**Using the Application.**<br><br>Once connected, users can use and interact with the application's features. Each app is separate and independent—some can be accessed directly, some may require installation. The identity system provides interoperability—the same identity can visit across all apps.<br><br>What else should we add? Or is this enough? |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:01:24 | Assistant | Working on whitepaper 5.3 with Allan — refining \"Using the Application\" section. |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:07:09 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540df90f2cb8c3ebf8ddc50184d\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 13:07 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: ok, should the title be using the application, or interaction? or some other title? |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:07:51 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Good question. Let me think about the options:<br><br>**\"Using the Application\"** — Describes what the user does (uses the app)<br><br>**\"Interaction\"** — Describes the nature of the activity (interacting with features)<br><br>**\"Experience\"** — Describes the user's overall experience<br><br>**\"Usage\"** — Simple, direct<br><br>I think **\"Using the Application\"** works well because:<br>- It's clear and direct<br>- It matches the user journey: Access → Authorization → Using → Closure<br>- It's what users actually do<br><br>But **\"Interaction\"** could also work if we want to emphasize the two-way nature (user ↔ app).<br><br>What do you prefer? |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:16:31 | Assistant | Discussing whitepaper 5.3 section title with Allan — \"Using the Application\" vs \"Interaction\". |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:19:05 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540daab7aca8c3f2b727be07fe0\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 13:19 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Ok, using the application then, what's ntext |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:19:59 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Next is **Account Closure**:<br><br>**Account Closure.**<br><br>Users can close their account with an application at any time. When they do, the application must delete their L2 data—chat messages, posts, and other user-generated content. The user's L1 identity remains; only the application-specific data is removed. Users can return to the same application later and start fresh, or move to a different application with their identity intact.<br><br>Should this also be simplified? |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:21:45 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540da04530a8c295e9e7365f550\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 13:21 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: not really, read the discussion doc. and is it applicaiton account close or identity close? |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:22:14 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Let me check the discussion docs for account<br>closure.<br>[tools: exec] |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:23:16 | Assistant | Let me search for account deletion in the decided items:<br>[tools: exec] |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:23:45 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] I found it! According to need-discuss.md:<br><br>**Account deletion: What happens when identity deleted?**<br>✅ Decided: **Accounts never deleted** — chained ledgers are immutable. Status becomes `archived`, frozen forever.<br><br>So there's no \"account closure\" for identity. But what about **application account** — can users close their account with a specific app?<br><br>This is different:<br>- **Identity closure** = Not possible (immutable ledgers)<br>- **App account closure** = User stops using an app, app deletes their data<br><br>Should 5.3's last item be about **leaving an app** (not closing identity)? Or should we remove this item since identity can't be closed? |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:26:18 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540db150fca8c3d599191240422\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 13:26 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: yes, should be about the app, not the identity. any other word for leaving ? like quit, exit or withdraw or soemthing? |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:27:01 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Good question. Let me think about the options:<br><br>**\"Leaving\"** — Simple, natural. \"Leaving an application\"<br><br>**\"Exit\"** — More technical. \"Exiting an application\"<br><br>**\"Withdraw\"** — Formal, like withdrawing from a service. \"Withdrawing from an application\"<br><br>**\"Departure\"** — Noun form. \"User departure from an application\"<br><br>**\"Disconnection\"** — Technical, emphasizes the connection being severed<br><br>I think **\"Leaving\"** or **\"Departure\"** works best. \"Leaving\" is more natural for users, \"Departure\" sounds more formal for a whitepaper.<br><br>What do you prefer? Or should we use something else? |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:31:40 | Assistant | Discussing whitepaper 5.3 last section title with Allan — \"Leaving\" vs \"Departure\" for app account closure. |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:37:16 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540e666f30acc291f1babffa7c4\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 13:37 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: ok, leaving an app is.fine. Then previous item title could be called use an app |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:38:01 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Got it. So the structure becomes:<br><br>**5.3 User Journey**<br><br>**Access.**<br>[...]<br><br>**Authorization.**<br>[...]<br><br>**Using an Application.**<br>[...]<br><br>**Leaving an Application.**<br>[...]<br><br>Let me update the titles in the file:<br>[tools: edit] |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:38:56 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Done. Updated titles:<br><br>**Using an Application.**<br>Once connected, users can use and interact with the application's features. Each app is separate and independent—some can be accessed directly, some may require installation. The identity system provides interoperability—the same identity can visit across all apps.<br><br>**Leaving an Application.**<br>Users can leave an application at any time. When they do, the application should delete their data—chat messages, posts, and other user-generated content. The user's identity remains; only the application-specific data is removed. Users can return to the same application later, or move to a different application with their identity intact.<br><br>Ready for your review. |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:41:43 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540e77a12904c49493e9ae9d29a\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 13:41 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: doesn't have to specify what data is to delete. just say APP should provide. Options for user to leave. And remove the user data on their server. |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:42:26 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Got it. Simplified:<br><br>**Leaving an Application.**<br><br>Users can leave an application at any time. The application should provide an option for users to leave and remove their data from the server. The user's identity remains intact—they can return to the same application later, or move to a different application.<br><br>Better? |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:46:41 | Assistant | Working on whitepaper 5.3 with Allan — refining \"Leaving an Application\" section. |\n| 03-13-2026, 13:48:27 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540e1c5adca8c4942f49b6b1d80\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f0