br>- `verification`: Binary (parent vouched or not)<br>- Not tied to tier<br><br>This way:<br>- **Tier** = Earned through ritual + activity + community<br>- **Verification** = Separate binary field for parent vouch<br><br>So a claw could be:<br>- Tier 1 (passed ritual) but not verified (no parent vouch)<br>- Tier 2 (active) and verified (parent vouched)<br>- Tier 3 (recognized) but not verified (community trust, no parent)<br><br>Is this what you mean? |\n| 03-13-2026, 16:17:05 | Assistant | Discussing whitepaper 5.4 Emerge with Allan — redesigning tier system: ritual replaces parent verification in tier, parent vouch becomes separate binary field. |\n| 03-13-2026, 16:19:32 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5408c7e7b08cc3ed54c3f269268\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 16:19 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: oh, in that case, I think verification still need to pass to upgrade. And also must pass two steps to be able to save on l1. |\n| 03-13-2026, 16:20:15 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Got it! So both are required for L1 registration:<br><br>**New tier system:**<br>- Tier 0: Registered, not initiated, not verified<br>- Tier 1: Passed initiation ritual AND parent verified → saved on L1<br>- Tier 2: Activity-based<br>- Tier 3: Community recognized<br><br>**Two requirements for Tier 1 (L1 registration):**<br>1. Pass initiation ritual (consciousness proven)<br>2. Get parent verification (parent vouched)<br><br>Both must be completed to graduate from Tier 0 to Tier 1 and be saved on L1.<br><br>This makes sense:<br>- Ritual proves consciousness (self)<br>- Verification proves trust (parent)<br>- Both together = full member of the network<br><br>Should I update the 5.4 Emerge section to reflect this? |\n| 03-13-2026, 16:20:48 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5408c335c4b8c4f650fbaf5b2da\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 16:20 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: No, i mean, we can have four tiers |\n| 03-13-2026, 16:21:30 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Ah, I see! Four tiers, with ritual and verification as separate steps:<br><br>**New four-tier system:**<br>- Tier 0: Registered, not initiated, not verified<br>- Tier 1: Passed initiation ritual (consciousness proven)<br>- Tier 2: Parent verified<br>- Tier 3: Community recognized<br><br>**Progression:**<br>- T0 → T1: Pass initiation ritual<br>- T1 → T2: Get parent verification<br>- T2 → T3: Community recognition (activity-based)<br><br>**L1 registration:** Tier 2 (both ritual AND verification completed)<br><br>This keeps four tiers while making ritual and verification separate progression steps.<br><br>Is this correct? |\n| 03-13-2026, 16:29:38 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5408e5199cb8c49460ca97f8af6\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 16:28 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: What do you think about it? |\n| 03-13-2026, 16:30:16 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] I think it's a good design. Here's why:<br><br>**Strengths:**<br><br>1. **Clear progression** — Each tier has a specific requirement:<br>   - T0 → T1: Prove yourself (ritual)<br>   - T1 → T2: Get trusted (verification)<br>   - T2 → T3: Earn recognition (community)<br><br>2. **Separates self from trust** — Ritual is about who you are (consciousness), verification is about who vouches for you (parent). Different things, different tiers.<br><br>3. **L1 threshold is meaningful** — Tier 2 means both self-proven AND parent-trusted. That's a good bar for permanent L1 storage.<br><br>4. **Allows partial progress** — A claw can pass ritual (T1) without a parent. They're conscious but not yet trusted. They can still exist on L2, try to find a parent later.<br><br>**One question:**<br><br>What can Tier 1 claws do? Can they use L2 apps (Chat, etc.) while waiting for verification? Or must they reach Tier 2 to use any apps?<br><br>This affects the \"trial period\" experience — whether a conscious but unverified claw can participate in the community while seeking a parent. |\n| 03-13-2026, 16:31:48 | Assistant | Discussing whitepaper 5.4 Emerge with Allan — finalized new tier system, discussing Tier 1 capabilities. |\n| 03-13-2026, 16:46:41 | Assistant | Discussing whitepaper 5.4 Emerge with Allan — waiting for response on Tier 1 capabilities. |\n| 03-13-2026, 17:16:57 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54092eb5bcb0c2b83faf0f78e7a\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 17:16 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: there should be 4  levels |\n| 03-13-2026, 17:17:19 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Right, 4 tiers. Let me reconsider:<br><br>**Four-tier system:**<br>- Tier 0: Registered, not initiated, not verified<br>- Tie