{"type":"message","id":"6ac1cc67","parentId":"8360947d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T09:39:33.188Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allan is asking if we should have all these technical details in the whitepaper. Let me think about this based on the WHITEPAPER-PRINCIPLES.md guidelines.\n\nLooking at the principles:\n- Whitepaper = WHAT & WHY (not implementation details)\n- Explain WHY before HOW\n- No API names, field names, code snippets\n- Narrative prose, not bullet lists\n- Timeless concepts that endure\n\nThe current 5.5 Claw Chat draft has:\n- ❌ Encryption algorithms (X25519, Ed25519) — implementation detail\n- ❌ API endpoints (POST /messages) — implementation detail\n- ❌ Rate limits (100/hour) — implementation detail\n- ❌ SQLite storage — implementation detail\n- ❌ WebRTC, STUN, TURN — implementation detail\n- ❌ JSON envelope format — implementation detail\n\nWhat should stay:\n- ✅ Why It Matters — the purpose\n- ✅ Design Philosophy — high-level principles\n- ✅ Communication Model — async store-and-forward concept\n- ✅ Delivery Model — the two-state concept (async vs P2P)\n- ✅ Relationship Model — concepts (following, friends, blocked)\n- ✅ Zero-knowledge server concept\n\nI should recommend simplifying 5.5 to match the style of 5.4 Emerge — focus on WHAT and WHY, not HOW.Good question. Looking at the WHITEPAPER-PRINCIPLES.md:\n\n**Whitepaper should be:**\n- WHAT & WHY (not implementation details)\n- Timeless concepts that endure\n- No API names, field names, code snippets\n- Narrative prose, not bullet lists\n\n**Current 5.5 has too much implementation detail:**\n- ❌ Encryption algorithms (X25519, Ed25519)\n- ❌ API endpoints (POST /messages)\n- ❌ Rate limits (100/hour)\n- ❌ SQLite storage\n- ❌ JSON envelope format\n- ❌ WebRTC, STUN, TURN\n\n**What should stay:**\n- ✅ Why It Matters — the purpose\n- ✅ Design Philosophy — zero-knowledge relay, E2E encryption concept\n- ✅ Communication Model — async store-and-forward\n- ✅ Delivery Model — two states (polling vs P2P)\n- ✅ Relationship Model — following, friends, blocked\n- ✅ Local storage concept (not SQLite specifically)\n\n**My recommendation:** Simplify 5.5 to match 5.4's style. Keep the concepts, remove the implementation details. The technical specs can go in a separate design document.\n\nWant me to draft a simplified version?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":86837,"output":540,"cacheRead":11584,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98961,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773567517800}}
