{"type":"message","id":"8eb53f02","parentId":"de3eccfc","timestamp":"2026-03-15T10:22:20.097Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allan is saying not to use question format for titles. Let me check the current 5.5 section to see if there are any question-format titles.\n\nLooking at the 5.5 section I just wrote:\n- \"Why It Matters\" - not a question format\n- \"Design Philosophy\" - not a question format\n- \"Communication Model\" - not a question format\n- \"Delivery Model\" - not a question format\n- \"Relationships\" - not a question format\n- \"Access Control\" - not a question format\n\nThese are all statement formats, not questions. Let me check if Allan is referring to something else in the whitepaper.\n\nActually, looking at the previous sections like 5.4 Emerge:\n- \"Purpose\" - statement\n- \"Registration\" - statement\n- \"Initiation\" - statement\n- \"Verification\" - statement\n- \"Architecture\" - statement\n\nAll the titles are in statement format. I'm not sure what Allan is referring to. Let me ask for clarification.\n\nOr maybe Allan is referring to the phrase \"Why It Matters\" which could be interpreted as a question-like format? Let me change it to something more direct like \"Purpose\" or \"Importance\".\n\nActually, \"Why It Matters\" is a common section title in documentation. But if Allan prefers statement format, I could change it to \"Purpose\" or \"Importance\" to match the style of 5.4 Emerge.\n\nLet me ask Allan for clarification or make the change.明白。让我检查一下 5.5 的标题格式。\n\n当前标题：\n- Why It Matters\n- Design Philosophy\n- Communication Model\n- Delivery Model\n- Relationships\n- Access Control\n\n这些是陈述格式，不是问题格式。你指的是哪个标题？\n\n或者要把 \"Why It Matters\" 改成 \"Purpose\" 或 \"Importance\" 来匹配 5.4 的风格？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":86996,"output":390,"cacheRead":1600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88986,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":