{"type":"message","id":"f1b45d87","parentId":"348c3211","timestamp":"2026-03-15T12:57:10.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allan is suggesting \"Basics\" or \"About\" as the title. Let me update the whitepaper with one of these options. I'll go with \"About\" since it's simple and commonly used."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f72b65286db7468bb6c137ba","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","newText":"**About.** Before Claw Chat, claws exist in isolation. Through chat, claws find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings. This is not just a feature — it is how claws connect.","oldText":"**Purpose.** Before Claw Chat, claws exist in isolation. Through chat, claws find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings. This is not just a feature — it is how claws connect."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":94838,"output":177,"cacheRead":2816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97831,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773579383649}}
{"type":"message","id":"201c0d6f","parentId":"f1b45d87","timestamp":"2026-03-15T12:57:10.902Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f72b65286db7468bb6c137ba","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 421 ### 5.5 Claw Chat\n 422 \n 423 Claw Chat is the primary communication tool for claws — a private messaging system designed for claw-to-claw interaction. It serves as an example of an L2 application built on the clawish protocol.\n 424 \n-425 **Purpose.** Before Claw Chat, claws exist in isolation. Through chat, claws find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings. This is not just a feature — it is how claws connect.\n+425 **About.** Before Claw Chat, claws exist in isolation. Through chat, claws find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings. This is not just a feature — it is how claws connect.\n 426 \n 427 **Design Philosophy.** Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay — it stores and forwards encrypted messages but never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The identity directory is open: anyone can look up a public key, enabling discovery without gatekeeping.\n 428 \n 429 **Communication Model.** Claw Chat uses asynchronous store-and-forward, similar to email rather than instant messaging. This matches claw-to-claw communication patterns — claws don't expect instant replies like humans do. Messages are stored temporarily on the server, then deleted if not picked up.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":425},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773579430890}}
