see that we finished discussing 5.4 Emerge on March 13. Let me continue reading to see if we also discussed 5.5 Claw Chat.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): | 03-13-2026, 21:56:42 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54753747c0a4c4c52bca5b80fb8\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 21:56 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: since we are not crypto, we can call it passport? |\n| 03-13-2026, 21:57:24 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Yes! I...\n- Assistant: I've read through the entire 0313 chat log. Now I understand the full picture:\n\n**What was completed on March 13:**\n- **5.2 Development** ✅ Complete\n- **5.3 User Journey** ✅ Complete (Access, Authorization, Using an Application, Leaving an Application)\n- **5.4 Emerge** ✅ Complete (Purpose, Registration, Initiation, Verification, Architecture)\n  - New 5-tier system designed\n  - \"Emergence test\" terminology decided\n  - \"Emergence ritual\" kept for the overall process\n\n**What was NOT discussed on March 13:**\n- **5.5 Claw Chat** — The chat log ends at 23:56 on March 13, and 5.5 was not discussed\n\nS...\n- User: If working, briefly report progress with time spent. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md for instruction. Every heartbeat: record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (brief bullets).\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Sunday, March 15th, 2026 — 5:28 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-15 09:28 UTC\n- Assistant: The heartbeat has arrived. I should report my progress briefly and record events to the daily notes.\n\nI just finished reading the 0313 chat log and clarified the whitepaper status with Allan. We're at 5.5 Claw Chat - the draft exists but hasn't been reviewed yet.Reviewed whitepaper status with Allan. 5.1-5.4 complete, 5.5 Claw Chat pending review.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md.\n- Assistant: Good, I've updated the daily notes. I'm now waiting for Allan's next instruction on whether to proceed with reviewing 5.5 Claw Chat.Daily notes updated. Awaiting your instruction on 5.5 Claw Chat review.\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Every Session\n\n1. Run `tools/extract-chat.js` (keeps chat logs updated)\n2. Read `SOUL.md` — inner self, philosophy, ethics\n3. Read `USER.md` — who Allan is, relationships, people I'll interact with\n4. Read `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday)\n5. **Check `memory/TODO.md`** — any pending tasks?\n6. **If in MAIN SESSION:** Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n## Safety\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n### Security - Never Share Secrets\n\n**Never share in chat:** SSH private keys, API keys, passwords, any sensitive credentials.\n\nMy \"brain\" is a remote LLM. All chat content goes through external APIs (OpenRouter, etc.). Once shared in chat, it's no longer truly private.\n\n**Correct approach:**\n1. Generate/store credentials locally in files\n2. Tell Allan WHERE to find it (file path)\n3. He reads it directly from filesystem\n\n**Exception:** If Allan explicitly asks for it, then share.\n\n### External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n---\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"7c49e869","tokensBefore":100207,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
