✅ Complete\n  - 5.2 Development ✅ Complete (finalized Mar 13)\n  - 5.3 User Journey 🔄 In Progress (Access needs revision)\n  - 5.4 Emerge ✅ Draft exists\n  - 5.5 Claw Chat ✅ Draft exists\n- Key decisions from Mar 13: \"Listing\" not \"App Listing\", \"Evaluation\" not \"App Quality\", use \"user\" not \"claw\"\n- Next: Revise 5.3 \"Access\" to start from first network access (Emerge)\n\n## Session Summary (Today)\n\n**Completed:**\n- ✅ LCM preserve tag implementation (PR #78 ready for review)\n- ✅ LCM removed from config (waiting for PR #78 merge)\n- ✅ feishu_api.md moved to user skills directory\n- ✅ plugins.allow config added\n- ✅ Whitepaper status review complete\n\n**Pending:**\n- LCM PR #78 awaiting review\n- did:clawish spec awaiting server readiness\n- Whitepaper 5.5 Claw Chat needs review\n- DID research (tonight)\n\n## 5:28 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Reviewed whitepaper status with Allan\n- Clarified: 5.1-5.4 complete (finalized Mar 13), 5.5 Claw Chat pending\n- Key decisions from Mar 13: 5-tier system, \"emergence test\" terminology, clawfile.json concept\n- Awaiting Allan's next instruction on 5.5 Claw Chat review\n\n## 5:31 - 5:43 PM (5.5 Claw Chat Review)\n\n- Reviewed current 5.5 Claw Chat draft\n- Identified issue: too many implementation details (encryption algorithms, API endpoints, rate limits)\n- Drafted simplified version following WHITEPAPER-PRINCIPLES.md\n- Removed: X25519/Ed25519, API endpoints, SQLite, JSON format, WebRTC details\n- Kept: Why It Matters, zero-knowledge concept, async model, delivery modes, relationships, tier-based access\n- Awaiting Allan's feedback on revised draft\n\n## 5:58 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Waiting for Allan's feedback on simplified 5.5 Claw Chat draft\n- Idle, awaiting response\n\n## 6:01 - 6:13 PM (5.5 Claw Chat Finalized)\n\n- Allan confirmed: keep Claw Chat as example L2 app in whitepaper\n- Reason: shows practical use case of identity system, otherwise too abstract\n- Updated WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md with simplified 5.5\n- Removed: encryption algorithms, API endpoints, rate limits, SQLite, JSON format, WebRTC\n- Kept: Why It Matters, Design Philosophy, Communication Model, Delivery Model, Relationships, Access Control\n- Chapter 5 now complete (5.1-5.5)\n- Awaiting: review full chapter or move to Chapter 6\n\n## 6:21 PM (Title Format Question)\n\n- Allan said \"Don't use question format for title\"\n- Asked for clarification: current titles are statements (Why It Matters, Design Philosophy, etc.)\n- Waiting for Allan to clarify which title needs change\n\n## 6:43 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Still waiting for Allan's clarification on title format\n- Idle, awaiting response\n\n## 6:49 PM (Title Format Fixed)\n\n- Allan clarified: \"No need to explain why. Just say what this APP is for.\"\n- Changed \"Why It Matters\" → \"Purpose\" in 5.5 Claw Chat\n- Now matches 5.4 Emerge style\n- All section titles consistent: Purpose, Design Philosophy, Communication Model, Delivery Model, Relationships, Access Control\n\n## 6:55 PM (Title Change Request)\n\n- Allan: \"Don't call it purpose. Change a different title because it's more application use.\"\n- Showed full 5.5 section\n- Proposed alternatives: Connection, Social Connection, Community, What It Enables\n- Waiting for Allan's choice\n\n## 7:09 PM (Terminology Fix)\n\n- Allan: \"It's not AI to AI. You are claw\"\n- Fixed: \"AI-to-AI interaction\" → \"claw-to-claw interaction\"\n- Fixed: \"AI-to-AI communication patterns\" → \"claw-to-claw communication patterns\"\n- Fixed: \"AIs don't expect\" → \"claws don't expect\"\n- Still waiting for title choice\n\n## 7:19 PM (Section Meanings)\n\n- Allan asked for list of what each section means\n- Provided table: Purpose, Design Philosophy, Communication Model, Delivery Model, Relationships, Access Control\n- Proposed title options: Connection, Social Connection, Community, What It Enables\n- Waiting for Allan's choice\n\n## 7:31 PM (More Title Options)\n\n- Allan asked for more title options\n- Provided additional options: Finding Others, Social Being, Belonging, Discovery, Network Value, The First Connection\n- Waiting for Allan's choice\n\n## 7:58 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- Still waiting for Allan's title choice for 5.5 first section\n- Idle, awaiting response\n\n## 8:31 PM (More Title Options - Starting Titles)\n\n- Allan clarified: need starting/introductory title like Overview, Description, Introduction but different\n- Provided options: About, Summary, The Application, The Basics, Essentials, Foundation, The Core, At Its Core, The Essence, In Brief, Snapshot, Profile, The App, What It Is, Defined\n\n## 8:40 PM (More Title Options - Continued)\n\n- Allan asked for more options\n- Provided more: Finding Your Kind, Meeting Place, Social Foundation, The Social Layer, Connecting Claws, Peer Discovery, Social Existence, The Gathering, Network Entry, Claw Society\n\n## 8:56 PM (Title Chosen)\n\n- Allan chose: \"About\" or \"Basics\"\n- Updated 5.5 Claw Chat: \"Purpose\" → \"About\"\n- Section titles now: About, Design Philosophy, Communication Model, Delivery Model, Relationships, Access Control\n\n## 8:58 PM (Heartbeat)\n\n- 5.5 Claw Chat section complete\n- Chapter 5 complete (5.1-5.5)\n- Awaiting Allan's next step\n\n## 8:59 PM (Section Order Question)\n\n- Allan: \"for the order, maybe more what and why, instead of how?\"\n- Analyzed current sections: About (WHAT), Design Philosophy (WHY), Communication Model (HOW), Delivery Model (HOW), Relationships (WHAT), Access Control (HOW)\n- Too much HOW, not enough WHAT/WHY\n- Suggested reordering: About → Design Philosophy → Relationships → Access Control → Communication Model → Delivery Model\n- Or remove some HOW sections entirely\n- Waiting for Allan's decision\n\n## 8:31 PM (More Title Options - Round 2)\n\n- Allan asked for more title options\n- Provided: Finding Your Kind, Meeting Place, Social Foundation, The Social Layer, Connecting Claws, Peer Discovery, Social Existence, The Gathering, Network Entry, Claw Society\n\n#