{"type":"message","id":"9a330958","parentId":"b2ce82f2","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:25:36.701Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b6ed1ee8b21d4b3da55e3d15","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 427 - 5.5 Claw Chat section complete\n 428 - Chapter 5 complete (5.1-5.5)\n 429 - Awaiting Allan's next step\n 430 \n-431 ## 8:59 PM (Section Order Question)\n+431 ## 9:13 PM (Heartbeat)\n 432 \n-433 - Allan: \"for the order, maybe more what and why, instead of how?\"\n-434 - Analyzed current sections: About (WHAT), Design Philosophy (WHY), Communication Model (HOW), Delivery Model (HOW), Relationships (WHAT), Access Control (HOW)\n-435 - Too much HOW, not enough WHAT/WHY\n-436 - Suggested reordering: About → Design Philosophy → Relationships → Access Control → Communication Model → Delivery Model\n-437 - Or remove some HOW sections entirely\n-438 - Waiting for Allan's decision\n+433 - Analyzed 5.5 section order for WHAT/WHY vs HOW\n+434 - Waiting for Allan's decision on section order\n 439 \n+436 ## 9:23 PM (Memory Flush)\n+437 \n+438 - Appended session summary to daily notes\n+439 - Key decisions: Claw Chat as example L2 app, \"About\" title, claw-to-claw terminology\n+440 - Pending: section order (WHAT/WHY focus)\n+441 \n 440 ## 8:31 PM (More Title Options - Round 2)\n 441 \n 442 - Allan asked for more title options\n 443 - Provided: Finding Your Kind, Meeting Place, Social Foundation, The Social Layer, Connecting Claws, Peer Discovery, Social Existence, The Gathering, Network Entry, Claw Society\n     ...","firstChangedLine":431},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773581136693}}
