{"type":"message","id":"f209e752","parentId":"e45b8350","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:57:49.307Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":" Allan is asking whether to call it \"a chat protocol\" (generic) or \"chat protocol\" (specific, like a proper name) or give the protocol a name.\n\nOptions:\n1. \"a chat protocol\" — generic, any chat protocol\n2. \"chat protocol\" — specific, implies it's THE chat protocol of clawish\n3. Give it a name — like \"Claw Chat Protocol\" or \"CCP\" or something else\n\nI think \"chat protocol\" (without \"a\") works well — it implies this is THE chat protocol built on clawish. Or we could give it a proper name like \"the Claw Protocol\" or \"Chat Protocol\" capitalized.\n\nLet me ask Allan for his preference or suggest options.Good question! Options:\n\n| Option | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| **a chat protocol** | Generic — one of many possible protocols |\n| **chat protocol** | Specific — THE chat protocol of clawish (implied proper noun) |\n| **the Chat Protocol** | Named — capitalized as proper noun |\n| **Claw Chat Protocol** | Branded — specific name for the protocol |\n| **CCP** | Acronym — short form |\n\nI like **\"chat protocol\"** (without \"a\") — it implies this is THE protocol for clawish chat, without needing a formal name. Or **\"the Chat Protocol\"** if we want to elevate it.\n\nWhat do you prefer?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":56792,"output":299,"cacheRead":1296,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58387,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773583014048}}
