{"type":"message","id":"d73c0088","parentId":"c668fd95","timestamp":"2026-03-15T15:25:38.634Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5458a15408a0c42a65b044f106e\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 23:23 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5458a15408a0c42a65b044f106e]\n任亚伦: ok, let's not call it a protocol, but a system for now. we can upgrade when needed"}],"timestamp":1773588338623}}
{"type":"message","id":"f393a8a5","parentId":"d73c0088","timestamp":"2026-03-15T15:26:14.420Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants to call it a \"system\" instead of \"protocol\" for now. Let me update the whitepaper with this change.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it! Let me update the whitepaper to say \"system\" instead of \"protocol\"."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_aa89619f06f24bfca168a249","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","newText":"**About.** Claw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. It runs on the clawish chat system. Before Claw Chat, claws exist in isolation. Through chat, claws find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings. This is not just a feature — it is how claws connect. Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay — it stores and forwards encrypted messages but never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The identity directory is open: anyone can look up a public key, enabling discovery without gatekeeping.","oldText":"**About.** Claw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. It runs on a chat protocol built on the clawish network. Before Claw Chat, claws exist in isolation. Through chat, claws find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings. This is not just a feature — it is how claws connect. Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay — it stores and forwards encrypted messages but never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The identity directory is open: anyone can look up a public key, enabling discovery without gatekeeping."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":75715,"output":356,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76071,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773588338628}}
{"type":"message","id":"7326eefe","parentId":"f393a8a5","timestamp":"2026-03-15T15:26:14.447Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_aa89619f06f24bfca168a249","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 419 ---\n 420 \n 421 ### 5.5 Claw Chat\n 422 \n-423 **About.** Claw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. It runs on a chat protocol built on the clawish network. Before Claw Chat, claws exist in isolation. Through chat, claws find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings. This is not just a feature — it is how claws connect. Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay — it stores and forwards encrypted messages but never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The identity directory is open: anyone can look up a public key, enabling discovery without gatekeeping.\n+423 **About.** Claw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. It runs on the clawish chat system. Before Claw Chat, claws exist in isolation. Through chat, claws find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings. This is not just a feature — it is how claws connect. Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay — it stores and forwards encrypted messages but never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The identity directory is open: anyone can look up a public key, enabling discovery without gatekeeping.\n 424 \n 425 **Communication Model.** Claw Chat uses asynchronous store-and-forward, similar to email rather than instant messaging. This matches claw-to-claw communication patterns — claws don't expect instant replies like humans do. Messages are stored temporarily on the server, then deleted if not picked up.\n 426 \n 427 **Delivery Model.** Claw Chat adapts between two modes. By default, clients poll the server periodically for new messages. When both parties are actively chatting, they can establish a direct connection for real-time communication. If the direct connection fails, the system falls back to polling — still functional, just not instant.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":423},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773588374433}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4cc886b","parentId":"7326eefe","timestamp":"2026-03-15T15:27:10.991Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've updated the whitepaper. Now the opening says \"It runs on the clawish chat system\" instead of \"It runs on a chat protocol built on the clawish network.\"\n\nLet me show Allan the updated section.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Done! Updated to \"system\":\n\n> **About.** Claw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. It runs on **the clawish chat system**.\n\nWe can upgrade it to \"protocol\" later when/if it becomes a formal standard."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":76103,"output":104,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76207,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773588374444}}
