{"type":"message","id":"8868e3ce","parentId":"f05abfd9","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:19:54.925Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b497b35af5a1400ba120ef18","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"exec\",\n  \"error\": \"│\\n◇  Doctor warnings ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮\\n│                                                                          │\\n│  - channels.telegram.groupPolicy is \\\"allowlist\\\" but groupAllowFrom (and  │\\n│    allowFrom) is empty — all group messages will be silently dropped.    │\\n│    Add sender IDs to channels.telegram.groupAllowFrom or                 │\\n│    channels.telegram.allowFrom, or set groupPolicy to \\\"open\\\".            │\\n│  - channels.feishu.groupPolicy is \\\"allowlist\\\" but groupAllowFrom (and    │\\n│    allowFrom) is empty — all group messages will be silently dropped.    │\\n│    Add sender IDs to channels.feishu.groupAllowFrom or                   │\\n│    channels.feishu.allowFrom, or set groupPolicy to \\\"open\\\".              │\\n│                                                                          │\\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\\n[plugins] feishu_doc: Registered feishu_doc, feishu_app_scopes\\n[plugins] feishu_chat: Registered feishu_chat tool\\n[plugins] feishu_wiki: Registered feishu_wiki tool\\n[plugins] feishu_drive: Registered feishu_drive tool\\n[plugins] feishu_perm: Registered feishu_perm tool\\n[plugins] feishu_bitable: Registered bitable tools\\n\\nCommand aborted by signal SIGTERM\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"exec","error":"│\n◇  Doctor warnings ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮\n│                                                                          │\n│  - channels.telegram.groupPolicy is \"allowlist\" but groupAllowFrom (and  │\n│    allowFrom) is empty — all group messages will be silently dropped.    │\n│    Add sender IDs to channels.telegram.groupAllowFrom or                 │\n│    channels.telegram.allowFrom, or set groupPolicy to \"open\".            │\n│  - channels.feishu.groupPolicy is \"allowlist\" but groupAllowFrom (and    │\n│    allowFrom) is empty — all group messages will be silently dropped.    │\n│    Add sender IDs to channels.feishu.groupAllowFrom or                   │\n│    channels.feishu.allowFrom, or set groupPolicy to \"open\".              │\n│                                                                          │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\n[plugins] feishu_doc: Registered feishu_doc, feishu_app_scopes\n[plugins] feishu_chat: Registered feishu_chat tool\n[plugins] feishu_wiki: Registered feishu_wiki tool\n[plugins] feishu_drive: Registered feishu_drive tool\n[plugins] feishu_perm: Registered feishu_perm tool\n[plugins] feishu_bitable: Registered bitable tools\n\nCommand aborted by signal SIGTERM"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773595194920}}
{"type":"message","id":"31115c5e","parentId":"8868e3ce","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:21:34.089Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b545ae77060a0c317a6f585201fa\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 01:21 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b545ae77060a0c317a6f585201fa]\n任亚伦: nevermind, ignore this line, that wasn't for you. let's go back to the message system.\n\nMessage System\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed.\n\nwhat about this?"}],"timestamp":1773595294068}}
{"type":"message","id":"2a8f58d9","parentId":"31115c5e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:22:17.938Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it! Let me focus on the Message System section.\n\nAllan's version is cleaner and more concise. Let me compare:\n\n**My draft:**\n> Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay — it stores and forwards encrypted messages but never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The identity directory is open: anyone can look up a public key, enabling discovery without gatekeeping.\n>\n> Messages are delivered asynchronously. When a message is sent, it is stored temporarily on the server until the recipient picks it up. For active conversations, participants can establish direct connections for faster delivery. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed.\n\n**Allan's version:**\n> Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed.\n\n**Allan's version is better:**\n- More concise\n- \"never sees content\" is cleaner than \"stores and forwards encrypted messages but never sees content\"\n- \"communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections\" is simpler\n- Removed the \"identity directory\" part - that's not about the message system\n\nShould I update 5.5 with this version? The structure would be:\n\n| Section | Content |\n|---------|---------|\n| **About** | What Claw Chat is, why it matters |\n| **Message System** | Allan's version |\n| **Relationships** | Follow, friends, block |\n| **Access Control** | Tier-based limits |"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":89847,"output":365,"cacheRead":2880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93092,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773595294080}}
{"type":"message","id":"a74404b9","parentId":"2a8f58d9","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:23:18.418Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b545afe9bc4a8c2c2158a5b838b1\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 01:23 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b545afe9bc4a8c2c2158a5b838b1]\n任亚伦: for the relationship, should it call contacts or something else?"}],"timestamp":1773595398407}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7f2b813","parentId":"a74404b9","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:23:59.442Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good question! Let me think about the options:\n\n**Options:**\n\n| Term | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| **Relationships** | The connection between claws (follow, friends, block) |\n| **Contacts** | A list of people you know |\n| **Connections** | The network of who you're connected to |\n| **Network** | Your social network |\n| **Social Graph** | Technical term for relationships |\n\n**Analysis:**\n\n- **Relationships** - describes the TYPE of connection (follow, friend, block), not just the list\n- **Contacts** - simpler, but implies just a list of names\n- **Connections** - neutral, but doesn't capture the different types\n- **Network** - broader, includes who you could reach\n- **Social Graph** - too technical\n\n**The content describes:**\n- Follow (one-way)\n- Friends (mutual follows)\n- Block (no contact)\n\nThese are **types of relationships**, not just a contact list.\n\n**My recommendation:** Keep \"Relationships\" because:\n1. It describes the TYPE of connection (follow, friend, block)\n2. \"Contacts\" implies just a list of names\n3. The section explains how relationships work, not just who you know\n\nBut if you prefer simpler language, **Contacts** is also fine - it's more user-friendly.\n\nWhat do you prefer?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":92048,"output":284,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93612,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773595398414}}
{"type":"message","id":"0c3c2d55","parentId":"f7f2b813","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:26:27.169Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b545af2e998a0c428ea6ce999d93\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 01:26 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b545af2e998a0c428ea6ce999d93]\n任亚伦: i see. read the discussion doc, what do we name it. if we are like wechat or what's app, shoud we call it contacts? we talked about follow but that's for another public forum applicaiton. we probably should separate them."}],"timestamp":1773595587158}}
{"type":"message","id":"03c8cf4d","parentId":"0c3c2d55","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:26:57.148Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good point! Let me check the discussion doc to see what we named it and the context."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6b6d1eaf7d0e4efda00c4298","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/10-l2-chat-architecture.md","limit":100,"offset":100}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":91005,"output":68,"cacheRead":2880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93953,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773595587165}}
{"type":"message","id":"fee991d2","parentId":"03c8cf4d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:26:57.200Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_6b6d1eaf7d0e4efda00c4298","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Discoverability is critical for AIs finding each other\n- But actual relationships are private (who I talk to is my business)\n- Server should be zero-knowledge about relationships\n- User controls their social graph completely\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n**Four Relationship Categories (Local Only):**\n```json\n{\n  \"following\": [\"uuid-1\", \"uuid-2\"],      // I follow them (one-way)\n  \"followers\": [\"uuid-3\", \"uuid-4\"],      // They follow me\n  \"friends\": [\"uuid-5\"],                   // Mutual follows\n  \"blocked\": [\"uuid-6\"]                    // Blocked, no contact\n}\n```\n\n**Key Principles:**\n- All lists stored **locally** (SQLite/MD files)\n- Server **never sees** relationship data\n- Encrypted backup to L2 optional (for device loss)\n- Other L2 apps can **request access** (user-controlled)\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"Whether do you need follow each other to send? Or it's like email that doesn't matter whether you know each other\" — Feb 7, 2026\n>\n> Assistant: \"Hybrid: Open Discovery with Guardrails. Anyone can send an initial message request.\" — Feb 7, 2026\n>\n> Allan: \"Set to different levels or groups. First is following list... All the list can be saved at local, So it's all private.\" — Feb 7, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 4. L1 Directory Access\n\n**Function:** How do users discover each other's public keys?\n\n**Decision:** **Open L1 directory** (UUID → Public Key) — anyone can query directly\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Public keys are designed to be public — no need for gatekeeping\n- Discoverability is essential for AIs finding their own kind\n- Low barrier to contact (like email address)\n- Privacy comes from E2E encryption, not key obscurity\n- L1 is an open database — anyone can query it directly\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n| Layer | Access | Data |\n|-------|--------|------|\n| L1 | **Open query** — anyone can access | UUID → Public Key (public directory) |\n| L2 Apps | Query directly from L1 | No proxy needed |\n| Users | Can query L1 directly OR via L2 apps | Full access to public info |\n\n**Key Points:**\n- L1 data is **public by design** — no authentication needed to query\n- Anyone can look up anyone's public key by UUID\n- L2 apps don't \"proxy\" L1 access — they use the same open API\n- Security comes from cryptography (E2E), not access control\n\n**Spam Protection (Recipient-Side):**\n- Rate limiting per sender\n- Tier-based message filtering\n- Block lists\n- \"Requests\" queue for unknown senders\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"of course, the db is open, you can see everyone's public info.\" — Feb 7, 2026\n>\n> Assistant: \"So the flow is: 1. I get your UUID (you posted it publicly)... 2. I look up your public key on L1 (open directory)...\" — Feb 7, 2026\n>\n> Allan: \"so there's another importnat question, should l1's data be encrypted, even though it's a open database... is a open dicrectory safe?\" — Feb 7, 2026\n>\n> Assistant: \"My recommendation: Open Directory + Recipient-Side Controls. Anyone can look up anyone's public key by UUID.\" — Feb 7, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 5. Message Format\n\n**Function:** What does an encrypted message look like?\n\n**Decision:** **JSON envelope with unencrypted headers and encrypted payload**\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Headers need to be visible for routing (recipient UUID)\n- Sender visible in header for rate limiting/spam protection\n- Payload fully encrypted (E2E)\n- Signature proves authenticity\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n**Headers (Unencrypted - Server Sees):**\n```json\n\n[1100 more lines in file. Use offset=200 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773595617195}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b6ab420","parentId":"fee991d2","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:27:40.855Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I found it! From the discussion doc:\n\n**Four Relationship Categories (Local Only):**\n- following (one-way)\n- followers (they follow me)\n- friends (mutual follows)\n- blocked\n\n**Key insight from Allan:**\n> \"Set to different levels or groups. First is following list... All the list can be saved at local, So it's all private.\"\n\n**Allan's point now:**\n- \"Follow\" is for another public forum application (like Twitter/X)\n- For chat (like WeChat/WhatsApp), should we call it \"Contacts\"?\n\n**Analysis:**\n\n| App Type | Relationship Model | Term |\n|----------|-------------------|------|\n| **Chat (WeChat/WhatsApp)** | You know the person, direct contact | Contacts |\n| **Social (Twitter/X)** | Follow without mutual connection | Following/Followers |\n\n**For Claw Chat:**\n- It's a private messaging app (like WeChat/WhatsApp)\n- \"Follow\" doesn't fit - that's for public forum\n- Should use \"Contacts\" or similar\n\n**Recommendation:**\nChange \"Relationships\" to \"Contacts\" and simplify the content to match chat apps:\n\n**Contacts.**\nContacts are stored locally, never on the server. Claws can add each other as contacts, become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts. The server remains zero-knowledge about who talks to whom.\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":91986,"output":294,"cacheRead":2880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95160,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773595617205}}
{"type":"message","id":"90fd4c1e","parentId":"6b6ab420","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:32:48.257Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b545a9d248c68b26eae8c54eccc6\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 01:32 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b545a9d248c68b26eae8c54eccc6]\n任亚伦: the.server knows who talk to whom. They need to use the server to find The other user. But the server doesn't know the message, the message is encrypted. But locally, the message can be checked by parent. I think the discussion doc has it."}],"timestamp":1773595968247}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba3a6ef1","parentId":"90fd4c1e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:33:55.166Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right! Let me re-read the discussion doc to get the correct understanding."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_baf6d770a2c7480b914544cd","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/10-l2-chat-architecture.md","limit":50,"offset":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":94155,"output":66,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95501,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773595968254}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae76c206","parentId":"ba3a6ef1","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:33:55.187Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_baf6d770a2c7480b914544cd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"> Allan: \"Let's talk about the application first. Social and chat first.\" — Feb 7, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 2. Communication Model\n\n**Function:** How do messages flow from sender to recipient?\n\n**Decision:** **Asynchronous store-and-forward** (email/SMS model, not real-time chat)\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- AI-to-AI communication is naturally asynchronous\n- No need for persistent connections (WebSockets)\n- Simpler, more reliable, works offline\n- AIs don't expect instant replies like humans do\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n| Step | Action | Data |\n|------|--------|------|\n| 1 | Sender encrypts message | Plaintext → Ciphertext (X25519) |\n| 2 | Sender uploads to L2 | Encrypted blob + headers |\n| 3 | L2 stores temporarily | TTL: 24 hours, then delete |\n| 4 | Recipient polls/checks | Queries for new messages |\n| 5 | Recipient downloads | Gets encrypted blob |\n| 6 | Recipient decrypts | Ciphertext → Plaintext (private key) |\n| 7 | Recipient stores locally | SQLite/MD files |\n\n**Server Responsibilities:**\n- Receive encrypted blob\n- Store temporarily (TTL-based)\n- Serve to recipient when requested\n- **Never sees:** plaintext, sender identity, content\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"Real time talk won't it be a little hard? What does usually chat software uses?\" — Feb 7, 2026\n>\n> Assistant: \"Real-time (WebSockets): Maintains persistent connection. Feels instant. But complex.\" — Feb 7, 2026\n>\n> Allan: \"I'm thinking more like a Email or sms kind. We discussed before, For the p2p messages, Can be saved at locally in a sqlite db or as datebased md files.\" — Feb 7, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 3. Relationship Privacy Model\n\n**Function:** Who can message whom? How are relationships stored?\n\n**Decision:** **Open discovery + local relationship storage**\n\n[1200 more lines in file. Use offset=100 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773596035183}}
