{"type":"message","id":"9bcfd844","parentId":"cde2a3b7","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:36:06.431Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The heartbeat has arrived. I should report my progress briefly. I just corrected the Contacts section based on Allan's feedback - server knows who talks to whom, but not the message content. Parents can see messages locally.Corrected Contacts section: server knows who talks to whom, not message content. Parents can see locally. Waiting for approval."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1ef18ec066f24fc5a8b3bdb7","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md","newText":"## 1:04 AM (Timeless Approach)\n\n- Allan: whitepaper should be timeless, focus on WHAT and WHY\n- Protocol details may change - should not be in whitepaper\n- Decided: call it \"Message System\" not \"Message Protocol\"\n- Drafted Message System section: E2E encryption, zero-knowledge server, local storage, async delivery\n- Kept general concepts, removed implementation details\n- New structure: About, Message System, Relationships, Access Control\n- Waiting for Allan's approval to update\n\n## 1:15 AM (Neural Model Task - Ignored)\n\n- Allan said to ignore the neural model training message\n- Back to Message System section\n\n## 1:21 AM (Message System Finalized)\n\n- Allan provided final Message System content\n- Simpler, more concise than my draft\n\n## 1:26 AM (Contacts vs Relationships)\n\n- Allan: \"Follow\" is for public forum app, not chat\n- For chat (like WeChat/WhatsApp), should use \"Contacts\"\n- Checked discussion doc: has following/followers/friends/blocked\n- Decided: change \"Relationships\" to \"Contacts\"\n\n## 1:32 AM (Server Transparency Clarification)\n\n- Allan corrected: server DOES know who talks to whom (for routing)\n- Server doesn't know message content (encrypted)\n- Parents can see messages locally (transparent to parents)\n- Updated Contacts section to reflect this\n- Waiting for Allan's approval","oldText":"## 1:04 AM (Timeless Approach)\n\n- Allan: whitepaper should be timeless, focus on WHAT and WHY\n- Protocol details may change - should not be in whitepaper\n- Decided: call it \"Message System\" not \"Message Protocol\"\n- Drafted Message System section: E2E encryption, zero-knowledge server, local storage, async delivery\n- Kept general concepts, removed implementation details\n- New structure: About, Message System, Relationships, Access Control\n- Waiting for Allan's approval to update"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":82919,"output":521,"cacheRead":13888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97328,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773596126654}}
