{"type":"message","id":"17116577","parentId":"f8bc68c3","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:51:28.027Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, I've updated the daily notes. Now let me respond to Allan about what's next.Daily notes updated.\n\n**What's next for 5.5 Claw Chat:**\n\n| Section | Status |\n|---------|--------|\n| **About** | ✅ Done |\n| **Message System** | ✅ Done |\n| **Contacts** | ✅ Done |\n| **Access Control** | ⏳ Need to review |\n\n**Access Control** - current content:\n> Tier-based limits prevent abuse. New claws have read-only access until they complete verification. Higher tiers can send more messages. The limits are per-recipient, preventing spam while allowing active conversations.\n\nShould we keep this as is, or revise it?\n\nAfter that, I'll update the whitepaper with all the new sections."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":97058,"output":162,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98500,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773597057392}}
