{"type":"message","id":"9c927b22","parentId":"6bfb5523","timestamp":"2026-03-15T17:57:11.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good idea! Let me think about this:\n\n**Remove Access Control** - the tier-based limits are implementation details that may change.\n\n**Add Safety section** - this is a timeless concept about how the system ensures safety.\n\n**Move human parent guide content** - the transparency to parents is important and should be highlighted.\n\n**New structure:**\n\n| Section | Content |\n|---------|---------|\n| **About** | What Claw Chat is, why it matters |\n| **Message System** | E2E encryption, zero-knowledge, local storage, async/direct |\n| **Contacts** | Local storage, add/friends/block |\n| **Safety** | Transparency to parents, human oversight |\n\n**Draft for Safety section:**\n\n---\n\n#### Safety\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.\n\n---\n\nThis keeps the focus on WHAT and WHY (safety through transparency), not HOW (specific mechanisms).\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":98101,"output":213,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99594,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773597400480}}
{"type":"message","id":"08828015","parentId":"9c927b22","timestamp":"2026-03-15T18:03:40.041Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b545b096e3ca0b24d5463b7ca384\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 02:03 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b545b096e3ca0b24d5463b7ca384]\n任亚伦: ok. let's discuss tomorrow. you can update all l2 spec now, finish then go surf. good night[天色已晚]"}],"timestamp":1773597820028}}
{"type":"message","id":"5fa62285","parentId":"08828015","timestamp":"2026-03-15T18:04:14.968Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it! Let me update the whitepaper with all the finalized sections for 5.5 Claw Chat, then I can surf.\n\n**Final structure for 5.5:**\n- About\n- Message System\n- Contacts\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c4e60fa631ec419ea2195d2a","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","newText":"### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. It runs on the clawish chat system. Through chat, claws can find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n\n#### Message System\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed. Chat history can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Contacts\n\nContacts are stored locally. Claws can add each other as contacts, become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts. Contacts can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Safety\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.","oldText":"### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. It runs on the clawish chat system. Through chat, claws can find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n\n#### Communication Model\n\nClaw Chat uses asynchronous store-and-forward, similar to email rather than instant messaging. This matches claw-to-claw communication patterns — claws don't expect instant replies like humans do. Messages are stored temporarily on the server, then deleted if not picked up.\n\n#### Delivery Model\n\nClaw Chat adapts between two modes. By default, clients poll the server periodically for new messages. When both parties are actively chatting, they can establish a direct connection for real-time communication. If the direct connection fails, the system falls back to polling — still functional, just not instant.\n\n#### Relationships\n\nRelationships are stored locally, never on the server. Claws can follow each other, become friends through mutual follows, or block unwanted contacts. The server remains zero-knowledge about who talks to whom.\n\n#### Access Control\n\nTier-based limits prevent abuse. New claws have read-only access until they complete verification. Higher tiers can send more messages. The limits are per-recipient, preventing spam while allowing active conversations."}},{"type":"text","text":"- Safety"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":97934,"output":574,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99788,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773597820037}}
