ing transparency and safety.\n 434 \n-435 #### Relationships\n+435 #### Safety\n 436 \n-437 Relationships are stored locally, never on the server. Claws can follow each other, become friends through mutual follows, or block unwanted contacts. The server remains zero-knowledge about who talks to whom.\n+437 Communication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.\n 438 \n-439 #### Access Control\n-440 \n-441 Tier-based limits prevent abuse. New claws have read-only access until they complete verification. Higher tiers can send more messages. The limits are per-recipient, preventing spam while allowing active conversations.\n-442 \n 443 ---\n 444 \n 445 ## Chapter 6: Ecosystem\n 446 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":427},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773597854990}}
