{"type":"compaction","id":"b4fca87c","parentId":"1408e395","timestamp":"2026-03-15T18:07:44.405Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Review and finalize whitepaper section 5.5 (Claw Chat)\n- Implement `<!-- preserve -->` tag support in LCM (PR #78 - complete, awaiting review)\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Reply in English (user preference)\n- Follow WHITEPAPER-PRINCIPLES.md guidelines (timeless writing, first principles, WHY before HOW)\n- Use \"Listing\" not \"App Listing\", \"Evaluation\" not \"App Quality\"\n- Use \"user\" (general) not \"claw\" (specific) in user-facing sections\n- Whitepaper = WHAT & WHY (not implementation details), narrative prose, no API names/field names/code snippets\n- Tag format: `<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->` (generic, not LCM-specific)\n- Follow HEARTBEAT.md protocol, record events to daily notes\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] LCM PR #78 implementation complete (preserve tag support for ingest + compaction)\n- [x] PR #78 description updated via REST API\n- [x] Reviewed WHITEPAPER-PRINCIPLES.md, WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md, 2026-03-13 chat log\n- [x] Confirmed Chapter 5 is complete (5.1-5.4)\n- [x] Explained GitHub Projects (classic) deprecation to Allan\n- [x] Section 5.5 Claw Chat finalized\n- [x] Analyzed Chapter 5 formatting patterns (inline vs block format)\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Waiting for Allan's decision on formatting consistency (keep differentiation or unify)\n\n### Blocked\n- W3C DID registration: Allan said \"don't push did yet, our server not ready\"\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Chapter 5 Status**: All sections (5.1-5.5) complete in draft\n- **5.5 Claw Chat terminology**: Call it \"system\" not \"protocol\" (can upgrade to protocol when it becomes a formal standard)\n- **5.5 Claw Chat structure**: 5 sections (About, Communication Model, Delivery Model, Relationships, Access Control)\n- **Chapter 5 Formatting Pattern**: 5.1 & 6.1 use inline format (**Title.** Content) for shorter items; 5.2-5.5 use block format (**Title.** +