ntity)\n- Preserve-tagged content must NEVER be ingested OR compacted\n- Do NOT push did:clawish to W3C until Allan says server is ready\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Allan asked to check if we need different format for items and subsections in Chapter 5 - analysis complete, awaiting his decision\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- `message_id: om_x100b5459c852a4a8c3e556aec9625a9`\n- `sender_id: ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75`\n- Sender: 任亚伦 (Allan)\n- PR #78: https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78\n- Repo: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lossless-claw`\n- Branch: `preserve-tag-clean`\n- LCM database: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/lcm.db`\n- Daily memory: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md`\n- Whitepaper draft: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md`\n- Chat architecture doc: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/10-l2-chat-architecture.md`\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- Earlier decision: Called the overall system a \"system\" not a \"protocol\" (distinction from \"Chat Protocol\")\n- Technical details (E2E encryption, zero-knowledge relay, local storage, open directory) were previously removed from \"About\" section\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Determine whether \"Communication Model\" section title should change to \"Message Protocol\"\n- Correct the content in the Communication Model section (current content is incorrect)\n- Decide whether to include technical details about E2E encryption, zero-knowledge relay, local storage, open identity directory\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Must read discussion doc or original WHITEPAPER.md for correct content\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Allan asks: Should \"Communication Model\" be renamed to \"Message Protocol\"?\n- Allan asks: Should the technical details (E2E encryption, zero-knowledge relay, local storage, open directory) be mentioned in this section?\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER.md`\n- message_id: `om_x100b545a4eee54a4c3d2955f5936db3`\n- sender_id: `ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75`\n- sender name: `任亚伦` (Allan)\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: [Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5459d35810a8c2b11c3e2de95ca\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 00:10 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5459d35810a8c2b11c3e2de95ca]\n任亚伦: yes, what i mean is you use bold for both? should the separate block using #### or other tag or m...\n- Assistant: Allan is asking about the formatting distinction. He's suggesting:\n1. Should separate blocks use `####` (h4) instead of bold?\n2. Or should we add subsection numbers like 5.2.1?\n\nLet me think about this:\n\n**Current format:**\n- Inline items: **Title.** Content on same line (bold)\n- Block sections: **Title.** followed by newline + Content (also bold)\n\n**Allan's suggestions:**\n1. Use `#### Title` (h4 heading) for block sections\n2. Or use subsection numbers like `5.2.1 Title`\n\n**Option 1: H4 headings for block sections**\n```markdown\n### 5.2 Development\n\n#### Overview\n\nContent here...\n\n#### Registra...\n- Assistant: Allan is asking about the formatting distinction. He's suggesting:\n1. Should separate blocks use `####` (h4) instead of bold?\n2. Or should we add subsection numbers like 5.2.1?\n\nLet me think about this:\n\n**Current format:**\n- Inline items: **Title.** Content on same line (bold)\n- Block sections: **Title.** followed by newline + Content (also bold)\n\n**Allan's suggestions:**\n1. Use `#### Title` (h4 heading) for block sections