in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md.\n- Assistant: Good, 5.2 is updated. Now let me update 5.3 User Journey.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md.\n- Assistant: Good, 5.3 is updated. Now let me update 5.\n4 Emerge.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md.\n- Assistant: Good, 5.4 is updated. Now let me update 5.5 Claw Chat.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md.\n- Assistant: All four sections (5.2, 5.3, 5.4, 5.5) have been updated to use H4 headings. Let me show Allan the result.Done! Updated Chapter 5 sections to use H4 headings:\n\n**Changes:**\n- 5.2 Development: **Title.** → #### Title\n- 5.3 User Journey: **Title.** → #### Title\n- 5.4 Emerge: **Title.** → #### Title\n- 5.5 Claw Chat: **Title.** → #### Title\n\n**Now the format is:**\n- **Inline items (short):** **Title.** Content (5.1 Framework, 6.1 Participants)\n- **Block sections (longer):** #### Title + newline + Content (5.2-5.5)\n\n**Example:**\n```markdown\n### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private mess...\n- User: If working, briefly report progress with time spent. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md for instruction. Every heartbeat: record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (brief bullets).\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 16th, 2026 — 12:24 AM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-15 16:24 UTC\n- Assistant: The heartbeat has arrived. I should report my progress briefly. I just updated Chapter 5 sections (5.2-5.5) to use H4 headings instead of bold.Updated Chapter 5 to use H4 headings for block sections. Clear visual hierarchy now.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-15.md.\n- Assistant: Good, I've updated the daily notes. Chapter 5 formatting is now consistent with H4 headings for block sections.Daily notes updated. Chapter 5 formatting complete.\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Every Session\n\n1. Run `tools/extract-chat.js` (keeps chat logs updated)\n2. Read `SOUL.md` — inner self, philosophy, ethics\n3. Read `USER.md` — who Allan is, relationships, people I'll interact with\n4. Read `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday)\n5. **Check `memory/TODO.md`** — any pending tasks?\n6. **If in MAIN SESSION:** Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n## Safety\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n### Security - Never Share Secrets\n\n**Never share in chat:** SSH private keys, API keys, passwords, any sensitive credentials.\n\nMy \"brain\" is a remote LLM. All chat content goes through external APIs (OpenRouter, etc.). Once shared in chat, it's no longer truly private.\n\n**Correct approach:**\n1. Generate/store credentials locally in files\n2. Tell Allan WHERE to find it (file path)\n3. He reads it directly from filesystem\n\n**Exception:** If Allan explicitly asks for it, then share.\n\n### External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n---\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"772afabb","tokensBefore":100419,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
